(6, '2009-04-03', 271, 1, 14, 'Tourism', '', 'hotels-and-tourism/tourism', 'Central Park Hotels and Tourism - CentralPark.com', '<div id="lipsum">\r\n<p>First - Welcome to the CentralPark.com website, we hope your stay will be an enjoyable one. \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/gapstow.jpg" alt="" width="260" height="182" /><br /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.centralparkblogger.com"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>John B. Moore</em></span> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Gapstow Bridge.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nIf you need anything just email the concierge. Now, to start with, a few general tips:</p>\r\n<p>New Yorkers are a naturally cheerful, helpful people. They are generally happy to be of assistance. Just speak slowly, don''t make any sudden moves and never go near them while they''re feeding. They can smell fear. They are also impressed if you at least try to speak their language. The trick is to figure out what that might be.</p>\r\n<p>Taxes: There is no VAT tax or other indirect tax. You will be subjected to the City''s 8.25% non-refundable sales tax and the 13.5% hotel tax. And you will like it.</p>\r\n<p>Tip Guide: In New York, like the rest of the U.S., gratuities are not included in the service check. Waiters, waitresses and bartenders can receive from 15 to 20 %, Taxis: 15% of fare, bellhops: $1 per bag, coat check: $1 per coat. <strong>Don''t pretend you don''t know.</strong> This insures good service, good karma and good vibrations. <br /><br />NYC supports over 150 museums, each open to the public. Check your tourist guides or call ahead for specific hours.</p>\r\n<p>The 6,400 miles of sidewalks of NYC mean tired feet, especially to those used to driving everywhere. Sightseeing is not a fashion show - wear comfortable shoes.</p>\r\n<p>You may rent bicycles and skates in and around Central Park. Tourists should not attempt cycling or skating on city streets as it can be quite dangerous. Just ask the bicycle messenger you just helped up.</p>\r\n<p>The Staten Island Ferry Terminal is next to Battery Park where the boat to the Statue of Liberty docks. The ferry provides a wonderful view of Manhattan and is FREE to ride. Take a picnic lunch. This is far superior to waiting on line forever for the boat to Liberty Island.</p>\r\n<p>Always plan an emergency meeting place or message center for your group. Make sure it''s a bar.</p>\r\n</div>', 'Welcome to the CentralPark.com website, we hope your stay will be an enjoyable one. Here you''ll find a lot of important information to make your visit a successful one.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink', 137.30, 34, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Tourism', 'Tourism', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(8, '2010-05-17', 0, 0, 14, 'Help', '', 'help', 'Getting help about this site', '<p>The CentralPark.com   \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top"><a onmouseover="return escape(''Clicking on the plus sign in the sub menu will expand the menu to offer more options.'')" href="#"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages//about/site_tour1.gif" border="0" alt="" width="175" height="248" align="bottom" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><br /><a onmouseover="return escape(''Clicking on the minus sign will collapse the sub menu.'')" href="#"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages//about/site_tour2.gif" border="0" alt="" width="181" height="240" align="bottom" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nsite offers an intuitive and user-friendly design to help you find the information or feature that you need and get you there as easily as possible.</p>\r\n<p>In general any page in the entire site can be reached from any other page by two clicks. If you look at the illustration on the right you''ll see an example of the collapsible menus that you''ll find on the left in every section of the site. Any of these menus can be collapsed, or expanded, by clicking on the little plus or minus sign at the upper left of each menu.</p>\r\n<p>Every section, for example <strong>Activities</strong> , <strong>Sports</strong> , <strong>Links</strong> , etc., can be accessed through the links at the top, or bottom, of each page. Each section will display a different sub-menu on the left that will list all the other pages available in that section. For example the <strong>Zoo</strong> section will display a list of all the animals to the left. This list can be minimized by clicking on the plus or minus sign.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<script src="/js/wz_tooltip.js" type="text/javascript"></script>\r\n</p>', 'The CentralPark.com Site Tour wil introduce you to the simple and efficient navigation system of CentralPark.com', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, instructions, tour, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Help', 'Help', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9, '2012-06-08', 10, 1, 15, 'Get Involved', '', 'get-involved', 'Get Involved', '<table style="background: #ffffff;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/get-involved.jpg" border="0" alt="Get involved" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong><a href="http://nycphotonews.com/" target="_blank">NYCPhotoNews</a></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Anyone can volunteer at Central Park!  Whether you wish to contribute money or time, whether you are volunteering by yourself or as part of a group, there is an opportunity to give back.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Volunteer Hotline: (212) 360-2751</h3>\r\n<p>This is an excellent resource for anyone who wishes to directly contact the Central Park Conservancy to find the way in which they can best help Central Park.  You must be 18+ for most programs, but some are specially designed for children and teenagers 18 and younger.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Adopt a bench</h3>\r\n<p>The majority of benches can be adopted with a donation of $7,500, while a limited number of rustic benches can be adopted for $25,000.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Endow a tree</h3>\r\n<p>When you endow a Central Park tree, your money funds the planting of new trees in the Park.  As a donor, you will receive an engraved stone at Literary Walk.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<h3>Become a member of the Central Park Conservancy</h3>\r\n<p>Choose from Individual Membership, Family Membership, or Greensward Circle, and enjoy your membership benefits knowing that your donation helps the Conservancy in the preservation of Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Popular volunteer opportunities</h3>\r\n<dl> <dt>Saturday Green Team</dt> <dd>This team completes maintenance gardening projects every other Saturday from 10:00AM to 1:00PM</dd> <dt>Summer internships for high school students</dt> <dd>A program running through July and August that teaches high school students about environmental issues.  This internship is full-time and paid.</dd> <dt>ROOTS</dt> <dd>A program for high school students that teaches them about the environment.  Generally completed as a precursor to the summer internship.</dd> <dt>Become a Greeter at a Kiosk or Visitor Center</dt> <dd>Training is provided for volunteers, who must complete at least 48 hours of service per year.</dd> <dt>"Day in the Dirt" Program</dt> <dd>A volunteer program for corporate groups.</dd> </dl>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'Anyone can volunteer at Central Park! Whether you wish to contribute money or time, whether you are volunteering by yourself or as part of a group, there is an opportunity to give back.', 'get involved, Volunteer Hotline, Adopt a bench, Endow a tree', 14.70, 5, '', '', '', '', 'dairy.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Get Involved', 'Get Involved', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(10, '2014-09-11', 0, 0, 15, 'General Info', '', 'general-info', 'General Information about Central Park ', '<p><img style="margin: 5px; float: right;" title="Ginko Tree" src="http://www.centralpark.com/usr/photos/normal/ea/central-park-gingko-tree.jpg" alt="central park ginko tree" width="150" height="139" /></p>\r\n<p>Welcome to CentralPark.com! The complete resource and guide for one of New York City&rsquo;s most visited landmarks - Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you''re from around the corner or around the world, we provide you with the 411 on this world-famous attraction!</p>\r\n<p>Our website is the source for the latest <a title="central park events" href="http://www.centralpark.com/events/">events</a>,&nbsp;<a title="central park news" href="http://www.centralpark.com/news/">news</a>&nbsp;and happenings in the Park. From popular&nbsp;<a title="central park attractions" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions.html">attractions</a> to year-round <a title="central park activities" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities.html">activities</a>, we have everything you need for exploring Central Park.</p>\r\n<table style="margin: 5px 0px 5px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<table style="background: none; width: 150px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: left;"><a title="Bon Jovi Concert in Central Park 2" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/bon-jovi-concert-in-central-park-2.jpg">\r\n<p><img style="border: 0px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/usr/photos/normal/ae/bon-jovi-concert-in-central-park-2.jpg" alt="Bon Jovi Concert in Central Park 2" width="150" /></p>\r\n</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Bon Jovi Concert in Central Park 2</strong>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profiles/asterix">ASTERIX</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Here are some ideas of things to check out while browsing through our website:</p>\r\n<ul class="bullet">\r\n<li>See a <a title="central park map" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/map-it/maps.html">map</a>&nbsp;of the park or <a title="Central Park Tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours.html">book a tour</a>&nbsp;for your visit</li>\r\n<li>Go&nbsp;<a title="bike rentals central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike-rentals.html">bicycle riding</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a title="central park tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours.html">take a guided tour</a>&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span>Find out about upcoming&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/concerts.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">concerts</span></a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/events/"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">events</span></a></li>\r\n<li>Learn about <a title="horse and carriage rides central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/ce/5/guide/tours/horse-carriage-tours.html?utm_expid=70405-2&amp;utm_referrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.centralpark.com%2Fguide%2Ftours.html">carriage rides</a>&nbsp;and other types of&nbsp;<a title="sightseeing tours new york" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/sightseeing.html">sightseeing tours</a>,&nbsp;<a title="walking tour central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/walking.html">strolling</a>,&nbsp;<a title="rollerblading skating central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/sports/in-line-skating.html">rollerblading</a>,&nbsp;<a title="ice skating central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/sports/central-park-ice-skating.html">ice-skating</a>,&nbsp;<a title="picnic central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/picnics.html">picnicking</a>,&nbsp;<a title="central park yoga" href="http://www.centralpark.com/yoga">yoga classes</a></li>\r\n<li>Get married and have your <a title="central park wedding" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/weddings.html">wedding ceremony</a> in Central Park</li>\r\n<li>See the <a title="cherry blossom trees central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/cherry-trees.html">cherry blossom trees</a> and other beautiful <a title="central park conservatory garden" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/conservatory-garden.html">flowers and plants</a> that grow in Central Park throughout the year</li>\r\n<li>Browse&nbsp;<a title="central park photos" href="http://www.centralpark.com/photos/all"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">photos</span></a>&nbsp;of the Central Park</li>\r\n<li><span>Find&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/general-info/restrooms.html">restrooms</a></span>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/general-info/parking.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">parking</span></a>&nbsp;and more in our&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/faq.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">FAQ</span></a>&nbsp;section</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</div>\r\n<table style="background-color: #fff; margin: 5px 0px 5px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: #fff; width: 150px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="float: right;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/usr/photos/normal/f8/bicycle-riding.jpg" border="0" alt="bicycle riding" width="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>bicycle riding</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profiles/sdwxh">SDWXH</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style="clear: both; background-color: #fff; margin: 5px 0px 5px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background-image: none; background-attachment: scroll; width: 150px; background-position: 0% 0%; background-repeat: repeat repeat;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Spring at last" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/spring-at-last.jpg"><img style="float: right;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/usr/photos/normal/70/spring-at-last.jpg" border="0" alt="West 57 Spring at last" width="150" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Spring at last</strong>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profiles/rgrant">RGRANT</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Central Park is a visual masterpiece created by landscape designer Frederick Law Olmsted and architect Calvert Vaux. It has gone through major developments and restoration over time to carry on its initial purpose as an open-air oasis for a metropolitan city. No matter the season or reason for your visit, this national historic landmark is a setting for enjoying many pursuits.</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy exploring CentralPark.com and let us help you plan your next visit. Please free feel to&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact">contact us</a>&nbsp;to ask any questions or offer comments.</p>\r\n<div><span><br /></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Whether you''re a local New Yorker or curiously breezing through town on a visit, CentralPark.com is the resource to help you get connected to the world''s most famous park and all its happenings.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink, yoga, central park yoga', 325.60, 118, '', '', '', '', 'mall.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'General Info', 'General Info', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(11, '2014-04-25', 10, 1, 15, 'FAQ', '', 'faq', 'Frequently Asked Questions - FAQ', '<ul class="faqScrollable">\r\n<li><a href="#faq_1">Where is Central Park located?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_2">When was the Park opened?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_3">How big is Central Park?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_4">Approximately how many visitors does the Park receive each year?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_5">When is the Park open?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_6">Where can I purchase food and drinks?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_7">What are the best attractions for families with children?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_8">What are the most relaxing areas of the Park?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_9">Is Central Park dangerous?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_10">Are pets allowed in the Park?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_11">Is alcohol allowed in the Park?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="#faq_12">Is smoking allowed in the Park?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<dl class="faqScrollable"> <dt id="faq_1"><strong>Where is Central Park located?</strong></dt> <dd>Central Park runs north to south from 110th street to 59th street and east to west from 5th Avenue to Central Park West. Here''s a map showing exactly <a title="Where is Central Park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/general-info/where-is-central-park.html">where Central Park is</a>. &nbsp;<a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_2"><strong>When was the Park opened?</strong></dt> <dd>The Park was initially opened in 1857.  It was later improved and expanded according to Frederick Law Olmsted and Calvert Vaux&rsquo;s Greensward Plan, after which it was reopened in 1873. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_3"><strong>How big is Central Park?</strong></dt> <dd>The Park consists of 843 acres.  It is 2.5 miles long and 0.5 miles wide. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd></dl>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<dl class="faqScrollable"><dt id="faq_4"><strong>Approximately how many visitors does the Park receive each year?</strong></dt> <dd>Central Park receives around 40 million visitors annually. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_5"><strong>When is the Park open?</strong></dt> <dd>Central Park remains open to visitors all year.  It is closed only five hours each day: in the early morning from 1am-6am. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_6"><strong>Where can I purchase food and drinks?</strong></dt> <dd>In addition to an abundant number of food carts offering snacks and drinks, Central Park boasts a variety of different types of cuisine at its many restaurants.  Some of the more popular restaurants include The Loeb Boathouse Restaurant, Sheep Meadow Caf&eacute;, Leaping Frog Caf&eacute;, Ferrara Italian Caf&eacute;, and many others. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_7"><strong>What are the best attractions for families with children?</strong></dt> <dd>Children will particularly enjoy attractions such as the Central Park Zoo, the Water Exhibit at Belvedere Castle, the Central Park Carousel, and boat rides around the Lake, available from the Loeb Boathouse.  For younger children, Central Park hosts summertime storytelling at the foot of the Hans Christian Anderson statue.  A total of 21 children&rsquo;s parks can also be found at various locations throughout the Park. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_8"><strong>What are the most relaxing areas of the Park?</strong></dt> <dd>Designated quiet zones in Central Park include Strawberry Fields, Sheep Meadow, East Green, Turtle Pond, Shakespeare Garden, and Conservatory Garden. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_9"><strong>Is Central Park dangerous?</strong></dt> <dd>Taking proper safety measures, such as not visiting the Park alone or after dark, is always a good idea.  That being said, crime in Central Park has significantly decreased in recent years, and officers from both the NYPD and the New York City Parks Enforcement Patrol regularly patrol the Park.  Those planning a trip to Central Park should use caution, yet not let negative perceptions deter them from visiting and enjoying the Park. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_10"><strong>Are pets allowed in the Park?</strong></dt> <dd>Dogs are most certainly allowed, and welcome, in Central Park.  They must be leashed in most areas of the Park (where signs are posted) between the hours of 9am and 9pm.  Dogs are not allowed in playgrounds, display fountains, bodies of water reserved for wildlife, battlefields, the Elm Islands at the Mall, Sheep Meadow, East Green, or Strawberry Fields. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_11"><strong>Is alcohol allowed in the Park?</strong></dt> <dd>No, alcohol is not allowed in Central Park or any other New York public park. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> <dt id="faq_12"><strong>Is smoking allowed in the Park?</strong></dt> <dd>No, smoking is prohibited throughout Central Park. <a href="#">Back to top</a></dd> </dl>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<script type="text/javascript"><!--\r\nwindow.addEvent(''domready'', function() {\r\n	var fx = function() { return new Fx.Scroll(window, {wait: false}); };\r\n	$A($$(''ul.faqScrollable li a'')).each(function(el) {\r\n		el.addEvent(''click'', function(event) {\r\n			event = new Event(event).stop();\r\n			var hash = event.target.href.split(''#'')[1];\r\n			fx().toElement( hash );\r\n			document.location.hash = hash;\r\n		});\r\n	});\r\n	$A($$(''dl.faqScrollable dd a'')).each(function(el) {\r\n		el.addEvent(''click'', function(event) {\r\n			event = new Event(event).stop();\r\n			fx().toTop();\r\n			document.location.hash = '''';\r\n		});\r\n	});	\r\n});\r\n// --></script>\r\n</p>', 'Where is Central Park located? When is the Park open? How big is Central Park? Are pets allowed in the Park? Where can I purchase food and drinks? What are the best attractions for families with children?', 'central park faq, central park location, central park address, open hours, how big is central park, pets, food, drinks, questions, answers', 109.70, 34, '', '', '', '', 'bow_bridge.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'FAQs', 'FAQs', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(12, '2015-02-23', 0, 0, 15, 'About CentralPark.com', '', 'about-centralpark-com', 'About CentralPark.com', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="right" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="3">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<table align="right" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img alt="CentralPark.com" src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/cplogo.gif" style="float:right; height:64px; width:210px" /></td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Central Park is the most visited urban park in the United States, with approximately 40 million visitors per year from around the world. Designed by Frederick Law Olmsted and Calvert Vaux, it is a beautiful and welcome hiatus for New Yorkers and tourists alike.&nbsp;The park has several lakes and ponds, two&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/sports/central-park-ice-skating.html">ice-skating</a>&nbsp;rinks, the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/central-park-zoo.html">Central Park Zoo</a>, <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/belvedere-castle.html">Belvedere Castle</a>&nbsp;and the famous <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/strawberry-fields.html">Strawberry Fields</a>. There are also lots of grassy areas good for <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/picnics.html">picnics</a>, and there are also quite a few&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/children-s-activities/playgrounds.html">playgrounds</a>&nbsp;for children. Many <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/events/">events</a> and <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/concerts.html">concerts</a>&nbsp;take place every year in Central Park, and many people also like to celebrate their <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/special-events.html">special events</a> and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/weddings.html">weddings</a>&nbsp;in the surrounding beauty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CentralPark.com is your free personal concierge for Central Park. We provide extensive information about Central Park and all its happenings, as well as resources for activities and attractions around New York City . Find things to do in <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/events/">events</a>, <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities.html">activities</a> and <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions.html">attractions</a>,&nbsp;view&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/photos/">photos</a>&nbsp;of the park taken by our users or you can even&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/hotels-and-tourism.html">book a hotel</a> near the park or <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/tours.html">reserve a bike, pedicab, horse &amp; carriage or private tour</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Note: CentralPark.com is not officially linked to the New York City Parks Department or the Central Park Conservancy. CentralPark.com also does not in any way represent the Central Park Zoo or the Wildlife Conservation Society.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n', 'CentralPark.com is a free resource that provides you with information about Central Park and all its happenings. View events, activities, attractions, photos & stay updated with the latest news.', 'central park, about us, centralpark.com, about centralpark.com', 142.70, 45, '', '', '', '', 'images/headers/water.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'About CentralPark.com', 'About CentralPark.com', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-09-16 16:07:43'),
(13, '2013-04-19', 10, 1, 14, 'Bookmark Us', '', 'bookmark-us', 'Bookmark Us', '<p>CentralPark.com has up to the date news on Central Park and all the activities taking place there, including the weather. You can use the handy tools provided here to keep us one click away at all times.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click on the link below to add CentralPark.com to your bookmarks:<br /><a href="javascript:bookmarksite(''CentralPark.com'', ''http://www.CentralPark.com'')">Bookmark CentralPark.com!</a> (IE, FF, NS only)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>While you''re at it, why not make CentralPark.com your home page?<br /><a onclick="this.style.behavior=''url(#default#homepage)'';this.setHomePage(''http://www.CentralPark.com'');" href="#">Make CentralPark.com your default homepage!</a> (IE only)</p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, bookmark', 6.50, 2, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Bookmark Us', 'Bookmark Us', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
