(23, '2013-10-25', 2, 1, 15, 'Alice in Wonderland', '', 'attractions/alice-in-wonderland', 'Alice in Wonderland in Central Park', '<p>Located just north of the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/conservatory-water.html">Conservatory Water</a> at East 74th Street, Alice in Wonderland stands&nbsp;eleven feet tall in bronze, surrounded by the Mad Hatter, the White Rabbit and a few of her other friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style="width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="margin: 4px; border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/alice.jpg" alt="Alice in Wonderland" width="200" height="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Alice in Wonderland in Central Park</strong> <br /> by <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile2893.html"><em>gracepap</em></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The sculpture was constructed in 1959 by&nbsp;Jos&eacute; de Creeft&nbsp;under the commission of philanthropist George Delacorte so that children could visit and experience the wonder of Lewis Carroll&rsquo;s classic story. Atypical of most sculptures, children are invited to climb, touch and crawl all over Alice and her friends. In fact, through the decades thousands of hands and feet have literally polished parts of the statue&rsquo;s surface smooth.</p>\r\n<p><span>Visit Alice in Wonderland during one of our Central Park&nbsp;</span><a title="horse and carriage tours central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/horse-carriage-tours.html">horse and carriage tours</a><span>,&nbsp;</span><a title="central park bike tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike.html">bike tours</a><span>,&nbsp;</span><a title="central park pedicab tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/pedicab.html">pedicab tours</a><span>, or&nbsp;</span><a title="central park walking tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/pedicab.html">walking tours</a><span>.</span></p>\r\n<p>The design for the bronze sculpture was patterned off the original illustrations of John Tenniel that were used in the first published edition of the book.  The obvious centerpiece of the work, Alice, who depicts the face of Creeft&rsquo;s daughter, Donna, is pictured sitting on a giant mushroom reaching toward a pocket watch held by the White Rabbit. Peering over her shoulder is the Cheshire Cat, surrounded by the Dormouse, Alice''s cat Dinah, and the Mad Hatter -- a caricature of George Delacorte. &nbsp;</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>The sculptor also included an inscription in a granite circle surrounding the work: a line from &ldquo;The Jabberwocky,&rdquo; also by Lewis Carroll: &ldquo;''Twas brillig, and the slithy toves did gyre and gimble in the wabe.&rdquo;</p>', 'Ones of Central Park''s most cherished sculptures is a depiction in bronze of Alice and her friends, the characters from Lewis Carroll''s Alice in Wonderland.', 'Alice, Alice in Wonderland, lewis carroll, sculpture, Alice in Wonderland in Central Park, children, mad hatter, white rabbit, cheshire cat, dormouse, ', 235.80, 59, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Alice in Wonderland', 'Alice in Wonderland', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(24, '2013-12-02', 2, 1, 15, 'Balto', '', 'attractions/balto', 'Balto Statue in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Balto" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/balto_statue_central_park_m.jpg"> <img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/balto_statue_central_park_m.jpg" alt="Balto" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Balto</strong>, by <br /><a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/centralpark/monuments/75">City of New York Parks &amp; Recreation</a></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>There is a bronzed hero, near the Tisch Children''s Zoo, who stands ready to accept hugs and offer rides to his admiring fans.</p>\r\n<p>The hero is Balto the sled dog who has nobly stood on a rock outcropping since 1925.  His statue, a big favorite in the Park, is located west of East Drive and 67th Street and north of the Zoo.</p>\r\n<p>Back in 1925 Nome, Alaska was stricken with a horrific diphtheria outbreak. Not enough antitoxin was available to treat all the sick until teams of mushers and sled dogs battled a blinding blizzard and traveled 674 miles to deliver the medicine.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>Balto, a husky, was one of the heroic lead dogs.</p>\r\n<p>In recognition of such bravery, the famed Brooklyn born sculptor Frederick George Richard Roth was commissioned to create a lasting tribute.</p>\r\n<p>Roth, whose other work at Park includes <em>Tales of Mother Goose</em> and <em>Dancing Goat and Dancing Bear</em>, unveiled the statue on December 16, 1925.  The most important among the honored guests was the real Balto himself.</p>\r\n<p>Over the past nine decades, Balto&rsquo;s statue has been a favorite as evidenced by the deep burnishing of his ears and back. Children and others frequently climb up on him for a photo opp, or to contemplate life and the stirring words on the statue&rsquo;s plaque:&nbsp;Endurance &middot; Fidelity &middot; Intelligence.&nbsp;Good words for today''s heroes and heroines too.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Location</strong>: <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/map-it/attractions/balto.html">East Drive at 67th Street</a></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Linda J. Bottjer</small></p>\r\n<p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>', 'Balto the sled dog has nobly stood on a rock outcropping in Central Park since 1925. His statue, a big favorite in the Park, is located west of East Drive and 67th Street and north of the Zoo.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, Balto, sled dog, alaskan malamute, sculpture, children, family', 245.40, 60, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Balto', 'Balto', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(26, '2012-06-08', 1, 1, 15, 'Soccer', '', 'sports/soccer', 'Soccer in Central Park', '<p>You can play soccer in Central Park from mid-September to mid-November. However, you must apply for a permit to organize a game. Permits are $10 for each session. If you wish to organize a game in the park, you must state on the application how many players and spectators you expect to attend. The permit application can be sent to or dropped off at the <a title="Arsenal" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/arsenal.html">Arsenal</a> building at 64th Street and Fifth Avenue.</p>\r\n<p>In addition to adult programs, there are several youth soccer teams that play in Central Park. The Central Park Conservancy runs a youth soccer clinic for its members on weekday afternoons.  There, young players can learn the finer points of game technique, as well as sportsmanship. The clinic hosts a scrimmage each class for players to practice what they have learned.</p>\r\n<p>You can play on fields seven, eight, and nine on the <a title="Great Lawn" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a>, which is in the middle of the park near 84th Street. Please note: at some times, fields seven and eight are only available for youth soccer games. You can also play at the <a title="North Meadow" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/north-meadow.html">North Meadow</a>, which is in the center of the park at 97th Street.</p>\r\n<p>Cleats cannot be worn in Central Park.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'Soccer can be played at two locations in Central Park-- the Great Lawn North Fields, and at the North Meadow. Permits are required, and cleats are prohibited.\r\n\r\n', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family progra