(42, '2014-08-07', 2, 1, 15, 'Dairy', '', 'attractions/dairy', 'Central Park Dairy', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="The Spring Dairy" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/the-spring-dairy-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/diary.jpg" border="0" alt="Diary" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>The Spring Dairy</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile9571.html" target="_blank">sooner</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>Open</strong>: Tuesday - Sunday from 10AM to 5PM</p>\r\n<p>Now serving as both an information center and gift shop, the Central Park Dairy was originally intended as a source of fresh milk for children in the late 19th century.</p>\r\n<p>The Dairy was constructed in 1870; at this time, fresh milk for children was difficult to find and desperately sought after by parents.  The Dairy was built at the southern end on the park, originally the children''s section, to provide milk and snacks for children in the cool and relaxing atmosphere near the Pond.</p>\r\n<p><span>{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>\r\n<p>Most of the building itself, located at 65th street, was constructed in the Victorian Gothic style, in particular its windows and spires.  The building''s beams and ceilings, however, are more reminiscent of those found in a barn, painted in bright yellow and orange colors.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'The Central Park Dairy, which now serves as an information center and gift shop inside the park, was originally intended as a source of fresh milk for children in the late 19th century.', 'dairy, store, central park gift shop, central park souvenirs, central park map, central park dairy, central park tshirt, central park gifts', 13.00, 5, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Dairy', 'Dairy', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(43, '2013-04-27', 2, 1, 15, 'Delacorte Theater', '', 'attractions/delacorte-theatre', 'Delacorte Theater in Central Park', '<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/delacorte.jpg" border="0" alt="Delacorte Theater in Central Park" width="200" height="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="page.php?pid=109"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Rick Anderson</span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Delacorte Theater in Central Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The Delacorte Theater, established in 1962, can be found just off of 80th street on the southwest corner of the <a title="central park great lawn" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Located at the heart of Central Park, the Delacorte Theater is best known<span lang="EN">&nbsp;for The Public Theater''s Free&nbsp;<a title="shakespeare in the park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/shakespeare-in-the-park.html">Shakespeare in the Park</a>, one of New York City''s most beloved summer traditions. Tens of thousands of New York natives and visitors come to the Delacorte to enjoy free Shakespeare.&nbsp;</span>Two plays are produced each summer, at least one of which is traditionally a play by Shakespeare.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tickets to shows at the Theater are free, so long as one is prepared to wait in line on the day of the performance to obtain them.</p>\r\n<p><span>The Delacorte Theater, operated by The Public Theater, founded by Joseph Papp, has hosted numerous productions of classic plays in addition to those by Shakespeare, such as Anton Chekov''s&nbsp;<em>The Seagull</em>&nbsp;and Bertolt Brecht''s&nbsp;<em>Mother Courage and Her Children</em>.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>While the Theater is responsible for having introduced many a new talent to the stage, it also frequently employs more well-known actors and actresses, including Meryl Streep, Al Pacino, and Philip Seymour Hoffman, among others.</p>\r\n<p>The Theater itself is an open-air theatre venue, which boasts a seating capacity of 1,872, offering clear views of the stage from any seat in the house.</p>\r\n<p>Both <a title="central park turtle pond" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/turtle-pond.html">Turtle Pond</a> and the majestic <a title="central park belvedere castle" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/belvedere-castle.html">Belvedere Castle</a> can be seen in the background, completing the picturesque setting for this renowned Central Park theater.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;">&nbsp;</p>', 'The outdoor Delacorte Theater is the summer home of the annual "Shakespeare in the Park" production. Begun in 1957 by Joseph Papp as part of the Public Theater/New York Shakespeare Festival, the annual productions draw thousands to the open air theater in the heart of Central Park. ', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Public Theater, New York Shakespeare Festival, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, Joseph Papp, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink', 24.00, 10, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Delacorte Theater', 'Delacorte Theater', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(44, '2013-10-24', 2, 1, 15, 'Discovery Center', '', 'attractions/discovery-center', 'Charles A. Dana Discovery Center in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Election Day glory, Harlem Meer" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/election-day-glory-harlem-meer.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/discovery-center.jpg" border="0" alt="Discovery center" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Election Day glory, Harlem Meer</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile19099.html" target="_blank">sconsidine</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The Charles A. Dana Discovery Center was opened in 1993 as one of the Park''s main visitor centers.  Named after Charles A. Dana, former editor of the New York Tribune and mediator between General Grand and Abraham Lincoln during the Civil War, the Discovery Center holds a multitude of educational workshops throughout the year.</p>\r\n<p>In addition to hosting environmental programs for children, the Discovery Center also teaches kids about wildlife firsthand by offering instructions and supplies for catch-and-release fishing in the Harlem Meer.</p>\r\n<p>The Discovery Center is located at 110th street; admission is free, and the Center is open Tuesday through Sunday from 10AM to 5PM.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'The Charles A. Dana Discovery Center was opened in 1993 as one of the Park''s main visitor centers. The Central Park Discovery Center holds a multitude of educational workshops throughout the year.', 'central park discovery center, Charles A. Dana, wildlife firsthand, workshops', 20.90, 5, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Discovery Center', 'Discovery Center', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(45, '2012-06-08', 2, 1, 15, 'Great Lawn', '', 'attractions/great-lawn', 'Great Lawn in Central Park', '<p>In the center of Central Park lies the Great Lawn, a green pasture of 55-acres that is considered one of the most famous lawns in the world. Located mid-park from 79th to 85th Streets, The Great Lawn is a wonderful place to have a picnic on a spring  afternoon or to catch some rays in the summer sun.&nbsp; It is open from  mid-April until mid-November. <br /> \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/the-great-lawn.jpg" alt="great lawn" width="250" height="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span><em>By </em><em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile2842.html">SAMiglio</a></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>A spring afternoon on the Great  <br />Lawn in Central Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Historically, the Great Lawn was not in the original plan of Central Park.&nbsp; The space was instead occupied by the rectangular Croton Reservoir, constructed in 1842.&nbsp; However, in 1917, the reservoir was made obsolete when a new water tunnel was built and all of its water was drained in 1931.&nbsp; During the Great Depression the area served as the home of displaced residents and surplus supplies and materials leftover from the construction of a subway line and Rockefeller Center.</p>\r\n<p>Over the next few years there was much debate about what would be done with the space. Options on the table included everything from a WWI Memorial to an opera house to underground parking garages.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>Eventually the debate concluded in 1937 and grass was planted, creating the oval styled-field now known as the Great Lawn.&nbsp; Then, during the 1950s, eight baseball diamonds were installed along the outer rim of the lawn.</p>\r\n<p>This splendor did not last long, though, and in the 1960s and 1970s the Great Lawn became overused and unkempt.&nbsp; However, in 1995, with a large-scale restoration effort from the Central Park Conservancy, the Great Lawn was once again lush as ever and has remained that way since.</p>\r\n<p>While it is a wide and vast serene greenery in the city, the Great Lawn is famous not just for its beauty.&nbsp; It has been the long time host to annual concerts such as the New York Philharmonic and the Metropolitan Opera, as well as other memorable performances by world-class acts such as Diana Ross, Bon Jovi and Garth Brooks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'In the center of Central Park lies the Great Lawn, a green pasture of 55-acres that is considered one of the most famous lawns in the world. Located mid-park from 79th to 85th Streets, The Great Lawn is a wonderful place to have a picnic on a spring afternoon or to catch some rays in the summer sun.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, Great lawn, concerts, central park great lawn, central park field', 86.20, 18, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Great Lawn', 'Great Lawn', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(46, '2015-07-16', 40, 2, 15, 'Heckscher Playground', '', 'attractions/conservatory-water/heckscher-playground', 'Heckscher Playground in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Central Park Playground" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/central-park-playground-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/heckscher-playground.jpg" border="0" alt="Heckscher Playground" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Central Park Playground</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile33137.html" target="_blank">skt618</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Heckscher Playground is not only the oldest playground in Central Park, it is also the largest at nearly three acres.  In addition to the typical park attractions, such as a variety of slides, swings, and seesaws, Heckscher Playground features both a water fixture and giant rocks for climbing.  It is also famed for its kickball games, which are popular during the summertime.</p>\r\n<p>Located at 7th Avenue and Central Park South, Heckscher Playground runs from 61st to 63rd streets and is open from 7:30am until dusk.  The Playground opened in 1926, when it was named for August Heckscher Sr., the grandfather of Parks Commissioner August Heckscher III.</p>\r\n<p>Complete with its own restrooms and snack carts, the Playground is best suited for children ages 6 to 12.  Heckscher Playground is most populated during the spring and summer months.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><span style="color: green; background-color: #efefef;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>\r\n<p>The Central Park Conservancy reconstructed Heckscher Playground in 2005 and the Heckscher Building in 2007. The playground includes a shaded area with swings and slides; a multiuse area comprised of synthetic turf and safety surfacing; and a large, maze-like climber and water feature with tunnels, ramps and slides. Includes two water feature areas during the summer, one area for older children and another geared to younger kids.</p>', 'Heckscher Playground is the oldest and largest playground in Central Park, measuring nearly three acres.', 'playgrounds, children attraction, ballfields in central park, kickball games, rocks for climbing', 36.10, 70, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Heckscher Playground', 'Heckscher Playground', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(47, '2013-10-25', 2, 1, 15, 'Nature Observatory', '', 'attractions/nature-observatory', 'Nature Observatory in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Wildlife" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/wildlife-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/nature-observatory.jpg" border="0" alt="Nature observatory" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Wildlife</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile30983.html" target="_blank">kclareramo</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The Henry Luce Nature Observatory is a wonderful educational site that teaches visitors about nature and wildlife in Central Park.  Climbing up and down the narrow, winding staircases of Belvedere Castle, guests can see all that this small Observatory has to offer, including microscopes, telescopes, and Discovery Kits complete with binoculars, maps, and paper for jotting down findings in the Park.</p>\r\n<p>The second floor, decorated with papier m&acirc;ch&eacute; replicas of the birds found in the Park, is a great location for bird watching.  The Observatory also offers up-to-the-minute weather forecasts for those who request them.</p>\r\n<p>This attraction is free, and is open to the public Tuesday-Sunday from 10AM - 5PM.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'The Henry Luce Nature Observatory is a wonderful educational site that teaches visitors about nature and wildlife in Central Park.', 'nature observatory, central park wildlife, educational site', 8.90, 3, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Nature Observatory', 'Nature Observatory', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(48, '2013-10-24', 2, 1, 15, 'Lake', '', 'attractions/lake', 'Central Park Lake', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Summer Day on the Lake" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/summer-day-on-the-lake-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/the-lake.jpg" border="0" alt="The Lake" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Summer Day on the Lake</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile9696.html" target="_blank">rl155</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The Central Park Lake, in conjunction with the Ramble, creates an essential part of the "Greensward" design plan created by Frederick Law Olmsted and Calvert Vaux when designing the initial features of what would become Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>What is now a stunning and picturesque 18-acre lake was once nothing more than a large, untamed swamp.  After its excavation in 1857, the Lake was opened for its first winter of ice-skating in 1858.  Until 1950, the Lake was used for ice-skating during the winter months and boating in the summer.  After 1950, however, the skating rink was officially closed, allowing the Lake''s former wildlife inhabitants to take up residence there once more.  As such, the Lake is now an excellent location for bird watching, where one can spot swans, ducks, and even the occasional egret or heron.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>The second largest man-made body of water in the Park, the Lake provides wonderful opportunities for viewing its abundant flora and fauna from rowboats, which are available for rent during the spring and summer months at the Loeb Boathouse. Aside from taking a boat, other options for nature sightseeing include taking a Venetian-style gondola ride around the Lake, or simply walking along the shore.</p>\r\n<p>Like many other Park attractions, the Lake was also restored by the Central Park Conservancy. It was reopened to visitors in 2008.  The Lake is a sight not to be missed if you''re in the mood for a calming boat ride through bamboo patches, bridges, and natural splendor in the Park.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'At twenty-two acres the Lake is Central Park?s largest body of water besides the Reservoir and offers a wide variety of activities and views to park visitors.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, boathouse, Lake, boats, rental boats, gondola, boat rides', 56.30, 14, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Lake', 'Lake', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(49, '2013-10-26', 2, 1, 15, 'Lasker Pool & Rink', '', 'attractions/lasker-pool-rink', 'Lasker Pool & Rink in Central Park', '<p>A dual-purpose Central Park recreational site, the Lasker area serves as both a pool during the summer and an ice skating rink during the winter.&nbsp; Located mid-park between 106th and 108th Streets, the site overlooks the beautiful <a title="harlem meer central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/harlem-meer.html">Harlem Meer</a> and is favorite of active park-goers all year round.</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Lasker Pool in Central Park" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/lake-pool-inviting.jpg"> <img title="lasker pool and rink" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/Lasker_Pool_and_Rink.jpg" alt="lasker pool and rink" width="250" height="165" /> </a> <br /> \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><em>by&nbsp;</em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile31921.html"><em>PattyA</em></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Lasker Pool in Central Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span><strong>LASKER POOL<br /></strong></span>Currently, the Lasker Pool features a wading pool and Olympic pool for visitors to enjoy every summer from the end of June through Labor Day. The free pool provides a deck area, lockers and a concession stand.&nbsp; Make sure to bring your own lock and towel!</p>\r\n<p>For kids who get hungry while swimming, the Department of Education has a free summer lunch program at the pool where children 18 and under can get breakfast and lunch for free on weekdays.</p>\r\n<p><span>The Lasker Pool also runs a series of free programming throughout the summer. Kids can partake in Learn to Swim lessons, and for adults there is the free Lap Swim program. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Pool Hours:<br /></strong>Open daily 11:00 AM to 3:00 PM, and 4:00 PM to 7:00 PM,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Free Lap Swim Program Hours:<br /></strong><span>"Early Bird" lap swim hours:&nbsp;</span>7:00 AM to 8:30 AM<br />"Night Owl" lap-swim hours: 7:00 PM to Dusk.<br />For more information call 212-534-7639.</p>\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>\r\n<p><span><strong>LASKER RINK<br /></strong></span>The Lasker Rink is just as busy during the winter when the water freezes and visitors trade their swimsuits in for ice skates.&nbsp; The rink is open daily every winter from the end of October through the end of March.</p>\r\n<p><strong>HOURS:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Monday - Thursday</strong>: 10:00am-3:45pm&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Friday</strong>: 10:00am -11:00pm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Saturday</strong>: 1:00pm-11:00pm</li>\r\n<li><strong>Sunday</strong> 12:30pm-4:30pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>During holidays or special events, the rink may have different hours. Check the <a title="Lasker Rink Calendar of Events" href="http://www.laskerrink.com/default.aspx?p=home&amp;e=6&amp;redirecturl=http%3a%2f%2fwww.laskerrink.com%2fdefault.aspx%3fp%3dDynamicModule%26pageid%3d335494%26ssid%3d233586%26vnf%3d1" target="_blank">Lasker Rink Calendar of Events</a>&nbsp;for details.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>PRICES:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Adults</strong>: $7.50</li>\r\n<li><strong>Children</strong> (11 &amp; under): $4.00</li>\r\n<li><strong>Seniors</strong>: $2.25</li>\r\n<li><strong>Skate</strong> <strong>Rentals</strong>: $6.50 (tax included)</li>\r\n<li><span><strong>Lock Rental</strong>: $3.25&nbsp;</span>(plus refundable $4.00 deposit, tax included)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In addition to regular ice-skating, hockey classes for all ages, as well as group and private skating school lessons are offered at the Lasker Rink.&nbsp; Kids can even have their birthday party on ice! Contact the Lasker Rink directly for further information on hours, rates and special events. Visit&nbsp;<a title="lasker rink central park" href="http://www.wollmanskatingrink.com/main_lasker.htm" target="_blank"><span>Lasker Rink''s Official Site</span></a> or call 917-492-3856.&nbsp;</p>', 'A dual-purpose Central Park recreational site, the Lasker area serves as both a pool during the summer and an ice skating rink during the winter.  Located mid-park between 106th and 108th Streets, the site overlooks the beautiful Harlem Meer and is favorite of active park-goers all year round.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, Lasker Pool, Lasker Rink, Harlem meer, ice skating, swimming, swimming central park, swimming in central park, Central Park, NYC, New York City , Wollman Rink, Ice Skating, family activities, winter sports, skating rink, trump lasker rink, ice skating central park, ice skating wollman rink, ice rink central park, skating rink central park, ice skating new york city, ice skating nyc, ice skate nyc, ice rink new york city, ice rink nyc, ice skate central park, ice skate lasker rink, ice skate wollman rink, winter sports central park, winter sports new york city, winter central park', 68.30, 14, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n