(52, '2013-12-04', 3, 1, 15, 'Dating Ideas', '', 'activities/dating-ideas', 'Dating Ideas in Central Park', '<table style="margin: 0 0 0 10px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Mid week boat ride" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/mid-week-boat-ride-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/dating-ideas.jpg" border="0" alt="Dating Ideas" width="200" align="right" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Mid week boat ride</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile24817.html" target="_blank">bsully17</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Central Park is one of the best places in New York City to bring a date. There are a wide variety of activities to do together, and many of the attractions are also low-cost.</p>\r\n<p>A romantic <a title="Horse &amp; Carriage Tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/horse-carriage-tours.html" target="_blank">horse-and-carriage ride</a>&nbsp;is the&nbsp;gold standard of Central Park dates. With the aid of a stylish roofed carriage, it is one of the few Central Park activities that can be enjoyed in the rain, and it is also particularly beautiful in the winter time.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>In the fall and winter time, <a title="ice skating central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/sports/central-park-ice-skating.html">ice skating</a> on Wollman or Lasker Rink is an iconic and picturesque way to spend some quality time together gliding across the ice, accompanied by the backdrop of the New York City skyline. Skate rentals are also available.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Not just for children and families, the <a title="Central Park Zoo" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/central-park-zoo.html" target="_blank">Central Park Zoo</a> is a good choice for a daytime date. The animal exhibits are excellent for inspiring conversation, and the zoo offers many quiet spots to enjoy conversation between the exhibits. Exotic animals like snow leopards, monkeys and penguins are unique and entertaining and can also make for a few good laughs.</p>\r\n<p>A <a title="picnics in central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/picnics.html">picnic</a> on one of the park&rsquo;s many lawns is a good way to get to know your date in a more intimate setting without interruption. Best of all, you can choose a spot that is as public or secluded as you like.&nbsp;Here''s a list of some of the&nbsp;<a title="top picnic spots in central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/picnics/top-7-picnic-spots.html">top picnic spots</a> in Central Park. If you don''t feel like&nbsp;packing your own picnic, there is an abundance of take-out <a title="restaurants central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/restaurants-around-central-park/top-10-restaurants-in-walking-distance.html">restaurants</a> and corner bodegas on both the East and West sides of the park that can help.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Rowboat rides&nbsp;on the&nbsp;<a title="Central Park Lake" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/lake.html" target="_blank">Central Park Lake</a>&nbsp;are another way to&nbsp;have a quiet conversation with your date while you&nbsp;view the excitement of the park together without being interrupted or disturbed.&nbsp;Rentals are available for&nbsp;reasonable hourly rates through the <a title="central park loeb boathouse" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/loeb-boathouse.html">Loeb Boathouse</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a title="bike rental central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike-rentals.html">Riding bikes</a> or walking through one of the park&rsquo;s many secluded trails is also a pleasant and low-key date activity. You can rent a bicycle for a couple hours or even the whole day if you wish.&nbsp;<a title="guided walking tours central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/walking.html">Guided walking tours</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a title="guided bicycle tour central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike.html">guided bike tours</a>&nbsp;are also available if you want to learn something new and exciting together with the aid of a knowledgeable guide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Central Park is also a memorable place to propose and get married. Here are some ideas for <a title="weddings in central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/weddings.html">weddings</a> and <a title="proposals in central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/weddings/proposals.html">proposals</a> in Central Park.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For more ideas, here''s a list of the <a title="10 best dates in central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/dating-ideas/10-best-dates.html">10 Best Dates in Central Park</a>.&nbsp;</p>', 'Central Park is one of the best places in New York City to bring a date. A major advantage of the park is that many of its attractions are free or low-cost.', 'Dating Ideas, Dating, Central Park, NYC, New York City, new york central park, central park date ideas, Balto, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike rentals central park, loeb Boathouse, Bow Bridge, central park proposals, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, rock climbing wall, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, romantic ideas, Wollman Rink, picnic central park, restaurants central park, ice skating central park, boat rentals central park, central park zoo, walking tours', 13.30, 3, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 14, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Dating Ideas', 'Dating Ideas', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(53, '2015-07-01', 2, 1, 15, 'Harlem Meer', '', 'attractions/harlem-meer', 'Harlem Meer in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Floating on the Harlem Meer" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/duck-on-the-harlem-meer-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/harlem-meer.jpg" border="0" alt="Harlem meer" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Floating on the Harlem Meer</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile5870.html" target="_blank">TomMonster</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Eleven acres of water surrounded by lush vegetation and immersed in a tranquil atmosphere compose the Harlem Meer.</p>\r\n<p>Named after the Dutch word for "small sea", the Meer is a large body of water located north of Conservatory Garden and east of the North Woods.  Various types of trees can be found along its banks, including the ginkgo, cypress, black locust, oak, and beech trees.</p>\r\n<p>Roses are in full bloom during the springtime, while summer-blooming hydrangea often make their first appearance in late May.  Visitors can enjoy the beauty of these plants while walking along the pathway that leads from the cove to the water''s edge; muskrats and black-crowned night herons may even make themselves visible here occasionally. &nbsp;</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>Also in the vicinity are Fort Clinton and Nutter''s Battery, gun emplacements that had been intended for use during the War of 1812. Activities at the Harlem Meer include the ever-popular catch-and-release fishing, two children''s playgrounds, and the Lasker Rink, open for skating in winter and swimming in summer.</p>\r\n<p><span>Check out the <a title="harlem meer performance festival" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/concerts/harlem-meer.html">Harlem Meer Performance Festival</a> every summer, at the Dana Discovery Center. The festival features a different type of international musical and/or dance performance every Sunday afternoon. See page for more details.</span></p>', 'Named after the Dutch word for "small sea", the Meer is a large body of water located north of Conservatory Garden and east of the North Woods.', 'meer, harlem, fishing, lush vegetation, children''s playgrounds, Lasker Rink, skating, swimming', 41.40, 10, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Harlem Meer', 'Harlem Meer', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(54, '2013-12-11', 2, 1, 15, 'Delacorte Music Clock', '', 'attractions/delacorte-music-clock', 'Delacorte Music Clock in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Delacorte Clock" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/delacorte-clock.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/delacorte-music-clock.jpg" border="0" alt="Delacorte muzic clock" width="200" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Delacorte Clock</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile4467.html" target="_blank">shereemccl</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The Delacorte Music Clock, located near the Children''s Zoo and Wildlife Center,&nbsp;is a great attraction for kids. Playing music every half hour from 8am until 5pm daily, it plays a total of 44 songs that change with the season, including classic children''s tunes such as Twinkle, Twinkle Little Star, Hickory Dickory Dock, Old King Cole, and Row, Row, Row Your Boat.</p>\r\n<p>The Music Clock was modeled after the musical clocks that George T. Delacorte saw while travelling in Europe.  The whimsical, bronze animal sculptures that adorn the Clock were created by sculptor Andrea Spadini, and include a goat playing the pipes, a kangaroo playing horns, a penguin on drums, a bear with a tambourine, and a hippo playing the violin.</p>\r\n<p>The Clock''s usual repertoire of songs changes to a collection of Christmas carols around the holiday season.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'The Delacorte Music Clock is a great attraction for kids, playing a total of 44 songs that change with the season. It''s located near the Children''s Zoo and Wildlife Center.', 'delacorte music clock, delacorte theater, central park clock, kids attraction, children''s attraction, twinkle twinkle little star, hickory dickory dock, christmas carols central park, music in central park', 5.00, 1, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Delacorte Music Clock', 'Delacorte Music Clock', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(55, '2013-10-25', 2, 1, 15, 'North Meadow', '', 'attractions/north-meadow', 'North Meadow in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="North Meadow" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/north-meadow-cp.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/north-meadow.jpg" border="0" alt="Angel of the Waters Fountain at Bethesda Terrace" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>North Meadow</strong> by             <em><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/toniweb/" target="_blank">Toniweb.com</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>North of the <a title="Central Park Great Lawn" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a>, at 97th Street, lies the Central Park North Meadow.  This large, 23-acre meadow includes twelve fields to be used for soccer, touch football, baseball, and softball.  A great choice for families with children, the North Meadow offers programs and sports in which visitors of all ages can participate.</p>\r\n<p>The <a title="North Meadow Recreation Center Central Park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/north-meadow-center.html">North Meadow Recreation Center</a> offers fitness courses for children and teens, lends out sporting goods, and even includes basketball and handball courts.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'This large, 23-acre meadow includes twelve fields to be used for soccer, touch football, baseball, and softball. ', 'meadow, soccer fields, football fields, baseball fields, softball fields, sport fields, sports, North Meadow Recreation Center basketball courts, handball courts', 47.80, 58, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'North Meadow', 'North Meadow', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(56, '2015-07-02', 2, 1, 15, 'Obelisk', '', 'attractions/obelisk', 'Obelisk in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Cleopatra''s Needle" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/cleopatra-s-needle-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/obelisk.jpg" border="0" alt="Obelisk" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Cleopatra''s Needle</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile724.html" target="_blank">MKR</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Though often referred to by its nickname, Cleopatra''s Needle, this ancient artifact was in fact commissioned by Pharaoh Thutmosis III around 1450 BC in celebration of his 3rd jubilee (or the 30th year of his reign).  Two of these obelisks were constructed, and, around 13 or 12BC, they were transported from Heliopolis to Alexandria.  The pair was separated in the late 19th century; one was sent to London and another to New York City, both by the Khedive of Egypt in exchange for aid in modernizing his country.</p>\r\n<p>The Obelisk''s move to New York City was nothing short of arduous.  Once in the City, it took laborers four months to simply move it from the Hudson River to Central Park where it now stands, located behind the Metropolitan Museum of Art.</p>\r\n<p>The Obelisk is known as the oldest man-made construction in Central Park.  Its shaft is 71 feet high and weighs about 200 tons.  Each corner of the Obelisk''s base is supported by huge, 900 pound bronze replicas of sea crabs originally created by the Romans while it was in Alexandria.  Each year visitors come to marvel at this piece of history, officially designated a scenic landmark in 1974 by the NYC Landmarks Preservation Commission.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 20px; text-align: left;"><span style="background-color: #efefef; color: green;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>\r\n<p>The Obelisk was a gift from Egypt to Central Park in 1881. &nbsp;Since then it has been the tallest structure and one of the most popular tourists sights in Central Park. &nbsp;In 2011, the Egyptian government threated to take back the Obelisk due to neglect. It took three years of planning and&nbsp;$500,000, (an amount that was raised privately by the Central Park Conservancy), to remove 3500 years of grime.&nbsp;The&nbsp;deterioration of the obelisk&nbsp;had less to do with conditions in New York City than the fact that, at some point in its history, it had toppled over and lay in desert sands for 500 years.</p>\r\n<p>After a year of renovation, which included using lasers to remove the dirt and grime, as well as glue, to&nbsp;fix sections that have become weak with age, the needle is open again for all to visit.&nbsp;The laser cleaning was not meant to bring the stone back to its pristine color, but to remove atmospheric deposition, along with damage that was done when it first arrived in Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>The monument underwent a restoration that did as much harm as good back in the 1880''s. &nbsp;Workers coated the entire structure in paraffin, which did preserve the surface. But first they cleaned a little too aggressively, scraping off an estimated 700 pounds of granite. When the obelisk arrived in New York, it was exposed to cold for the first time, which did not help its condition.</p>\r\n<p>Prior to this restoration, The Central Park Conservancy and the Metropolitan Museum of Art, worked closely together. &nbsp;The obelisk was extensively documented. Photographers from the Met created a detailed record of its condition, capturing every crack and crevice from the vantage of a boom lift.</p>', 'Though often referred to by its nickname, Cleopatra''s Needle, this ancient artifact was in fact commissioned by Pharaoh Thutmosis III around 1500 BC in celebration of his 3rd jubilee (or the 30th year of his reign).', 'obelisk, cleopatra''s needle, egyptian monument, monument, central park landmark', 95.10, 24, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Obelisk', 'Obelisk', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(57, '2012-06-08', 1, 1, 15, 'Frisbee', '', 'sports/frisbee', 'Frisbee in Central Park', '<p>Frisbee is a classic game that is the perfect compact enjoyment for a day in Central Park. It is one of a few games whose equipment can easily be carried in a backpack or even a purse, making it ideal as part of an all-day New York adventure.</p>\r\n<p>Central Park has several fields that are ideal for playing Frisbee. The <a title="North Meadow" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/north-meadow.html">North Meadow</a>, <a title="Great Lawn" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a>, and <a title="Sheep Meadow" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/sheep-meadow.html">Sheep Meadow</a> are all large enough to stage a game. However, you must be mindful of other park patrons. In busy spots, it is best to keep the game to two or three people. Avoid areas with many trees, and stay away from the lakes and ponds if you don''t want to lose your disc.</p>\r\n<p>Ultimate Frisbee tournaments occur every Saturday at 10 a.m. and Sunday at 1 p.m. at Great Hill, near Central Park West and 106th Street. This organized sport version of Frisbee is competitive and fast-paced. If you are looking for a unique New York experience that lets you interact with the locals, this is a good choice.</p>\r\n<p>Even if you don''t bring a Frisbee to the park, you can still play. Just go to the <a title="North Meadow Recreation Center" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/north-meadow-center.html">North Meadow Recreation Center</a> to borrow a field day kit. All kits include a Frisbee, and you only need a valid photo ID to borrow one.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'Frisbee is a popular sport around the open fields of Central Park - favorite spots in the park for tossing a Frisbee about include The Great Hill, The Great Lawn and the Sheep Meadow. \r\n', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Frisbee', 19.00, 5, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=7&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a98c2241&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=7&n=a98c2241'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>\r\n', '', ''