(68, '2012-06-08', 1, 1, 15, 'Walking', '', 'sports/walking', 'Walking in Central Park', '<p>New York''s Central Park is one of the city''s safest and most desirable walking locations. Since it offers miles of trails, it is suitable for both those who can withstand only short periods of exercise and endurance, and also speed walkers who want to cover many miles at once. If you are looking for an especially picturesque tour you might try the <a title="Reservoir" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/reservoir.html">Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis Reservoir</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The walkway around the Reservoir is made out of cinder, making it soft and slightly springy. Adjacent to the Reservoir is the dirt bridle path. The longest loop that you can make in Central Park without repeating any terrain is 6.1 miles. This trail follows the Loop, and can be picked up anywhere on it.</p>\r\n<p>For those who would like a more rigorous experience, there are 58 miles of hiking trails throughout the park. These trails feature steep inclines and rugged or bumpy pathways that are frequently unpaved. The Ravine, the <a title="Ramble" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/ramble.html">Ramble</a>, and the North Woods also offer hiking trails of various levels of difficulty.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>For those who wish to enjoy leisurely walks, especially with strollers or children, the <a title="Great Lawn" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a> is ideal. There are many sights to see, including other park users enjoying games and picnics on the lawn.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you are visiting Central Park for the first time or are a frequent park-goer, you can learn fascinating facts about the park''s history, architecture, and its role in the city''s culture on a <a title="Guided walking tour" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/walking.html">guided walking tour</a>. Tours are available that focus on architecture, cinema, and other topics, so it''s easy to find one no matter what your interests are.</p>', 'Central Park''s 250 acres of lawns and 136 acres of woodland offer a multitude of landscapes, trails, and pathways for everyone from the serious hiker to the recreational stroller.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, power walking, fitness walking, health walking, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, walking, Wollman Rink', 2.50, 1, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=7&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) do