(98, '2015-05-29', 3, 1, 15, 'Shakespeare in the Park', '', 'activities/shakespeare-in-the-park', 'Shakespeare in the Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0px initial initial;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/romeo-juliet.jpg" alt="Shakespeare in the Park" width="200" height="235" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Shakespeare Garden</strong> by <em><a title="lilybart" href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profiles/lilybart" target="_blank">lilybart</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Free Shakespeare in the Park is an annual event that is held at the Delacorte Theater in Central Park. It is produced by The Public Theater, and attendance is free, provided that guests wait in line for tickets on the day of the performance.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Shakespeare in the Park includes two productions over the course of the summer, and one of New York City''s most beloved summer traditions.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>2015 Schedule<br /></strong>This summer is the 53rd anniversary of Shakespeare in the Park&nbsp;at the Delacorte Theater in Central Park.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Tempest: May 27th to July 5th</strong></p>\r\n<p><span>Academy Award nominee&nbsp;</span><span>Sam Waterston</span><span>&nbsp;(</span><em>Newsroom, Law &amp; Order</em><span>, The Public&rsquo;s&nbsp;</span><em>King Lear</em><span>) and&nbsp;</span><span>Jesse Tyler Ferguson&nbsp;</span><span>(</span><em>Modern Family, The Comedy of Errors</em><span>) return in&nbsp;</span><span>THE TEMPEST</span><span>, Shakespeare&rsquo;s classic about young love, old enemies and the eternal magic of storytelling.&nbsp;</span><span>Exiled to a fantastical island, Prospero unleashes a churning storm to shipwreck the traitor brother who stole his throne and settle the score once and for all. But bitter revenge is upended by newfound love in this sublime masterpiece that proves we are all &ldquo;such stuff as dreams are made on.&rdquo;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>This production will run from May 27th to July 5th.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span>Running time: 2hrs and 45mins with one 15 minute intermission</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Cymbeline: July 23rd to August 23rd</span></p>\r\n<div><span class="content">\r\n<p><span>Tony Award winner&nbsp;</span><span>Daniel Sullivan</span><span>&nbsp;(King Lear, The Comedy of Errors, Proof) directs the Shakespearean fairy tale&nbsp;</span><span>CYMBELINE</span><span>, featuring Tony nominee&nbsp;</span><span>Lily Rabe</span><span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span>Hamish Linklater</span><span>.&nbsp;</span><span>Princess Imogen&rsquo;s fidelity is put to the royal test when her disapproving father banishes her soul mate. Cross-dressing girls and cross-dressing boys, poisons and swordfights and dastardly villains all take the stage in this enchanting romp about the conquering power of love.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This production will run from July 23rd to August 23rd.</span></p>\r\n<p>Running time: 2hrs and 45mins with one 15 minute intermission</p>\r\n</span></div>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span class="content"><strong>Tickets</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span class="content">Tickets to Shakespeare in the Park are FREE&nbsp;and are distributed, two per person, at the Delacorte Theater in Central Park at 12 noon on the day of the show. People often line up a few hours before noon, so plan ahead.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class="content">Seat locations are distributed randomly.</span></p>\r\n<p>Free tickets are also available through the Virtual Ticketing lottery at&nbsp;<a title="NYC''s Shakespeare in the Park ticket lottery" rel="external" href="http://shakespeareinthepark.org/" target="_blank">shakespeareinthepark.org</a>&nbsp;on the day of the show.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span><strong>Location</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">The Delacorte Theater in Central Park is accessible by entering at 81st Street and Central Park West or at 79th Street and Fifth Avenue.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'Shakespeare in the Park is an annual production that is held at the Delacorte Theatre in Central Park and attendance is free.', 'Shakespeare, Delacorte Theatre, Public Theatre, All''s Well that Ends Well and Measure for Measure, shakespeare in the park, free shakespeare in central park, central park shakespeare', 0.00, 0, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 48, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Shakespeare in the Park', 'Shakespeare in the Park', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(99, '2013-08-13', 3, 1, 15, 'Marionette Theater', '', 'activities/marionette-theater', 'Marionette Theater in Central Park', '<p>Located at the Swedish Cottage, the children''s Marionette Theatre holds daily shows during the summer months and is even open during the school year.  Favorites such as <em>Jack and the Beanstalk</em>, <em>Cinderella</em>, <em>Hansel and Gretel</em>, and <em>Gulliver''s Travel''s</em> are often performed here.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>The Theatre became a permanent fixture at the Swedish Cottage in the 1970''s and since then, has been restored by the Central Park Conservancy.  Now under the direction of the City Parks Foundation, the Marionette Theatre one of the most enjoyable children''s attractions in the Park.</p>\r\n<p>Reservations are necessary, and ticket prices are $8.00 for an adult ticket, and $5.00 for a child''s ticket.  The Theatre is located at 79th street and West Drive.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'Jack and the Beanstalk, Cinderella, Hansel and Gretel, and Gulliver''s Travel''s are often performed here.', 'Marionette Theater, swedish cottage, Jack and the Beanstalk, Cinderella, Hansel and Gretel, Gulliver''s Travels', 0.00, 0, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 28, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Marionette Theater', 'Marionette Theater', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(100, '2009-05-15', 3, 1, 14, 'Alternative Walking Tours', '', 'activities/alternative-walking-tours', 'Central Park Walking Tours - CentralPark.com', '<p>The <a href="http://www.centralparknyc.org/" target="_blank">Central Park Conservancy</a> \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/walkies.jpg" border="0" alt="Walking Tours in Central park" width="250" height="149" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://centralparkblogger.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>John B. Moore</em> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Bethesda Fountain in Central Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nconducts free, volunteer-led walking tours throughout various parts of the park. This is a great way to discover the Park''s history, ecology and design. These tours are approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours and place year round, rain or shine, except in extreme weather conditions (heavy rain, snow storms, 25 degrees or less, or 95 degrees or above). <strong>No reservations are required</strong>. Call 212-360-2726 Tuesday through Saturday for additional information.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.wildmanstevebrill.com/" target="_blank">Wildman Steve Brill</a> conducts tours that introduces park visitors to many of the edble plants that grow wild in the park.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.phototrektours.com/">PhotoTrek Tours</a> Experience New York through the eyes of a native, while you are photographed in the city''s most exciting locations.</p>\r\n<p>Check out the Events Calendar on your left to see what''s going on today.</p>', 'The Central Park Conservancy conducts free, volunteer-led walking tours throughout various parts of the park. This is a great way to discover the Park''s history, ecology and design. ', 'Walking Tours, Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn', 0.00, 0, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Alternative Walking Tours', 'Alternative Walking Tours', 0, '0