(102, '2014-04-02', 10, 1, 15, 'Park Contact Numbers', '', 'general-info/park-contact-numbers', 'Central Park Contact Numbers', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>General Numbers</h3>\r\n<p>Information Line<br /> (212) 360-3444</p>\r\n<p>Central Park Conservancy<br /> (212) 310-6600</p>\r\n<p>Central Park Medical Unit<br /> (212) 585-0911</p>\r\n<p>Central Park Police<br /> (212) 570-4820</p>\r\n<p>Central Park Zoo<br /> (212) 439-6500</p>\r\n<p>Volunteer Hotline<br /> (212) 360-2751</p>\r\n<p>Ballfield Permits<br /> (212) 408-0234</p>\r\n<p>North Meadow Recreation Center<br /> (212) 348-4867</p>\r\n<p>NYC Parks Department<br /> 311 (or 212-NEW-YORK)</p>\r\n<p>The Plaza Hotel<br /> (212) 759-3000</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Visitor Centers</h3>\r\n<p>Belvedere Castle<br /> (212) 772-0210</p>\r\n<p>Charles A. Dana Discovery Center<br /> (212) 860-1370</p>\r\n<p>Dairy Visitor Center and Gift Shop<br /> (212) 794-6564</p>\r\n<p>Tavern on the Green<br /> (212) 877-TOTG (8684)</p>\r\n<p>Chess &amp; Checkers House<br /> (212) 794-4064</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'Park Contact Numbers, including general information, the Central Park Medical Unit, the Central Park Police and the Volunteer Hotline.', 'central park contact, central park telephone numbers, central park information, central park hotline, central park contact information', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'mall.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Park Contact Numbers', 'Park Contact Numbers', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(103, '2013-08-13', 3, 1, 15, 'Children''s Activities', '', 'activities/children-s-activities', 'Children''s Activities in Central Park', '<p>Many attractions in Central Park were created especially with kids in mind.  Below are some Park locations that are perfectly suited for families with young children.</p>\r\n<ol class="arabic">\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/children-s-zoo.html">Tisch Children''s Zoo</a></strong>\r\n<p>Located within the main Central Park Zoo, the Tisch Children''s Zoo features a petting zoo, Acorn Theatre, and the "Enchanted Forest", a complete habitat that is home to birds, turtles, and frogs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/belvedere-castle.html">Belvedere Castle''s "Woods and Water Exhibit"</a></strong>\r\n<p>Designed for kids, this exhibit teaches visitors about the flora and fauna of Central Park.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/carousel.html">Central Park Carousel</a></strong>\r\n<p>Open April through November, this very popular children''s attraction is a traditional merry-go-round, complete with the sound of organ music and vendor cart treats nearby.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/lake.html">Boat Rides on the Lake</a></strong>\r\n<p>Renting a rowboat from the Loeb Boathouse has been a fun, family activity in Central Park since the 19th century and remains a great choice in the spring and summer months.  On these trips around the Lake, visitors can spot Mute Swans and ducks, in addition to the occasional Heron or Egret.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/hans-christian-andersen.html">Storytelling</a></strong>\r\n<p>Younger children might enjoy the storytelling that takes place each summer at the site of the Hans Christian Anderson Statue, located near 72nd Street and 5th Avenue.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/wollman-rink.html">Ice Skating at Wollman Rink</a></strong>\r\n<p>Wollam Rink, the most popular outdoor skating rink in the city, is open weekdays and weekends during winter months.  Youth skating and hockey programs are also offered at the Rink, and skaters can warm themselves with hot drinks from the nearby caf&eacute;.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/lasker-pool-rink.html">Swimming at Lasker Pool</a></strong>\r\n<p>Offering free admission, Lasker Pool is a favorite summertime family attraction at Central Park.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/harlem-meer.html">Fishing at the Meer</a></strong>\r\n<p>Catch and release fishing is offered at the Meer through the Dana Discovery Center.  The Discovery Center lends visitors bamboo fishing poles, perfect for catching bass, catfish, bluegill sunfish, grass carp, rock perch, and golden shiners in the calm waters of the Meer.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/marionette-theater.html">The Marionette Theatre</a></strong>\r\n<p>The Marionette Theatre is located at the Swedish Cottage.  Hosting shows in the summertime and school season, productions include classic tales such as Sleeping Beauty, Cinderella, and Jack and the Beanstalk among others.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/conservatory-water.html">Model Boat Sailing</a></strong>\r\n<p>Model boats and even lessons in sailing them are available at Conservatory Water.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'Many attractions in Central Park were created especially with kids in mind. Read about some Park locations that are perfectly suited for families with young children.', 'tisch children''s zoo, woods and water exhibit, central park carousel, boat rides on the lake, storytelling, ice skating at wollman rink, swimming at lasker pool, fishing at the meer, the marionette theatre, model boat sailing', 14.30, 3, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 10, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Children''s Activities', 'Children''s Activities', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(104, '2013-08-13', 3, 1, 15, 'Educational Programs', '', 'activities/educational-programs', 'Educational Programs in Central Park', '<p>Central Park hosts several educational programs for various age ranges. The Woodlands Youth Crew is one such program. Designed for middle- and high-schoolers in New York, this after-school group cares for two of Central Park&rsquo;s woods, <a title="Ramble" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/ramble.html" target="_blank">The Ramble</a> and The North Woods. This program is designed for grades 7 through 12.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>The Restoration of the Outdoors Organized by Teen Students (ROOTS) engages high school students in ecological restoration and natural learning through a program that spans two to three months. By participating in the project, the students earn community service hours.</p>\r\n<p>Tourists in search of education opportunities for their children can take advantage of <a title="Bike Tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike.html" target="_blank">guided bike tours</a>. These tours allow children and adults to learn about Central Park&rsquo;s history from a knowledgeable local guide who can answer their questions.</p>\r\n<p>The Spring Visitor Internship Program is a small program, accepting only six teenagers each year. The program allows participants to develop their people skills by working directly with visitors at information centers located throughout the park. The program operates on Saturdays during the spring. Some program participants go on to become employees of the park with the summer internship program. Interns work at the visitors&rsquo; centers at the <a title="The Chess and Checkers House" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/sports/chess-checkers.html" target="_blank">Chess and Checkers House</a>, <a title="Belvedere Castle" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/belvedere-castle.html" target="_blank">Belvedere Castle</a>, <a title="Tavern on the Green" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/tavern-on-the-green.html" target="_blank">Tavern on the Green</a>, and other locations.</p>', 'The Central Park Conservancy provides a diverse collection of learning experiences that draw on the park?s rich history, its amazing array of flora and fauna and its wide range of topographical features.', 'Educational Programs, Children, Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, ', 4.90, 2, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 18, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Educational Programs', 'Educational Programs', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(107, '2009-05-19', 87, 1, 6, 'Artic Fox', '', 'central-park-zoo/artic-fox', 'Central Park Arctic Fox - CentralPark.com', '<p>The Central Park Zoo is home to an Artic Fox (Alopex lagopus), named Stripe. \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/zoo/arcticfox1[1].jpg" border="0" alt="Artic Fox at the Central Park Zoo" width="200" height="158" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.maryschwalm.com/" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Mary Schwalm</em></span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Rusty the Artic Fox chills at the  <br />Central Park Zoo.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nLike many New Yorkers he is nocturnal, sleeping during the day and only coming out at night. In his case he spends the daylight hours curled up in the rocks of the Harbor seal exhibit.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Staying warm</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stripe, like all Artic Foxes, is extremely well adapted to life in the sub-zero temperatures of the artic. With densest fur of any land mammal Stripe has the distinction of owning the warmest fur coat in Manhattan. His fur protects him so much that he would only begin to shiver at -50 degrees F! When sleeping, this fox will use its bushy tail like a scarf, wrapping around its face and leg to protect it from the cold and wind. Stripe even has furred paws for warmth while walking on snow and to prevent it from slipping, just like his friend the Polar bear. Artic Foxes have evolved shorter, rounded ears, muzzles, and legs to hold in heat better. Much like your average busboy.</p>\r\n<p>An Arctic fox&rsquo;s fur changes color depending on the seasons &ndash; white in winter &ndash; tundra gray in summer. This is helpful when hunting food, such as lemmings or squirrels, or avoiding becoming food. If you have a cat and a sweater, you know all too well aware of the process of shedding hair to prepare for warm weather.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Diet </strong></p>\r\n<p>The Arctic fox uses its great sense of smell and of hearing to detect prey beneath the snow and ice. They are also known to track Polar bears, shadowing them and feasting on the remains of their food. You may guess that the bears do not appreciate this so the fox&rsquo;s white coat and amazing speed (up to 25mph) are useful for staying out of a bears&rsquo; way. At the CPZ, Stripe is fed a gourmet confection of horsemeat, dog kibble, and bird salad.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Conservation </strong></p>\r\n<p>Global warming is having a significant impact on the habitat of the Arctic fox. Food availability is reduced. The Arctic foxes are also being pushed north by their southern cousins, the Red fox. These larger canines cannot live in the icy environments of the tundra. The official status of the Arctic fox is &ldquo;non-threatened&rdquo;. But while the world population is abundant, this animal is on the point of extinction in the southern parts of its range, like Sweden and Finland. Only Alaska and Canada possess large tundra regions too severe for the Red fox to live. Unfortunately, these populations are now under threat because of oil drilling in the Arctic Refuge.</p>', 'The Central Park Zoo is home to an Artic Fox (Alopex lagopus), named Stripe. Like many New Yorkers he is nocturnal, sleeping during the day and only coming out at night. In his case he spends the daylight hours curled up in the rocks of the Harbor seal exhibit. \r\n', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City,  weekend, weekend actvities, zoo, artic fox', 19.40, 4, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https:/