(109, '2013-08-19', 145, 2, 15, 'Rick Anderson', '', 'about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson', 'Rick Anderson - CentralPark.com Staff', '<p>Rick Anderson is the official photographer of CentralPark.com. He is known internationally for his work which<img style="float: right; margin: 5px; border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about/RickCP.jpg" alt="Rick Anderson" width="195" height="300" /> includes his bestselling series of city skylines including several breathtaking shots of the <a href="http://www.rickanderson.com/newyocisk.html" target="_blank">New York City</a> skyline. He is also well known to fans of Central Park for his beautiful poster of the <a href="http://www.rickanderson.com/bridofcenpar.html" target="_blank">Bridges of Central Park</a>. CentralPark.com is very proud to be featuring Rick''s photography throughout the website, most notably the panoramic shots that appear at the top of many sections of the site.</p>\r\n<p>In 1995, Rick A. Anderson left the family business where he had worked for 16 years to pursue photography as a full-time career. &ldquo;The Big Red Adventure&rdquo; his first book of photography, was published in 1996. Specializing in scenic photography, Rick''s extensive work as a free-lance aerial photographer can be seen in his published prints and posters, which include city skylines, sunsets, and collegiate sporting events.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>\r\n<table style="width: 240px;" border="2" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" align="center">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.downyonder.com/dy/detail/3859.html"><img style="vertical-align: bottom; margin: 5px; border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about/bridges.gif" alt="The Bridges of Central Park" width="225" height="161" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p align="center"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>The Bridges of Central Park</em> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>', 'Rick Anderson, the official photographer of CentralPark.com. ', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'bow_bridge.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Rick Anderson', 'Rick Anderson', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-08-31 16:59:08'),
(110, '2013-11-15', 87, 1, 15, 'California Sea Lion', '', 'central-park-zoo/california-sea-lion', 'California Sea Lion - Central Park Zoo', '<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>California Sea Lion</strong></span> (Zalophus Californianus)             \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Patient Sea Lion" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/fishhold.jpg" alt="Sea Lion Holding Fish" width="168" height="267" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.judithwolfe.com" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Judith Wolfe</em> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Patiently waiting to eat her fish</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br /><strong>Our collection includes:</strong> CPZ has four female California Sea Lions. April was born in 1991 in the Bronx. Katie was born in 2008 in the Bronx, Edith was born in 2010 at the NY Aquarium and Charlotte (Charlie) was rescued in the California waters in the summer of 2013.<br /><br /><strong>Found in the wild:&nbsp;</strong> California sea lions are found along the western coast of North America, from Vancouver south to Mexico and off the Galapagos Islands.<br /><br /><strong>See Them at the Central Park Zoo:</strong> In the large tank in the Temperate Zone in the Central Garden<br /><br /><strong>Description:</strong> California sea lions are agile both on land and in the water. This is due to their long front flippers, strong enough that they can balance their weight on them. Considering a male sea lion may reach up to 1000 lbs., this is no small feat. Female sea lions may weigh between 100-400 lbs. and reach approximately 5-6.5 feet in length. The CPZ&rsquo;s 2 female sea lions average between 200-400 lbs. &nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Zoo Sea Lion Habitat:</strong> The large tank is lightly chlorinated and contains 148,000 gallons of water. The water depth is 8 feet and the tank is filtered at 400 gallons per minute.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><strong>What do they eat:</strong> Adult California sea lions may eat 15-40 lbs. of fish and marine life a day. At the CPZ, the two sea lions are fed capelin, herring, vitamin E, and salt supplements. Feedings coincide with behavior enrichment and training three times a day at 11:30 AM, 2 PM and 4 PM. <br /><br /><strong>Life span:</strong> A California sea lion&rsquo;s average life span is 17 years but can live much longer in captivity.</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="April and Scooter in the Snow" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/twosealions.jpg" alt="Two Sea Lions in the Snow" width="168" height="197" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.judithwolfe.com" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Judith Wolfe</em> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Scooter &amp; April in a winter snow</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Threats: </strong>Pollution, over fishing, oil drilling and spilling, and coastal development.<br /><br /><strong>Fun Facts:</strong> California sea lions are able to hold their breath for up to 15 minutes and dive to depths of 700 feet. They use their long front flippers to propel themselves in the water and can swim about 12 mph. But when they porpoise, an action that allows the sea lions to leap into the air while swimming and breathe without losing momentum, they may reach speeds up to 25 mph. This is comes in handy when trying to avoid a killer whale or a shark, or when hunting prey.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align="center">\r\n<object width="320" height="265" data="http://www.youtube.com/v/035aiWHX9yA&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash">\r\n<param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" />\r\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" />\r\n<param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/035aiWHX9yA&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0" />\r\n<param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" />\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'The large tank in the Central Garden of the Central Park Zoo houses two female California sea lions: Scooter, born in 1987 and April, born in 1991.\r\n', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City,  weekend, weekend activities, california sea lions, Central Park Zoo', 23.50, 6, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=20&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=af4bb96a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=20&n=af4bb96a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'sea_lion.jpg', '<a href="http://www.maryschwalm.com" target="_new">Mary Schwalm</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'California Sea Lion', 'California Sea Lion', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
