(134, '2009-05-15', 87, 1, 6, 'Colobus Monkey', '', 'central-park-zoo/colobus-monkey', 'Central Park Colobus Monkey - CentralPark.com', '<p><strong></strong> \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="middle">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="middle"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages//zoo/colobus2[1].jpg" border="0" alt="Colobus Monkey at the Central Park Zoo" width="200" height="149" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.maryschwalm.com/" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Mary Schwalm</em></span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<strong> </strong> \r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="middle">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Colobus Monkey contemplates life  <br />at the   Central Park Zoo.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nBlack-and-white  colobus monkey (Colobus guereza)   <br /><strong>Where found</strong> : Equatorial Africa.  These monkeys are highly arboreal and spend most of their time in trees.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Diet</strong>: Leaves. An amazing thing about these animals is that they have a  two-chambered stomach, specifically designed to break down leaves.  Unfortunately, because leaves are not a high-energy diet and they take a while  to digest, colobus monkeys are not very active.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Life span</strong>: Up to 20 years in the wild and 30 years in captivity.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Interesting note</strong>: Not only does the amazingly long and beautiful white  hair on this monkey&rsquo;s back and tail break up its outline to confuse predators,  but it also serves as a sort of parachute, slowing its descent when jumping  great distances from tree limb to tree limb. Two of the adult females, Mac and Tana, have given birth this spring. For the first three months of their lives, these babies will be white and slowly accumulate the black fur of their parents. 1-year old Kima now has some competition for visitors&rsquo; attention.</p>', 'The Central Park Zoo features theBlack-and-white colobus monkey, these monkeys are highly arboreal and spend most of their time in trees. \r\n', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Colobus Monkey, Central Park Zoo', 56.40, 16, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=20&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) docume