(140, '2014-05-28', 2, 1, 15, 'Victorian Gardens', '', 'attractions/victorian-gardens', 'Victorian Gardens in Central Park', '<table style="margin: 0 0 0 10px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="The resting carnival" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/the-resting-carnival-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/victorian-gardens.jpg" border="0" alt="Victorian Gardens in Central Park" width="200" align="right" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>The resting carnival</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile13207.html" target="_blank">natalac</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Open: June to Sept</p>\r\n<p>See schedule for hours of operation&nbsp;<a title="victorian gardens central park hours of operation" href="http://victoriangardensnyc.com/hours-operation.asp" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Victorian Gardens is one of few amusement parks within the New York metropolitan area.</p>\r\n<p>This small but well-designed park opened in 2003. It occupies the <a title="Wollman Rink" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/wollman-rink.html">Wollman ice skating rink</a>&nbsp;every summer in Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>The park hosts 12 rides. Among them are:</p>\r\n<p>-The Aeromax: fly in pint-sized airplanes<br />-The Kite Flyer: imitates hang gliding<br />-The Convoy: an auto-style train ride<br />-The Red Baron: pilot imitation antique airplanes<br />-Mini Mouse: a roller coaster for young kids (parents welcome)<br />-The Jump Around: a bouncy ride especially appealing to children<br />-Samba Balloon: pilot your own hot air balloons</p>\r\n<p>Of particular interest to teenagers and adults are:</p>\r\n<p>-The Fun Slide: a three-story-tall slide<br />-Family Swinger: a classic swing ride<br />-Rockin&rsquo; Tug: a traditional swinging boat ride<br />-The Hydro Racer: a fast-paced water ride</p>\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>\r\n<p>There are also classic carnival games at Victorian Gardens like whac-a-mole, where players compete to hit the most moles with their mallets, and Rising Water, a water gun game.</p>\r\n<p>Even though it''s a small park and the rides are compact, all of the attractions can accommodate both adults and children. However, the majority of the rides are designed for children between the ages of 2 and 12. The amusement park is a controlled environment designed to allow parents to relax while they monitor their children.</p>\r\n<p>Victorian Gardens also hosts birthday parties and special events.</p>', 'Central Park''s Victorian Gardens offers a wide assortment of rides, games, and food for the whole family. Attractions include a Family Swinger, Samba Balloon, Aeromax, Convoy, Crazy Trolley, Kite Flyer, Rio Grande Train, Mini Tea Cup, and Mini Mouse Coaster. ', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, weekend, weekend actvities, Victorian Gardens, amusement park, family activities', 46.60, 14, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=15&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a026fe8a&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=15&n=a026fe8a'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Victorian Gardens', 'Victorian Gardens', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(141, '2009-09-14', 10, 1, 14, 'Directions', '', 'general-info/directions', 'Get Directions', '<p>The Park can be reached by subway on the East Side on the number 4, 5, 6 trains <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/subway.gif" border="0" alt="subway.gif" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="205" height="293" align="right" />and the 1, 2, 3, 4 buses on 5th Ave. On the West Side you can take the A, B, C,and D trains and the M10 bus. <a href="http://www.lirr.org/nyct/maps/submap.htm" target="_blank">Click here for the official MTA full Subway Map</a>.</p>\r\n<p>For door to door Google Map directions from anywhere go to our <a href="/pages/general-info/get-directions.html">Get Directions</a> page in the Fun Stuff section of the site.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>An excellent tool for finding your way to the park by public transportation is this <a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/parks/centralpark/tripplanner" target="_blank">Trip Planner</a>, suppied by the MTA.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Another great resource for finding your way to the park (and anywhere else in New York city for that matter) is <a href="http://www.gypsymaps.com" target="_blank">GypsyMaps</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, directions, subway, mass transit', 36.60, 38, '', '', '', '', 'mall.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Directions', 'Directions', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(142, '2009-05-19', 10, 1, 14, 'Membership', '', 'general-info/membership', 'Membership', '<p>The first time you visit CentralPark.com you''ll notice the little membership login/registration box on the left. It''s free, there''s no obligation, no salesman will call and we won''t fill your email with annoying offers for, well, you know. And, by registering for membership, you enable us to offer free-of-charge access to all of CentralPark.com''s very cool features. Registration also makes it possible for us to determine which areas of the site are of greatest interest to our users. And make sure to take a minute to check out our <a href="page.php?pid=15" target="_self">Privacy Policy</a> if you are concerned about entering your personal information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CentralPark.com members receive exclusive access to features including:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n<li>Breaking news stories about Central Park </li>\r\n<li>A searchable database of news, features and informative articles about activities and attractions throughout the park. </li>\r\n<li>The ability to upload your favorite pictures of Central Park and share them with visitors from around the world </li>\r\n<li>Regular copies of our CentralPark.com Newsletter (which you can opt in or out of separately) that will keep you updated on doings around the park and new features on the site </li>\r\n<li>Our extensive maps section with a zoom-able aerial view of the park </li>\r\n<li>And best of all access to our event planning feature which enables you to plan an event, invite friends by email, post it either publicly or privately and then pick the exact spot where you want everyone to meet up. It does everything but bring the potato salad. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You''ll also find exclusive Web reports, photos, multimedia and other enhanced features for many of your favorite Central Park sections. CentralPark.com features the most comprehensive online guide to the Central Park Zoo available, an online store filled with great gift ideas and our sports section which guides you through everything from yoga in the park to lawn bowling. Besides all this there is our Fun Stuff page which will have trivia contests, photo contests secrets of the park, downloadable wallpaper and other interesting bits to amuse you while you''re browsing about. And most of all you''ll be helping to create an online community of people from around the world that love Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So, take a moment to register. It''s fast, it''s easy and it''s lots of fun.</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../acc_create.php">\r\n<p>Join Now!</p>\r\n</a></p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, membership, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, member registration, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'mall.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Membership', 'Membership', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(144, '2013-08-19', 145, 2, 15, 'Aric Boyles', '', 'about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles', 'Aric Boyles - CentralPark.com Staff', '<p>Aric Boyles is the President and Founder of CentralPark.com. He has worked in the Internet Communications field for over 15 years, honing his skills as a web developer, creative director, new media consultant and entrepreneur.<img style="float: right; margin: 5px;" title="Aric Boyles" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/Dinner.JPG" alt="Aric Boyles" width="212" height="250" /></p>\r\n<p>Aric Boyles moved to New York City in the late 90''s and immediately fell in love with Central Park.&nbsp;In 1999, Aric produced the first <a href="http://www.centralparkposters.com/" target="_blank">aerial view poster of Central Park</a>, currently sold in galleries, gift shops and museums all over the world including the Metropolitan Museum of Art and The Museum of Natural History in New York City. He has also worked as a volunteer in the <a title="Central Park Zoo" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/central-park-zoo.html">Central Park Zoo</a> and spent countless hours introducing friends and relatives to the wonders of this very special place. Aric also created&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralparkhistory.com/" target="_blank">CentralParkHistory.com</a>&nbsp;which remains the most comprehensive online source for information about the park''s rich history.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>CentralPark.com is very much a labor of love for Aric, the fulfillment of a vision that he has long had to create the&nbsp;internet''s most complete, up-to-date, and definitive website about Central Park, offering park-goers accurate and relevant information about <a title="Central Park Attractions" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions.html">attractions</a>, <a title="Central Park Activities" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities.html">activities</a>, <a title="Central Park Tours" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours.html">tours</a>, <a title="Central Park Events" href="http://www.centralpark.com/events/">events</a>,&nbsp;<a title="Central Park Hotels" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/hotels.html">hotels</a>&nbsp;and <a title="Central Park Weddings" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/weddings.html">weddings</a>&nbsp;in this world famous landmark.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span>Outside of CentralPark.com and CentralParkHistory.com, Aric has founded several other exciting online ventures including&nbsp;</span><a title="FullScreenPhotos.com" href="http://www.fullscreenphotos.com/" target="_blank">FullScreenPhotos.com</a><span>,&nbsp;</span><a title="QR-Codes.com" href="http://www.qr-codes.com/" target="_blank">QR-Codes.com</a><span>,&nbsp;</span><a title="BLITS Brothers" href="http://www.blitsbros.com/" target="_blank">BLITSBros.com</a><span>&nbsp;</span><span>and mobile app&nbsp;</span><a title="AppAlerts iPhone app" href="http://click.linksynergy.com/fs-bin/stat?id=8JRCVCsooFk&amp;offerid=146261&amp;type=3&amp;subid=0&amp;tmpid=1826&amp;RD_PARM1=http%253A%252F%252Fitunes.apple.com%252Fus%252Fapp%252Fappalerts%252Fid508273949%253Fmt%253D8%2526uo%253D4%2526partnerId%253D30" target="_blank">AppAlerts</a><span>. You can get in touch with him via any of his profile links on&nbsp;</span><a title="About.me Aric" href="http://www.about.me/aric" target="_blank">About.me/aric</a><span>.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'CentralPark.com founder Aric Boyles moved to New York City in the late 90''s and immediately fell in love with Central Park. In 1999 Aric produced the first aerial view poster of Central Park.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 65.30, 21, '', '', '', '', 'bow_bridge.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Aric Boyles', 'Aric Boyles', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(145, '2013-08-19', 12, 1, 15, 'Staff', '', 'about-centralpark-com/staff', 'CentralPark.com Staff', '<p>The Staff of CentralPark.com is a group of dedicated professionals that share a passion for Central Park and the incredible city that surrounds it. They have joined together to produce what they hope is the most comprehensive, useful and visually stunning web representation of Central Park possible. They have pledged themselves to always use their powers for good and never evil.<a href="page.php?pid=144"> </a></p>\r\n<p><a href="page.php?pid=144">Aric Boyles</a> is the President and Founder of CentralPark.com. Aric has worked with great success on the cutting edge of the internet industry for more than 10 years and has used his extensive experience and insight in launching this project. It is his vision and passion for Central Park that has made this site a reality. <br />Do not play pool with him for money.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/cristian-nicolescu.html">Cristian Nicolescu</a>&nbsp;is the main brain behind the face of CentralPark.com. "Cristi" is one of those people who always answers "yes" and can build pretty much any online application. He loves Star Wars, Lord of the Rings and fast cars.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/eileen-callen.html">Eileen Callen</a> is the Marketing Director of CentralPark.com. Eileen brings seven years of online marketing experience and creative insight&nbsp;to CentralPark.com to help grow the site and ensure its continued success as a useful destination for Park lovers and visitors from all over the world.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/jillian-ryan.html">Jillian Ryan</a>&nbsp;is a native Brooklyn, New Yorker and the content director for CentralPark.com.&nbsp; And avid traveler,&nbsp; admirer of all things New York City and writing nerd, Jillian is excited to join this great team of Central Park lovers.&nbsp; Although already a big fan, she is eager to learn more about the park so she can share her knowledge with you.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/judith-wolfe.html">Judith Wolfe</a> updates the Central Park Zoo information as changes take place.&nbsp;An avid conservationist, she has been a volunteer at the Wildlife Conservation Society''s Central Park Zoo since 1990. Come visit the Zoo and catch Judy chatting about the animals on any given Friday.</p>\r\n<p><a href="page.php?pid=109">Rick Anderson</a> is the Official Photographer of CentralPark.com. Rick has been a professional photographer for the past ten years and is internationally known for his prints and posters, which include city skylines, sunsets, and collegiate sporting events. One of the most amazing things about the stunning photography that Rick has contributed to this site is the fact that he is able to capture these images during a few short visits to the City. This is while others of us wander around the Park seemingly for weeks trying take a few pictures that are half way acceptable. And he''s tall. Sort of annoying actually.<br /><a href="http://www.maryschwalm.com/"></a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.maryschwalm.com/">Mary Schwalm</a> has contributed additional photos for the Zoo pages. Mary is employed by the Associated Press as a Sports Photo Editor. She developed her fascination with animals as photography subjects at an early age at the Phoenix Zoo and continued with it later, after moving to New York, as a volunteer at the Central Park Zoo. More examples of Mary&rsquo;s amazing work can be found at her <a href="http://www.maryschwalm.com/" target="_blank">website</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 9.80, 2, '', '', '', '', 'bow_bridge.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Staff', 'Staff', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-08-31 17:00:33'),
(146, '2012-06-08', 10, 1, 15, 'Central Park Police', '', 'general-info/central-park-police', 'Central Park Police', '<table style="background: #ffffff;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/central-park-police.jpg" border="0" alt="Central Park Police" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Police riding horses</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile2306.html" target="_blank">sdwxh</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Central Park is patrolled by both the New York City Parks Enforcement Patrol and the New York Police Department.  The Central Park Police Precinct can be found on 86th St and Traverse Road, where it has been located since its construction in 1871.</p>\r\n<p>New safety measures put into action in 2005 have drastically increased safety within Central Park.  There are now less than one hundred crimes per year, which can make Central Park''s annual 20 million visitors feel a bit more at ease.</p>\r\n<p>The Central Park Precinct can be contacted by calling (212) 570-4820.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'Central Park is patrolled by both the New York City Parks Enforcement Patrol and the New York Police Department.', 'central park police precinct, nyc parks enforcement patrol, central park safety, police, patrol', 138.10, 29, '', '', '', '', 'police.jpg', 'Deputy Inspector Roger Thomas', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Central Park Police', 'Central Park Police', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(148, '2013-08-19', 16, 1, 15, 'Nasa Zooms', '', 'fun-stuff/nasa-zooms', 'Nasa Zooms', '<p>Using data from different spacecraft and some powerful computer technology, <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/funstuff/centralParkZoomIn.jpg" border="0" alt="centralParkZoomIn.jpg" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="200" height="148" align="right" />visualizers at the Goddard Space Flight Center have created a collection of visualizations of American cities in a way you have never seen them before. Starting with a camera high above the Earth, they rush in towards the surface at what would be an impossible speed for any known vehicle. Passing though layers of atmosphere, the colors of our destinations shimmer with their own unique characteristics, and suddenly you find ourselves floating in virtual space just above the ground in Central Park!</p>\r\n<p><a title="Central Park Zoom In" name="Central Park Zoom In" href="http://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/vis/a000000/a002400/a002443/centralParkZoomIn.mpg">Click here</a> for the zoom INTO to Central Park.</p>\r\n<p><a title="Central Park Zoom Out" name="Central Park Zoom Out" href="http://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/vis/a000000/a002400/a002442/centralParkZoomOut.mpg">Click here</a> for the zoom OUT from Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><em>Videos Courtesy of NASA/Goddard Space Flight Center Scientific Visualization Studio</em></p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'carousel.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Nasa Zooms', 'Nasa Zooms', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(150, '2013-12-04', 3, 1, 15, 'Horse-Drawn Carriages', '', 'activities/horse-drawn-carriages', 'Horse and Carriage Rides in Central Park', '<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<table style="background: #ffffff;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img title="horse drawn carriage central park" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/horse_carriage_2.jpg" alt="horse drawn carriage central park" width="200" height="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong><a title="horse and carriage tours new york central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/horse-carriage-tours.html">Horse-Drawn Carriages in the Park</a></strong> by &nbsp;<em><a title="nyc photo news" href="http://www.nycphotonews.com" target="_blank">NYCPhotoNews.com</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Horse-Drawn Carriages are a wonderful way to experience the beauty of the Park. They can be found all year round lined up along Central Park South between 5th and 6th Avenues.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sit back and relax in a stylish coach while you take in some of Central Park''s most popular attractions on a horse and carriage ride with that special someone, friends and family.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Experience our most popular tour of Central Park!</strong></p>\r\n<table style="width: 400px;" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 48%; padding-right: 2%;">\r\n<p>Reserve in advance to ensure availability. Customize rides for weddings, proposals, birthdays, anniversaries and more.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class="alignR valignTop" style="width: 50%;"><a href="/tours/horse-carriage"> <img src="/usr/media/tours.v2/reserve-online-horse-carriage.png" alt="Reserve Online" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>\r\n<p>There are a couple different kinds of rides to choose from:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pre-Arranged Carriage Rides:&nbsp;</strong>To ensure that a carriage is available, visitors can arrange for their ride in advance by making a reservation.&nbsp;Pre-booked rides are priced according to length, and they range from 45 minutes to 1.5 hours.&nbsp;This service, although providing a similar experience to the standard walk-up ride, includes additional sites and a booking fee. A pre-arranged 45 minutes ride is quoted at $165 per carriage during off-season months. Add-ons such as ride length, photography, flowers, chocolates, special pick-up and drop-off locations, etc may increase this rate. Alternatively, a&nbsp;<strong>walk-up 45 minutes ride will cost around $110</strong>; however it is not possible to guarantee availability or pre-arrange add-ons with a walk-up ride. Customers can choose between a walk-up or pre-arranged carriage ride depending on their individual needs.<strong>&nbsp;<a href="/tours/horse-carriage?duration=0">Reserve Now &rsaquo;</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href="/tours/horse-carriage?duration=0"></a>Custom Carriage Rides: </strong> Carriage rides can also&nbsp;be tailored to fit personalized wants and needs for various occasions.&nbsp;Reservations are required for custom rides.&nbsp;<a href="/tours/horse-carriage?duration=0"><strong>Reserve Now &rsaquo;</strong></a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Standard Carriage Rides:</strong>&nbsp;<span>Walk-up rides without a reservation are $50 for *up to* 20 mins, plus $20 per extra 10 mins, plus tip. Walk-up rides can not be&nbsp;<a class="tooltips" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/horse-carriage-tours.html">pre-customized</a>&nbsp;and availability cannot be guaranteed.&nbsp;</span>Prices may vary, so make sure you check with the driver before the ride begins. Sites seen on the tour may include: The Wollman Rink, the Pond, the Central Park Zoo, Sheep Meadow, the Mall (statues), the Dairy (tourist information center), the Carousel and the Dakota (where the former Beatle John Lennon lived). Approximate distance of the ride is .75 miles.</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>NOTE:</strong>&nbsp;</strong>There are no reservations for standard rides, only walk ups. To take a standard carriage ride, you can locate a carriage on Central Park South between 5th and 6th avenues.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Carriage Ride Regulations:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em> All rides are subject to New York City rules and regulations and ordinances:<br /></em>1. Summer restrictions - No carriage may operate above 89 degrees. It is suggested that you watch the weather reports during the summer months. Often the authorities will send the carriages home at 87 degrees.<br />2. Winter restrictions - No carriage may operate below 19 degrees or during Blizzards. ASPCA has, on occasion, sent horses home on short notice when it snows.<br />3. Police blockades or visits from important political figures visiting New York City may cause streets to be closed down. If the carriage is unable to gain access to your pick-up point, the carriage company cannot take responsibility. <br />4.&nbsp; Carriage Capacity - Four (4) adults per carriage, or: &nbsp;3 adults &amp; 2 kids under the age of 12, or:&nbsp; 1 adult &amp; 4 kids under the age of 12.<br />5.&nbsp; Monday-Friday rides start at 10AM, Saturday and Sunday rides start at 9AM<br />6.&nbsp; No rides below 34th Street. This is NYC Law.</p>', 'Horse-drawn carriage rides through Central Park are one of the most picturesque and romantic ways to see New York''s Central Park.', 'Horse-Drawn Carriages, horse rides central park, central park carriage, carriage ride central park, horse and carriage, horse tour central park, central park carriage ride', 153.50, 45, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'horsebuggy800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 24, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Horse-Drawn Carriages', 'Horse-Drawn Carriages', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(151, '2013-10-30', 0, 0, 14, 'Newsletters', '', 'newsletters', 'CentralPark.com ::: The Complete Guide to New York City''s Central Park', '<p>The CentralPark.com Newletter is our way to keep all of our members up do date on all the news and events taking place in Central Park. We will also use it to notify you of any important announcements about the park. You can sign up for any, or all, of the three different editions of the newsletters that send out each month.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Weekly Newsletter  First we have a weekly Newsletter that features highlights of the upcoming week. Performances in Central Park, special events as well as reminders about some of the weekly walks and programs sponsored by the Central Park Conservancy. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>Monthly Newsletter</strong> <br />There''s also a monthly edition that highlights the main events for the month ahead. These include seasonal events, special performances and updates on any changes to the site itself, either in content or in the many features that you can use to take full advantage of the Park''s many attractions. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>Special Edition</strong> <br />Lastly there is a special newsletter we use to notify you of any important announcements or breaking news concerning Central Park, including changes in events already on the schedule. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href="../../acc_create.php">Click here to become a member!</a> You can opt in, or out, of receiving any of these editions simply by editing your membership information after logging in.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<!--//GWO::Start//--><script>utmx_section("A")</script>B</noscript><!--//GWO::End//-->', 'The CentralPark.com Newsletter is your way to stay up to date on all the information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, newsletters, news 123', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'the_rock.jpg', '<a href="http://www.luminous-newyork.com">Joergen Geerds</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Newsletters', 'Newsletters', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
