(161, '2014-04-02', 3, 1, 15, 'North Meadow Recreation Center', '', 'activities/north-meadow-center', 'North Meadow Recreation Center in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="North Meadow Center" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/north-meadow-recreation-center.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/north-meadow-center.jpg" border="0" alt="North Meadow Center" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>North Meadow Center</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/56865697@N03/" target="_blank">~Ryval</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The Central Park North Meadow Recreation Center is located within the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/north-meadow.html" target="_blank">North Meadow</a>&nbsp;mid-park above the&nbsp;<a title="central park reservoir" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/reservoir.html">Reservoir</a>&nbsp;at 97th Street.</p>\r\n<p>Contact: (212) 348-4867&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Center, formerly a stable, contains a lab responsible for monitoring Central Park''s water and soil while teaching kids biology and chemistry.  Computer rooms, available for use by visitors, are also located at the Center.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>Central Park visitors can borrow North Meadow Recreation Center kits that include various sporting goods, such as frisbees, jump ropes, balls, bats, and hula-hoops.  Basketballs, to be used at the Center''s basketball courts, are available upon showing a photo id.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'The North Meadow Recreation Center, formerly a stable, contains a lab responsible for monitoring Central Park''s water and soil while teaching kids biology and chemistry.\r\n\r\n', 'north meadow, sports, bats, hula-hoops, Frisbee, and jump ropes, climbing wall, family programs', 0.00, 0, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=12&blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=ab1f636b&cb=1233'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=12&n=ab1f636b'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 36, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'North Meadow Recreation Center', 'North Meadow Recreation Center', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(162, '2012-06-08', 1, 1, 15, 'Bouldering', '', 'sports/bouldering', 'Bouldering in Central Park', '<p>For bouldering enthusiasts, Central Park is an ideal spot to practice the hobby. Bouldering, an offshoot of traditional rock climbing that is concentrated on climbing challenges under 10 feet in height, is experiencing a revival in the United States, particularly in New York City. It is one of few mentally and physically challenging sports that can be practiced inside the confines of the city. To play, all you need is a chalk bag to keep you hands dry on slippery slopes, a fall pad, which is like a small mattress that goes under you to protect you if you fall, and hopefully a buddy to spot you while you climb. Bouldering challenges are broken up into "problems" which reflect the dual mental and physical nature of the sport. Some climbs have the possibility of eliminates, which refers to specific handicaps undertaken during the climb to make it artificially more challenging. An example of this might be not using an obvious handhold during the ascent.</p>\r\n<p>Some of the more popular locations for bouldering are Worthless Boulder, located near 110th Street; Cat Rock, near <a title="Wollman Rink" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/wollman-rink.html">Wollman Rink</a>; and Rat Rock, near the <a title="Heckscher Ballfields" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/heckscher-ballfields.html">Heckscher Ballfields</a>. Rat Rock is most suitable for beginners, since expert climbers at the rock are usually willing to show new climbers the best routes. Worthless Boulder is more isolated and challenging.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'Bouldering in Central Park is a sport that is growing in popularity every year.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, umpire rock, running track, Sheep Meadow, rat rock, rock climbing, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, bouldering, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 12.90, 3, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document.MAX_used) document.MAX_used = '','';\r\n   document.write ("<scr"+"ipt type=''text/javascript'' src=''"+m3_u);\r\n   document.write ("?zoneid=7&amp;blockcampaign=1");\r\n   document.write (''&amp;cb='' + m3_r);\r\n   if (document.MAX_used != '','') document.write ("&amp;exclude=" + document.MAX_used);\r\n   document.write ("&amp;loc=" + escape(window.location));\r\n   if (document.referrer) document.write ("&amp;referer=" + escape(document.referrer));\r\n   if (document.context) document.write ("&context=" + escape(document.context));\r\n   if (document.mmm_fo) document.write ("&amp;mmm_fo=1");\r\n   document.write ("''></scr"+"ipt>");\r\n//]]>--></script><noscript><a href=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a98c2241&cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE'' target=''_blank''><img src=''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=7&n=a98c2241'' border=''0'' alt='''' /></a></noscript>\r\n', '', '', '', 'softball.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, 