(169, '2012-07-19', 17, 1, 14, 'Poster Maps', '', 'maps/poster-maps', 'Central Park Poster and Map', '<p>\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<p>CentralPark.com features two different Central Park&nbsp;<a title="central park maps" href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/maps-and-posters.html">poster maps</a> for sale. The first is a high resolution <a title="aerial view map of central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/maps-and-posters/central-park-poster.html">aerial view map</a> of the park that is so finely detailed that you can pick out individual trees. The second is a beautifully drawn <a title="central park map" href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/maps-and-posters/central-park-map.html">representational map</a> that lists all of the park''s many features and attractions, as well as important information like running distances throughout Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>Both posters were recently featured in the Hollywood hit movie&nbsp;<em>Extremely Loud &amp; Incredibly Close</em> with Tom Hanks and Sandra Bullock.&nbsp;<span>See an image&nbsp;</span><span>from the movie of the&nbsp;</span>aerial map&nbsp;<a title="central park poster extremely loud &amp; incredibly close" href="http://extremelyloudandincrediblyclose.warnerbros.com/images/photos/EL-00680r.jpg " target="_blank">here</a>&nbsp;and the drawn map&nbsp;<a title="central park map extremely loud &amp; incredibly close" href="http://extremelyloudandincrediblyclose.warnerbros.com/images/photos/EL-00577FD.jpg" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a title="buy central park maps" href="http://www.centralparkposters.com"><img title="buy now" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/buy_now_sm.png" alt="buy now button" width="100" height="25" /></a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Or visit&nbsp;<a title="Central Park Posters" href="http://www.centralparkposters.com" target="_blank">CentralParkPosters.com</a>&nbsp;for more information.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.centralparkposters.com"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/poster-small.jpg" border="0" alt="Central Park Poster" width="184" height="550" align="bottom" /></a></td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.centralparkposters.com"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/postershane_small.gif" border="0" alt="Central Park Map" width="172" height="550" align="bottom" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'Central Park on your home or office wall with these beautiful detailed maps and posters. Choose from an aerial view and a detailed drawn map featuring all of Central Park''s attractions and other important information such as running distances. ', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, Maps, runner''s map, central park map, central park aerial view, aerial view map, central park aerial view map, central park maps, central park poster, central park posters', 94.30, 29, '', '', '', '', 'sheep_meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Poster Maps', 'Poster Maps', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(170, '2011-07-07', 8, 1, 14, 'Map It', '', 'help/map-it', 'Map It in Central Park', '<table style="width: 90px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="90" height="152" align="right"><a onmouseover="return escape(''You can click and drag the red rectangle around the small map to change the area displayed in the Map It panel.'')" href="#"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about/small_map.gif" border="0" alt="" width="90" height="152" align="top" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td height="82"><a onmouseover="return escape(''You can click on the arrows to navigate around the map. By clicking on the dial you can return the map to full view.'')" href="#"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about/map_buttons.gif" border="0" alt="" width="90" height="82" align="top" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a onmouseover="return escape(''By clicking on the plus or minus signs you can control the maginification of the map.'')" href="#"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about/magnifier.gif" border="0" alt="" width="90" height="209" align="top" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The interactive Map It system helps you to locate features and landmarks inside Central Park. You can also zoom in on a location and  display it in high resolution.   <br /> <br />On the right of each Map It panel are some simple navigation controls (see photo on right).    <br /> <br />At the top there is there is a miniature version of the map displaying a red rectangle. This rectangle represents the area of the map that is  currently being viewed in the Map It panel. Click and drag the area to another part of the map you wish to  view, and this change will be reflected in the Map It panel.<br /> <br />Just below the small map there are four arrows and a dial.  By clicking on the arrows you can navigate around the map. The dial button returns the map to full view.   <br /> <br />Below the  buttons there is a crosshatched line with a plus or minus sign at each end. By  clicking on the plus or minus signs you can control the amount of magnification  displayed in the Map It panel.</p>\r\n<p><br /> <br /><br /></p>', 'The interactive Map It system helps you to locate features and landmarks inside Central Park. Zoom in on a location and display it in high resolution.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, map, distance, locator, map it', 26.20, 14, '', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Map It', 'Map It', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(171, '2011-07-07', 8, 1, 14, 'Page Icons', '', 'help/page-icons', 'Page Icons', '<p><a onmouseover="return escape(''You can click on the page icons to display relevant map information. You can also print, comment on and email the page contents.'')" href="#"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages//about/icons.gif" border="0" alt="" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="160" height="63" align="right" /></a>At the top of the center panel in each page there are up to four  icons.&nbsp;<br /> <br />The first is the Compass icon. This is displayed on every page  that has one or more map locations associated with it. Clicking on it will cause  the Map It panel to display.   <br /> <br />The second is the Comments icon. Clicking  on this icon will bring into view the comments page which you can use to enter  comments on the page content.   <br /> <br />The third icon is the Print this Page  icon. You can use this icon to print the page contents.   <br /> <br />The last is the  Email this Article icon. Clicking this will enable you to email the contents of  the page to a friend.</p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Page Icons', 'Page Icons', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(172, '2009-05-15', 152, 1, 8, 'Custom Opportunities', '', 'sponsors/custom-opportunities', 'Custom Opportunities - Advertising', '<p>If you want to market your business, brand or product to over 500,000 monthly unique smart, tech savvy individuals &ndash; you have come to the right place! CentralPark.com is a site dedicated to serving the 25 million yearly visitors to New York City&rsquo;s Central Park. It is the number one online destination throughout the world for anyone seeking information about the park. We&rsquo;ve created an online community of Central Park visitors and supporters that return on a regular basis for information on park events as well as the many interactive features which inform, involve and entertain.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Newsletters</strong></p>\r\n<p>CentralPark.com is dedicated to keeping our visitors up to date with everything and anything to do with the park. Our weekly, monthly and &ldquo;Special Edition&ldquo; newsletters are designed to keep our audience apprised of the latest and greatest from Central Park. They include valuable park information, exclusive offers, site updates, news, upcoming park events and much more. Total distribution is estimated to be up to 70,000 opt in users. Open rates are above industry standard as people who request information from us truly want it!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Influence</strong> . Readers depend on CentralPark.com to directly guide their use of the Park, whether visitng from around the corner or around the world. With interactive maps, comprehensive event database and hundreds of informative articles about Central Parkattractions CentralPark.com is the first stop for anyone planning a visit to the Park. <br /><br /><strong>Readership</strong> . CentralPark.com is growing rapidly. We''ve tripled our unique visitors since January of 2007, and expect to do the same by the end of 2008. <br /><br /><strong>Demographics</strong> . CentralPark.com&rsquo;s core user group consists of New Yorkers that live wit