(176, '2012-06-08', 10, 1, 15, 'Safety Tips', '', 'general-info/safety-tips', 'Safety Tips in Central Park', '<p>If you are planning on enjoying a day in Central Park, it is a good idea to know where the park''s safety resources are. Central Park has several call boxes that can be used in an emergency. Just some of these call boxes can be found in the following locations:</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> on West Drive at 100th, 102nd, 110th, 93rd, 90th, 83rd, 68th, and 60th Streets.</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> on East Drive at 102nd, 92nd, 90th, 84th, 79th, and 63rd Streets.</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> at the Mariner''s Playground.</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> at Mineral Springs.</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> at the Bernard Family Playground.</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> at the <a title="central park lasker pool and rink" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/lasker-pool-rink.html">Lasker Pool</a>.</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> at the <a title="central park conservatory garden" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/conservatory-garden.html">Conservatory Garden</a>.</p>\r\n<p><span>&raquo;</span> at the East 96th Street Playground.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><span>The Central Park Conservancy maintains an up-to-date list of the callbox locations in the park. Callboxes connect the caller directly to the&nbsp;</span><a title="central park police" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/general-info/central-park-police.html">Central Park Precinct</a><span>, though they can take up to half a minute to do so.</span></p>\r\n<p>The 843 acres that make up Central Park are patrolled by the <a title="central park police" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/general-info/central-park-police.html">Central Park Precinct</a>, a division of the New York City Police Department. This precinct can be reached by calling (212) 570-4820 or by visiting the station on the 86th Street Transverse Road, which cuts through the center of the park. The precinct can be found in the middle of that road, between the <a title="central park great lawn" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a> softball field and the <a title="central park reservoir" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/reservoir.html">Reservoir</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Medical needs within Central Park are often met by the <a title="central park medical unit" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/general-info/central-park-medical-unit.html">Central Park Medical Unit</a>, which is a volunteer ambulance service staffed entirely by New York state certified EMTs. The majority of calls to the CPMU are about bicycle and rollerblade accidents, as well as asthma attacks.</p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 4.90, 1, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Safety Tips', 'Safety Tips', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(177, '2009-05-15', 152, 1, 8, 'Promote Your Event', '', 'sponsors/promote-your-event', 'CentralPark.com ::: The Complete Guide to New York City''s Central Park', '<p>CentralPark.com offers the unique opportunity to promote your special event on our website. For a specified length of time your event will appear first on the CentralPark.com home page under "Today''s Events", with a photo or logo of your choice. Your event will also appear at the top of the search results for any event inquiry. In addition your event and description will be featured in the Weekly and Monthly Newsletters (when applicable). <br /><br />Please <a href="page.php?pid=175">contact</a> a member of the CentralPark.com ad sales team for more information.</p>', 'CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink, Central Park Zoo', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Promote Your Event', 'Promote Your Event', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(178, '2013-05-02', 17, 1, 15, 'Runner''s Map', '', 'maps/runner-s-map', 'Central Park Running Map', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="float: right; margin: 5px; border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/runners-map-front-300x360.jpg" alt="CentralPark.com Runner''s Map" width="200" height="240" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Central Park Running Map</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>You can download a free, printable version of our helpful running map&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/usr/maps/CentralParkRunningMap.pdf" target="_blank">here</a>. This map will allow you to determine your distance within a few meters.</p>\r\n<p><br /><em>If you need to download Adobe Acrobat you can click <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readstep2.html" target="_blank">here</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>', 'The CentralPark.com Runner''s Map is an essential tool for runners that use Central Park for workouts, and especially those preparing for the NYC Marathon.', 'central park running map, central park map, running in central park, central park running tracks, nyc marathon map, free running map, buy central park running map, central park runner''s map, free running map central park', 215.40, 144, '', '', '', '', 'sheep_meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Runner''s Map', 'Runner''s Map', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
