(267, '2013-10-24', 266, 2, 15, 'Greyshot Arch', '', 'attractions/bridges-of-central-park/greyshot-arch', 'Greyshot Arch in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Greyshot Arch" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/greyshot-arch-f.jpg"> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/greyshot-arch.jpg" border="0" alt="Greyshot Arch" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Greyshot Arch</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/raccettura/" target="_blank">raccettura</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Greyshot Arch, popular with bikers and runners, was built by Vaux in 1860.  The arch is made of white-gray gneiss, while its balustrade has been crafted from New Brunswick sandstone and decorated with fleur-de-lis carvings.  One of the most frequently used arches in Central Park, this arch is 80 feet long and ten feet high.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>Greyshot Arch is located near Merchant''s Gate, between 61st and 62nd Streets.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>', 'Greyshot Arch is located near Merchant''s Gate, between 61st and 62nd Streets.', 'merchant gate, biking, running, white-gray gneiss, Brunswick sandstone', 0.00, 0, '<script type=''text/javascript''><!--//<![CDATA[\r\n   var m3_u = (location.protocol==''https:''?''https://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'':''http://ads.centralpark.com/www/delivery/ajs.php'');\r\n   var m3_r = Math.floor(Math.random()*99999999999);\r\n   if (!document