(268, '2012-02-16', 5, 1, 15, 'Seneca Village', '', 'history/seneca-village', 'Seneca Village', '<p>Seneca Village was one of the first African American communities in New York City and&nbsp;existed from 1825 through 1857. It was located between 82nd and 89th Streets and Seventh and Eighth Avenues in what is now a&nbsp;part of Central Park. It was also&nbsp;Manhattan''s first significant community of African American property owners. By the 1840s, it had become a multi-ethnic community of&nbsp;African Americans, Irish, and German immigrants, and perhaps a few Native Americans. In 1855, the New York State Census reported approximately 264 individuals living in the village. This included three churches, as well as a school and several cemeteries.&nbsp; Good fortune for the residents of the city in general was bad luck for the residents of the tiny community - within two years&nbsp;Seneca Village would be razed and its identity erased by the creation of Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>For further information try these links:</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.learn.columbia.edu/seneca_village/htm/flash/map.htm" target="new">Seneca Village Project</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://projects.ilt.columbia.edu/seneca/frame.html" target="new">New-York Historical Society: Seneca Village and the Making of Central Park</a></p>', 'Central Park is online at CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'sheep_meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Seneca Village', 'Seneca Village', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(269, '2012-02-16', 145, 2, 1, 'Cristian Nicolescu', '', 'about-centralpark-com/staff/cristian-nicolescu', 'Cristian Nicolescu - CentralPark.com Staff', '<p><img src="http://en.gravatar.com/userimage/7843278/d69e07938e7c1cbfda44ec71ba877d78.jpg?size=150" alt="Cristian Nicolescu" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="150" height="150" align="right" /></p>\r\n<p>One of the most essential members of the CentralPark.com team is Cristian Nicolescu. His unique ability to take design concepts from drawing board to web reality makes his contribution to the success of this site incalculable (especially if you consider the exchange rate).</p>\r\n<p>Cristi was born, and resides, in the beautiful city of <a href="http://www.romaniatourism.com/bucharest.html">Bucharest, Romania</a>. From an early age he has been fascinated by science in general, while concentrating in Physics and Math, and has been programming since the age of 14.<span>&nbsp; </span>With CentralPark.com he has been successful in fulfilling his own goals of creating not only a technically dynamic website, but also one that combines ease of use and maintenance with cutting edge security.</p>\r\n<p>When not hard at work on CentralPark.com, Cristi enjoys playing the guitar and practicing indoor rock climbing. From time to time, he also writes on his <a href="http://mandagreen.com/" target="_blank">blog</a> or <a href="http://twitter.com/firewizard" target="_blank">tweets</a> about web stuff.</p>\r\n<p>We are very happy that the global workplace has expanded enough to allow us to employ this very gifted young man.</p>', 'His unique ability to take design concepts from drawing board to web reality makes his contribution to the success of CentralPark.com incalculable.', 'cristian nicolescu, web developer, web2.0, web design, php, mysql, web brands, social media, centralpark.com developer', 14.50, 3, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Cristian Nicolescu', 'Cristian Nicolescu', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(270, '2009-09-26', 271, 1, 14, 'Horse-Drawn Carriage Rides', '', 'hotels-and-tourism/horse-drawn-carriage-rides', 'Horse-Drawn Carriage Rides', '<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages//activities/carriage2.jpg" border="0" alt="Horse-drawn Carriage in Central Park" width="210" height="147" align="bottom" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://centralparkblogger.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Horse-Drawn Carriages in the Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Carriages can be found all year round lined up along Central Park South between 5th and 6th Avenues.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Legal Rate:<br /></strong>$34 for the first 1/2 hour and <br />$10 for each additional 1/4 hour.&nbsp;&nbsp; There is no tax.&nbsp; Cost is per ride, not per person.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Carriage Capacity:</strong> 4 Adults <strong><em>or</em></strong> 3 Adults and 2 children under the age of 12 <strong><em>or</em></strong> 1 Adult and 4 children under the age of 12</p>\r\n<!--<br />Call <a href="http://www.centralparkcarriages.com/" mce_href="http://www.centralparkcarriages.com/" target="_blank">Central Park Carriages</a> at 212-736-0680 for more information.-->', 'Horse-drawn carriage rides through Central Park are a unique and romantic way to see one of the most beautiful parts of New York City.', 'Horse-Drawn Carriages, Central Park, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, Horse Drawn Carriages', 51.50, 13, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Horse-Drawn Carriage Rides', 'Horse-Drawn Carriage Rides', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
