(274, '2014-10-27', 10, 1, 15, 'Adopt a Bench', '', 'general-info/adopt-a-bench', 'Adopt a Bench in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/adopt-a-bench.jpg" border="0" alt="Adopt a bench" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>The bench</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile9823.html" target="_blank">sebapg</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Adopting a Bench is a great way to support Central Park.  Established in 1986, the Adopt-a-Bench program has led to the adoption of over 2,000 of the Park''s 9,000 benches.</p>\r\n<p>The majority of benches can be adopted with a donation of $7,500, while a limited number of rustic benches can be adopted for $25,000.  Those who make these donations receive a personalized plaque on the bench that they choose.  There are four styles of benches available for adoption in specified areas: wood and concrete benches, rustic benches, world''s fair benches, and Central Park settees.</p>\r\n<p>You can download an Adopt-a-Bench application form from the <a title="adopt a bench" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.centralparknyc.org/assets/pdfs/forms-and-applications/Adopt-A-Bench-Form.pdf">Central Park Conservancy website</a>.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'Adopting a Bench is a great way to support Central Park. There are four styles of benches available for adoption in specified areas: wood and concrete benches, rustic benches, world''s fair benches, and Central Park settees.', 'adopting a central park bench,wood and concrete benches, rustic benches, world''s fair benches,Central Park settees.', 60.20, 14, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Adopt a Bench', 'Adopt a Bench', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(275, '2011-06-10', 10, 1, 14, 'Picnics', '', 'general-info/picnics', 'Central Park Picnics | Your Complete Guide to Picnics Central Park', '<p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img title="picnic in central park" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/picnic.png" alt="picnic in central park" width="230" height="165" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a title="View  stella0619''s profile" href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile30001.html">stella0619</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>A Picnic in Central Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nSpreading a blanket or sheet down for a picnic is a wonderful way to enjoy Central Park.&nbsp; For a small gathering with a handful of people, all you need to do is pick a spot and pack your picnic basket, then you are good to go.&nbsp; Favorite picnic locales in the park include the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/conservatory-garden.html">Conservatory Garden</a>, the<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/bridges-of-central-park/bow-bridge.html"> Bow Bridge</a>, <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/strawberry-fields.html">Strawberry Fields</a>, the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a> and the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/sheep-meadow.html">Sheep Meadow</a>. (Note that while usually a staple of picnicking, barbecuing is not permitted in Central Park).</p>\r\n<p>If you are looking to plan a larger-scale picnic, please check with  the <a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_permits_and_applications/events_faq.html" target="_blank">New York Department of Parks and Recreation</a>.&nbsp;  Parties of more than 20 people require a special permit which must be  obtained in advance.&nbsp; In addition, factors including planned  activities, location within the park, use of tables and chairs and others, also  determine whether a permit is needed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style="margin: 6px; float:  left;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/casual_picnic_basket_for_two.jpg" alt="Picnic Basket for Two." width="175" height="175" />Any great picnic requires planning and our <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">online store</a> has many of the essentials that you''ll need to get started.&nbsp; For a clean, dry surface to spread out on, check out the&nbsp; <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/central-park-picnic-blanket-and-carrier.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Water Resistant Picnic Blanket and Carrier</a> or the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/central-park-coffee-and-blanket-tote.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Coffee and Blanket Tote</a>.&nbsp; Pack all of your food and drink items into the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/central-park-picnic-backpack.html?utm_source=picnic&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Central Park Picnic Backpack</a>, the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/collapsible-picnic-basket-for-two-3.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Collapsible Picnic Basket for Two</a> or the <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/casual-picnic-basket-for-two.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Casual Picnic Basket for Two</a>.&nbsp; For a quick picnic on the run, consider the popular <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/central-park-picnic-set.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Picnic  Set</a>. Other fun picnic choices include an <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/eco-cooler-tote.html?utm_source=picnic&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Eco-Friendly Tote</a>, a <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/central-park-coffee-tote.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Coffee Tote</a> and for larger picnics a <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park/central-park-cooler-on-wheels.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Cooler on Wheels</a>. Click here for a complete listing of all of our <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/store/picnic-in-the-park.html?utm_source=Picnics&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Store%2BPromo">Picnic Items</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Spreading a blanket or sheet down for a picnic is a wonderful way to enjoy Central Park.  ', 'Central Park, central park picnic, picnic basket, picnic blanket, great lawn picnic, picnic in central park,', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Picnics', 'Picnics', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(276, '2009-10-18', 10, 1, 14, 'Special Event Planning', '', 'general-info/special-event-planning', 'Special Events Planning', '<p class="sectionhead"><img style="margin: 5px; float: right;" title="CP Wedding" src="http://www.centralpark.com/usr/photos/normal/33/pre-wedding.jpg" alt="" width="169" height="253" /> Are you thinking about planning an event in Central Park? Here''s everything you need to know to make it a success!&nbsp; Also, if you have a specific question regarding an event, or Central Park in general, you can always contact our staff using the form <a title="Contact page" href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>If your event is a wedding or a proposal, let our expert Wedding Support Staff help you with all the arrangements!&nbsp; Their page can be found <a title="Weddings" href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/general-info/weddings-in-central-park.html">here</a>.<br /><br />The best place to start answering your questions is the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation <a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_things_to_do/events/ev_faqs_manhattan.html" target="_blank">Special Event FAQ</a>.</p>\r\n<p>When thinking about your event, you should know that <strong>a</strong><span class="body"><strong>ll</strong> events in  the City of New York with more than 20 people attending will require special event permits. Please fill out the  <a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_permits_and_applications/planning_an_event.html" target="_blank">event application form</a> and fax to: Citywide Special Events, Fax: (212)  360-1478.</span></p>\r\n<p class="body">There is $25 non-refundable administrative processing fee for all  special events permits. <br />People who want to sell at, charge for, or  conduct any sort of revenue-generating activity on parkland for a short period  of time should read the <a class="links" href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_opportunities/business_ops/vendex_forms/tua.pdf" target="_blank">Temporary Use  Authorization (TUA) Guidelines</a> (16 kb).</p>\r\n<p class="body">More information about special events in Central Park can be found here:</p>\r\n<p class="body">&bull; <a class="links" href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_permits_and_applications/planning_an_event.html" target="_blank">Special Events  Request Approval Form</a><br />&bull; <a class="links" href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_permits_and_applications/planning_an_event.html" target="_blank">Special Events  Permit Application</a><br />&bull; <a class="links" href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_things_to_do/events/ev_special_events_guidelines.html" target="_blank">Special Events Guidelines<br /></a>&bull; <a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_about/rules_and_regulations/rr_2-10.html" target="_blank">Rules &amp;  Regulations for Special Events Concessions</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   <br />&bull; <a class="links" href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_things_to_do/events/ev_bbq_areas.html">Designated Barbecuing Areas in City Parks</a></p>\r\n<p><span class="bodybold">Citywide Special Events voicemail  information:</span><br /><span class="body">(212) 360-1319, or (212)-408-0226 <br /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class="body">Have fun! And don''t forget to submit your event to our CentralPark.com events database once you''ve made your plans! It only takes a few minutes. <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/login/">Start here</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p>Photo by JasonG</p>\r\n<p><span class="body"><br /></span></p>', 'Central Park is online at CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Special Event Planning', 'Special Event Planning', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(278, '2009-05-19', 11, 2, 14, 'Weddings in Central Park', '', 'faq/weddings-in-central-park', 'Weddings in Central Park', '<p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/wedding.jpg" border="0" alt="Wedding" width="210" height="195" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.centralparkblogger.com"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>John B. Moore</em> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>A Spring Wedding in Central Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nFrom the classically designed Conservatory Garden to the scenic panorama from Hernshead overlooking the Lake, Central Park''s 843 acres offer an endless array of romantic settings.&nbsp; Whether it''s in front of the Dancing Maidens of the Untermayer Fountain, underneath a pastorally secluded weeping willow near the Pool or above Bow Bridge on beautiful Cherry Hill the park has a site that will make your special day a memorable one.</p>\r\n<p>As you might expect there are some requirements for wedding ceremonies and photography in Central Park. Use&nbsp; the links below to find out more about what you need to do. We also added some useful suggestions, as well as some ways in which CentralPark.com''s wedding planning team can make the experience as simple, memorable and stress-free as possible.</p>\r\n<p><a href="/pages/activities/weddings/ceremonies.html"><strong>Ceremonies</strong></a> The park is one of the most romantic places on earth - but it is still part of the city.&nbsp; Wedding ceremonies in Central Park require permits and reservations.&nbsp; Click the link on the left to find out what you need to do.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href="/pages/activities/weddings/proposals.html">Proposals</a></strong> Make that special moment perfect by staging it in the perfect spot in the Park - from Belvedere Castle to Bethesda Terrace there is a spot that is right for you.&nbsp; Click on the link above for some great suggestions on the best places in the park to go down on one knee.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href="/pages/activities/weddings/receptions.html">Receptions</a></strong> There are a variety of venues in and around Central Park in which to celebrate your post "I do" festivities.&nbsp; Click on the link above to find out some of your options.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href="/pages/activities/weddings/photography.html">Photography</a></strong> Like weddings photography in Conservatory Garden requires a permit and a reservation.&nbsp; Click on the link to the left for al the information you need and some ideas on how make the most of your wedding day memories.</p>\r\n<p>Using our online form, you can <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact-wedding">request more specific information about weddings in Central Park</a>, or any other questions you might have about ceremonies or photography.</p>', 'Central Park is online at CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, family programs, Frederick Law Olmsted, Frederick Olmsted, Gates, Great Lawn, Greensward, Harlem Meer, Heckscher ballfields, Ice Skating, Imagine, Lasker Rink, Loeb Boathouse, merry-go-round, Metropolitan Museum, Obelisk, Olmsted, park, playground, public monuments, public park, Ramble, recreation programs, reservoir, rock climbing, row boating, running track, Sheep Meadow, skating, softball, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tennis, tennis court, tours, Vaux, volunteer, volunteer programs, walking tours, wall climbing, weekend, weekend actvities, weekend family programs, Wollman Rink', 2.50, 1, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Weddings in Central Park', 'Weddings in Central Park', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(279, '2013-11-09', 10, 1, 15, 'Wireless Access in Central Park', '', 'general-info/wireless-access-in-central-park', 'Wireless Access in Central Park', '<p><strong>Learn About the Best Places to Get Online Access in Central Park, New York City</strong></p>\r\n<p>Central Park is not only the first public park built in the U.S., but it is also arguably the most famous. Every year, 25 million people visit the park for vacation, recreation or even as a brief respite from business. With our incredibly connected world today, it&rsquo;s inevitable that park-goers will want to get online during their visit.<span> </span></p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6">Throughout New York City, the Parks and Recreation department is setting up AT&amp;T Wi-Fi hot spots to enable greater connectivity. The five-year initiative will provide access at 26 locations throughout all five boroughs. Four of these locations are within Central Park.</p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6">In addition, there are other groups throughout the city that are working to provide free online access such as NYCwireless. Some of these locations will be close to the park, but not inside it, so coverage may not be as reliable.</p>\r\n<p class="c1"><span class="c3 c0"><strong>How to Get Online During Your Visit</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6">For the best chances of getting online, visit one of the AT&amp;T hot spots. They are located at:</p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6"><span class="c0">&middot; </span><span class="c3 c0"><strong>Mineral Springs Pavilion</strong>:&nbsp;</span><span class="c0">Located between 69th St. and 70th St. on the west side of the park right next to Sheep Meadow, Mineral Springs Pavilion offers park-goers a place to relax and grab a bite to eat. The eatery is operated by Le Pain Quotidien, a Belgian restaurant, and it serves bread, soup, sandwiches and other light fare. The terrace sits up to 100 people, making it the perfect place to sit and snack while checking your email or catching up on some quick business.</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6"><span class="c0">&middot;&nbsp;</span><span class="c3 c0"><strong>Rumsey Playfield</strong>:&nbsp;</span><span class="c0">Host of the Central Park SummerStage concerts, Rumsey Playfield hosts thousands of music-goers every year. The free Wi-Fi in this area is available June through September, in conjunction with the SummerStage series. Rumsey Playfield is on the east side of the park, and is accessible via E. 69th St.</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6"><span class="c0">&middot;&nbsp;</span><span class="c3 c0"><strong>Central Park Zoo</strong>:&nbsp;</span><span class="c0">New York&rsquo;s famed Central Park Zoo is home to a wide range of wild animals, and now, you can hop online and play social games on your iPad or do more complex work such as attend an online learning course on web development or learn</span><span class="c0"><a class="c5" href="http://www.shopwpthemes.com/how-to-guides/how-to-install-wordpress-on-bluehost/">&nbsp;</a></span><span class="c2 c0"><a class="c5" href="http://www.shopwpthemes.com/how-to-guides/how-to-install-wordpress-on-bluehost/">how to install WordPress on BlueHost</a></span><span class="c0">&nbsp;in between animal watching. The Zoo is on the southeast side of the park near E. 64th St.</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6"><span class="c0">&middot;&nbsp;</span><span class="c3 c0"><strong>Tavern on the Green</strong>:&nbsp;</span><span class="c0">Tavern on the Green is not only a dining hot spot, but now it&rsquo;s a Wi-Fi hot spot as well. The restaurant is currently undergoing a renovation, but is slated to reopen in December of 2013. It is located on the west side between W. 66th St. and W. 67th St.</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1"><span class="c0">To log on at any of these locations, look for the network name &ldquo;attwifi&rdquo; on your computer and click on it. You do not need a username or password, and best of all, you don&rsquo;t need to pay anything.</span></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p class="c1"><span class="c3 c0"><strong>Other Ways to Log On in the Park</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class="c1"><span class="c0">There are other groups working to provide free wireless throughout the city. Most of these groups are devoted to providing wireless in one area of the city, such as Union Square or Bryant Park. However, NYCwireless is one group looking at the city as a whole. You can check out their website (</span><span class="c2 c0"><a class="c5" href="http://www.nycwireless.net/">www.nycwireless.net</a></span><span class="c0">) to view a list of hot spots in the area, some of which are in the vicinity of Central Park. For example, the Apple store on Fifth Ave. next to the park is one place where you can get free Wi-Fi.</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1"><span class="c0">In addition, you can check out the Open WiFi NYC site (</span><span class="c2 c0"><a class="c5" href="http://www.openwifinyc.com/">www.openwifinyc.com</a></span><span class="c0">), which lists free hot spots throughout New York City.</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1"><span class="c3 c0"><strong>Follow the People for the Best Access</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class="c1"><span class="c0">Overall, if you&rsquo;re looking to get online during your visit to Central Park, it makes the most sense to stick to the most densely populated areas in the park, which are generally on the southern half. You can also look for restaurants and cafes along the border of the park which are likely to provide free access.</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1" style="text-align: right;"><span class="c0">-By Kathryn Sucich</span></p>\r\n<p class="c1 c6" style="text-align: left;"><em><span class="c0 c4">Kathryn Sucich is a freelance writer and fan of the latest technology for both business and personal use. While she may not be able to tell you how to use the</span><span class="c0 c4"><a class="c5" href="http://www.shopwpthemes.com/blog/wordpress-email-plugin/">&nbsp;</a></span><span class="c2 c0 c4"><a class="c5" href="http://www.shopwpthemes.com/blog/wordpress-email-plugin/">WordPress email plugin</a></span><span class="c0 c4">, she can tell you about her favorite iPhone apps or e-books that she&rsquo;s read.</span></em></p>\r\n<div style="text-align: left;"><span class="c0 c4"><br /></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Learn about the best places to get online wifi access in Central Park, New York City.\r\n', 'wifi Central Park, wi fi central park, wifi new york, wi fi new york, wifi nyc, wi fi nyc, wifi new york city, wi fi new york city, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Conservancy, Central Park History, children, climbing wall, conservancy, wireless, wifi, internet access in central park.', 6.90, 4, '', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Wireless Access', 'Wireless Access', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
