(284, '2009-05-15', 145, 2, 14, 'Ramona Quincey', '', 'about-centralpark-com/staff/ramona-quincey', 'Central Park The Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<p><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Ramona Quincey is the<span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helv;"> Marketing Director</span> at CentralPark.com</span> <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/about/RamonaQuincey.jpg" alt="Ramona Quincy" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="172" height="227" align="right" /><br /><br /><span style="font-family: Verdana;">Ramona Quincey was born and raised on the remote island of Hawaii, lived her teenage years in the Bay Area, California and her college years in Orange County. Ramona received her BA in Communication Studies from California State University Long Beach, and her Executive MBA in Media Management from Metropolitan College of New York.   <br /><br />Ramona&rsquo;s passion in life is adventure. She has traveled extensively, including living in Brighton Beach, UK for a period of her life, and attending the Cannes Film Festival. Her ideal vacation would include a beach, a hammock, and the Harry Potter series.<br /><br />Ramona''s favorite part of Central Park is the Reservoir, which she enjoys running around during warm weather.&nbsp; She also hopes to take part in an upcoming New York Marathon.&nbsp; She is easily the most cheerful member of the staff.<br /><br />email - Ramona at CentralPark.com<br /><br />Ramona can also be reached by IM at:<br /><br />Yahoo: ramonaquincey<br />AOL: quinceyr12<br /></span></p>', 'Central Park is online at CentralPark.com - Your first stop for information on Central Park and The Central Park Zoo!  Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, ballfields, Balto, baseball, basketball, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, bike, Boathouse, Bow Bridge, Calvert Vaux, Carousel, Central Park Con