(383, '2013-10-24', 2, 1, 1, 'Cherry Blossom Trees in Central Park', '', 'attractions/cherry-blossom-trees', 'Cherry Blossom Trees in Central Park', '<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Central Park Cherry Blossoms" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/central-park-cherry-blossoms-f.jpg"> <img title="Central Park Cherry Tree" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/cherry-tree.jpg" border="0" alt="Central Park Cherry Tree in Blossom" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Central Park Cherry Blossoms</strong> by             <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profiles/K_Ogonosky">K_OGONOSKY</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>In the springtime from mid to late April and May there are two species of cherry trees in season in Central Park. The Kwanzan Cherry and Yoshino Cherry are in both in bloom for tourists and residents to gaze upon, as they blend in perfectly, completing the park''s stunningly aesthetic scenery during these months.</p>\r\n<p>The Yoshino Cherry is the most popular ornamental cherry tree planted in Central Park. In mid to late April those perusing the park can expect to see the first buds of these trees typically blossoming before any other tree or flower. Before the leaves appear on the trees pale pink flowers emerge in clusters of five or six. Then as the tree''s leaves grow, they are usually a bronze color when they first develop then change to a darker green as the summer approaches. The origin of the Yoshino Cherry, which produces a hybrid cherry, is not specific. However, it is known that the first trees were brought as a gift into the U.S. from Japan in 1912. These trees, which grow up to 30 feet, are believed to be the ones along the east side of the Reservoir.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>In Central Park there are numerous areas populated with the Yoshino Cherry, such as the east side of the <a title="central park reservoir" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/reservoir.html">Reservoir</a>, Lilac Walk (northeast of Sheep Meadow), <a title="conservatory water central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/conservatory-water.html">Conservatory Water</a>, <a title="ramble central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/ramble.html">Ramble</a> (mid-Park at 72nd Street), <a title="delacorte theater central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/delacorte-theatre.html">Delacorte Theater</a> (mid-Park at 80th Street) and at the southeast edge of <a title="great lawn central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The Kwanzan Cherry, also known as the Japanese Cherry, is an ornamental cherry tree that is most commonly found in Japan, Korea and China. This particular tree has double-petal pink flowers, which start to bloom in early May after the Yoshino Cherry. When these trees first bloom their leaves are bronze colored and then turn dark green to yellow to orange and then finally to copper in autumn. These trees are fairly small, growing to reach 25 to 30 feet, and have a wide vase-shaped spreading crown. The life span of the Kwanzan Cherry, which does not produce fruit, is 15 to 25 years.</p>\r\n<p>There are several locations where the Kwanzan Cherry resides in Central Park, including the West side of the&nbsp;<a title="central park reservoir" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/reservoir.html">Reservoir</a>, East Green, West of <a title="metropolitan museum of art" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/museums/metropolitan-museum-of-art.html">Metropolitan Museum</a> at East 83rd to 84th Streets, East Drive at 74th Street, Bethesda Terrace (mid-Park at 72nd Street), across the east Drive from the <a title="loeb boathouse central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/loeb-boathouse.html">Loeb Boathouse</a> and at the Southeast corner of the Great Lawn Oval.</p>\r\n<p>There are several festivals worldwide that celebrate these types of cherry blossom trees known for their dramatic beauty. In New York City there is the Cherry Blossom Festival in the Brooklyn Botanic Garden which typically takes place in April or May.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Vanessa Oswald</small></p>', 'Both the Kwanzan Cherry trees and the Yoshino Cherry trees are in bloom for tourists and residents to gaze upon, completing the park''s stunningly aesthetic scenery during the spring months.', 'cherry blossom trees central park', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Cherry Blossom Trees', 'Cherry Blossom Trees', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(384, '2009-05-19', 0, 0, 0, 'Central Park Videos', '', 'central-park-videos', 'Central Park Videos', '<div id="vu_ytplayer_vjVQa1PpcFOez6EHBFYqmIRB1zFrZuuqnmCvLsGTY2k="><a href="http://www.youtube.com/browse">Watch the latest videos on YouTube.com</a></div>\r\n<p>\r\n<script src="http://www.youtube.com/cp/vjVQa1PpcFOez6EHBFYqmIRB1zFrZuuqnmCvLsGTY2k=" type="text/javascript"></script>\r\n</p>', '', '', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'header_image2.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Central Park Videos', 'Central Park Videos', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(385, '2013-08-19', 5, 1, 15, 'Frederick Law Olmsted', '', 'history/frederick-law-olmsted', 'Frederick Law Olmsted, Architect of Central Park', '<p>Olmsted spent his first two adult decades searching for a calling while  remaining financially dependent on his father, a prosperous dry goods merchant  and descendant of a prominent Puritan family in Hartford, Connecticut. (Raised a  Congregationalist, Olmsted avoided organized religion in later years.) He was  driven by a sense of duty but found pursuing a career for money distasteful.  Because a case of sumac poisoning weakened his eyes, Olmsted''s formal education  -- a combination of common and boarding schools -- ended when he was eighteen.  While his brother and<img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/history/olmsted.jpg" border="0" alt="Edward Law Olmsted" hspace="4" vspace="4" width="180" height="250" align="right" /> closest friends were attending Yale, he tried a year as a  clerk in a New York dry goods house and another year at sea. Neither pursuit  proved agreeable. In the mid-1840s he prepared for what he thought would be a  suitable profession as a gentleman farmer by living and studying with several  prominent agriculturalists, among them George Geddes, whose upstate New York  farm had won the state agricultural society prize for exemplary management. When his father bought him farms first in  Connecticut and then on Staten Island, Olmsted envisioned himself as a "country  squire" with a responsibility to disseminate scientific knowledge and rural  taste. <br /><br />{{ADSPACE_300_250}}<br /><br />As a youth, <strong>Frederick Law Olmsted</strong> traveled through the  New England countryside with his father, who admired rural scenery; and as a  young gentleman farmer, he read the latest literature on art criticism  (including Ruskin''s Modern Painters), on horticulture, and on English landscape  gardening. He wrote articles for Downing''s Horticulturalist on pear and apple  farming and another on the attractions of Liverpool''s Birkenhead Park. With the  rural improvement movement at its peak, he also helped organize an agricultural  society on Staten Island for the promotion of rural tastes and scientific  agriculture. But while Olmsted learned the art of landscape appreciation and the  latest theories in rural improvement, he gained little experience in the work of  design. <br /><br />In the 1850s, Olmsted abandoned model  farming for journalism, another field in which he hoped "to take up and keep a  position as a recognized literateur, a man of influence in literary matters."  Following a trip to England, he published <em>Walks and Talks of an American Farmer</em> in England, which combined observations on the English social landscape with  sentimental invocations of "Old England for ever! -- Amen." He took several  journeys through the American South and sent a series of letters to the New York  Times that formed the basis for his three influential books on southern mores  and the economic conditions of slavery. In 1855 Olmsted became both a managing  editor of Putnam''s Magazine and a partner (again through his father''s  investment) in the publishing house of Dix and Edwards, which was publishing his  second book.&nbsp; The Dix and Edwards firm became an early casualty  of the 1857 depression. A family friend, Park Commissioner Charles Elliott,  encouraged Olmsted to apply for the post of the park superintendent, and he did  so.</p>\r\n<p align="center">All text from:<br /> <br /> <span style="font-size: small;"><strong><em>The Park and the  People</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<div>Courtesy of Barbara Blackmar &amp; Roy Rosenzweig<br /> <a href="http://www.centralparkhistory.com/the_book/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.centralparkhistory.com/common/images/icon_book.gif" border="0" alt="" vspace="5" width="49" height="73" /></a> <br /> <a href="http://www.centralparkhistory.com/the_book/" target="_blank">Click here  for<br />more info.</a></div>', 'Frederick Law Olmsted was a landscape designer and  architect, famous for designing (together with Calvert Vaux) New York''s Central Park.', 'frederick law olmsted, central park architecture, calvert vaux, new york landscape architecture, walks and talks of an american farmer', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'sheep_meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Frederick Law Olmsted', 'Frederick Law Olmsted', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(387, '2012-03-21', 3, 1, 14, '150 Anniversary of Greensward Plan', '', 'activities/150-anniversary-of-greensward-plan', '150 Anniversary of Greensward Plan', '<p>2008 marks 150th anniversary of the Greensward Plan, Frederick Law Olmsted''s and Calvert Vaux''s design for Central Park.&nbsp; <br /><br />To observe the event there is an exhibition at the Arsenal in Central Park. The Central Park Conservancy and the New York City Department of Parks &amp;  Recreation are hosting a free, special exhibition at the Arsenal celebrating the  history of the Park, its landscape and use, subsequent deterioration, and recent  transformation by the Central Park Conservancy.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br /><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/ev_details.php?showev=584">more..</a><br /><br />On October 13, 1857, just  two weeks after the original park dwellers left their homes, the Board of  Commissioners of Central Park offered prizes of four hundred to two thousand  dollars for the four best proposals for "laying out the park." This notice for  the first important landscape design competition in the United States elicited  thirty-three varied proposals, which revealed the influence of English and  continental traditions of landscape design as well as more eclectic vernacular  ideas about what would make this public place appealing. But when the  commissioners opened the proposals six months later, they found one curious  entry. Plan 2 by an anonymous contestant was nothing but a pyramid. <br /><br /><a href="/pages/history/greensward-plan.html">more..</a></p>', 'CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 1002. 2008 marks 150th anniversary of the Greensward Plan.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, Bow Bridge, Central Park Maps, Great Lawn, reservoir, running track, Sheep Meadow, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tours, walking tours, Wollman Rink, 150th anniversary greensward plan, greensward plan', 4.60, 1, '', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 1, 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, '150 Anniversary of Greensward Plan', '150 Anniversary of Greensward Plan', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(388, '2015-06-17', 92, 1, 15, 'Proposals', '', 'weddings/proposals', 'Wedding Proposals in Central Park', '<div>\r\n<script src="https://fareharbor.com/embeds/api/v1/"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>We''ve put together a sample wedding proposal package with some of our most popular services to get you started with the basics.</p>\r\n<p>You can also create your own custom proposal package - please <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact/wedding">contact us</a> to get started!</p>\r\n<p class="alignC"><a class="noHoverBg" onclick="FH &amp;&amp; FH.open &amp;&amp; FH.open({shortname: ''acentralparkwedding'', asn: ''centralpark'', items: [2322], view: ''all-availability''}); return false;" href="https://fareharbor.com/acentralparkwedding/items/2322/"><img src="/usr/media/weddings/wedding-reserve-online-button.png" alt="reserve online" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SURPRISE PROPOSAL PACKAGE - $1,250.00</h3>\r\n<p>Our sample package is fully customizable and includes:</p>\r\n<ul class="bullet">\r\n<li>Assistance selecting proposal location</li>\r\n<li>Proposal day coordination </li>\r\n<li>One hour of professional photography and all print-quality images on disc</li>\r\n<li>One dozen roses in the color of your choosing </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>If you have an idea for your proposal that you don&rsquo;t see listed, please <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact/wedding">contact us</a> to discuss!</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>PROPOSAL PACKAGE ADD-ONS:</h3>\r\n<p>The following services can be added to the above package. You can also remove anything to customize as you see fit.</p>\r\n<ul class="bullet">\r\n<li>Walkthrough of proposal prior to the day</li>\r\n<li>Additional hour of photography</li>\r\n<li>Acoustic soloist to play during or after proposal</li>\r\n<li>Upgrade to custom floral arrangement</li>\r\n<li>Romantic picnic for two</li>\r\n<li><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/horse-carriage-tours.html">Horse drawn carriage ride</a> through Central Park</li>\r\n<li>Gondola ride around the lake</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>Please&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact/wedding">contact us</a>&nbsp;for more details and pricing.</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>PROPOSAL LOCATION IDEAS:</h3>\r\n<p>Here are some romantic Central Park proposal locations to consider:</p>\r\n<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/loeb-boathouse.jpg" border="0" alt="Loeb Boathouse" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Willows in front of the Boathouse</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile8272.html" target="_blank">valda64</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/loeb-boathouse.html">The Loeb Boathouse</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>The Loeb Boathouse is a beautiful setting for a quiet lunch watching swans drift along the still water. The boathouse also offers Venetian gondola rides complete with serenades of classic arias for a romantic experience.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/bow-bridge.jpg" border="0" alt="Bow Brige" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Bow Bridge stretches across the Lake in Central Park</strong> by 	<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html"><em>Rick Anderson</em></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/bridges-of-central-park/bow-bridge.html">Bow Bridge</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>Sunset creates the perfect scene to propose in the middle of Bow Bridge. The Bow Bridge has been a magnificent setting for lovers from around the world and also in famous films such as Manhattan and Keeping the Faith.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Central Park Carousel" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/flowers-and-the-carousel.jpg" alt="Central Park Carousel" width="200" height="152" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Flowers and the Carousel</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profiles/Cartagena"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>by Cartagena</em> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/carousel.html">The Carousel</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>Propose after you&rsquo;ve enjoyed a ride on The Carousel at 64th street. It continues to be one of the most popular attractions in Central Park with an interesting history and a bit of romantic symbolism.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style="background: #ffffff; margin: 0 0 3px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% #ffffff; width: 200px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/shakespeare-garden.jpg" alt="Shakespeare Garden" width="200" height="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: xx-small;" align="right"><strong>Shakespeare Garden</strong> by <em><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile29854.html" target="_blank">eilypily</a></em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/shakespeare-garden.html">Shakespeare Garden</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>Take a relaxing stroll along the winding paths of Shakespeare Garden and propose within its serene and romantic atmosphere, or maybe pop the question just around the corner on Belvedere Castle Terrace.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to helping you plan your special day in New York City''s beautiful Central Park! Please <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact/wedding">contact us</a> with any questions.</p>\r\n<p class="alignC"><a class="noHoverBg" onclick="FH &amp;&amp; FH.open &amp;&amp; FH.open({shortname: ''acentralparkwedding'', asn: ''centralpark'', items: [2322], view: ''all-availability''}); return false;" href="https://fareharbor.com/acentralparkwedding/items/2322/"><img src="/usr/media/weddings/wedding-reserve-online-button.png" alt="reserve online" /></a></p>', 'Central Park is one of the best locations in New York City to propose. Make your proposal memorable and choose an ideal spot to get down on one knee. Our partner provides start-to-finish assistance with all of the special details of your unique proposal. ', '', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'weddings-in-central-park.jpg', 'Fotovolia', '', '', 0, '/usr/media/weddings.v2/weddings.v2.css', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Proposals', 'Proposals', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(389, '2014-10-30', 92, 1, 14, 'Photography', '', 'weddings/photography', 'Central Park Wedding Photography', '<table style="margin-left: 10px" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/wed4a.jpg" border="0" alt="Silhouettes in front of Bethesda Fountain" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="180" height="270" align="right" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/sharon-bushman.html"> <span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Sharon Bushman</em> </span> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Silhouettes underneath<br /> Bethesda Terrace</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>One of the most important components of successful nuptial celebrations is the photographic record of the event. Central Park features some of the most amazing scenery in New York City so you''ll want to be sure to have all the information and resources you need to make your wedding album a treasure for years to come. Below you''ll find information and links to assist you with planning, and a few suggestions for services our CentralPark.com wedding planning team can provide.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><em><a class="noHoverBg" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/weddings/ceremony-packages.html"><img src="/usr/media/weddings/wedding-reserve-online-button.png" alt="Reserve Online" /></a></em></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We offer three different <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/weddings/ceremony-packages.html">Wedding Packages</a> that are customizable to fit your needs.  These services include all the essential components that will make your wedding day memorable in every way.</p>\r\n<p>One of the most popular locations for wedding photography in Central Park is <a href="page.php?pid=41">Conservatory Garden</a>. The Conservatory Garden is comprised of three beautiful areas; the North Garden, the South Garden, and Wisteria Pergola. Each garden has its own unique look decorated with statues, trees and flowers that change from fall to spring.</p>\r\n<p>A special permit is required to take photographs in Conservatory Gardens due to the wonderful upkeep. Apart from the gardens, other popular places for wedding photographs include Cherry Hill, Bow Bridge, Shakespeare Garden, Bethesda Fountain, Belvedere Castle Terrace, Ladies Pavilion, the Mall, Wagner Cove, the 100th Street Pool, Cop Cot and the Harlem Meer.  For more information, please call the Special Events &amp; Permits Office of the NYC Department of Parks &amp; Recreation at 212-408-0226 or visit their <a href="http://www.nyc.gov/parks" target="_blank">website</a>.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>The following are some popular photographic services offered by CentralPark.com wedding planners. <strong>For more information about any of our services, or Central Park weddings in general, please click <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact-wedding" target="_blank">here</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Here are some unique Central Park photography ideas:</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Surprise Proposal:</strong> This is a very romantic way to make your proposal more memorable. Our team works with you directly to organize your Central Park engagement. On the day-of, we meet you at your desired location to photograph that special moment. Afterwards, we take pictures of you and your fianc&eacute; in beautiful locations around Central Park.</em></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Engagement:</strong> Central Park can be the beautiful background for your engagement photographs. We take you and your fianc&eacute; to various locations in the park to get the best pictures. Our team will make it an enjoyable experience for you both. These photograph packages include:</em></p>\r\n<p><em> <strong>&raquo;</strong> Your desired hours of photography. <br /> <strong>&raquo;</strong> All your picture files on a CD. <br /> <strong>&raquo;</strong> Additional shots as requested. </em></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Wedding: </strong>Have your beautiful Central Park wedding photographed by a professional photographer! Take advantage of the amazing sceneries of the park on your big day.</em></p>\r\n<p><em> <strong>&raquo;</strong> Your desired hours of photography. <br /> <strong>&raquo;</strong> All your picture files on a CD. <br /> <strong>&raquo;</strong> Additional location shots as requested. </em></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Trash The Dress:</strong> Never going to use your wedding dress again? Then there is no better place to Trash the Dress than in Central Park! Have fun getting all dressed-up again and take creative photographs trashing your dress. This is a unique way to get some artistic shots in various Central Park locations.</em></p>\r\n<p><em> <strong>&raquo;</strong> Your desired hours of photography.<br /> <strong>&raquo;</strong> All your picture files on a CD.<br /> <strong>&raquo;</strong> Additional shots as requested. </em></p>\r\n<p>For more information about any of these services, or Central Park weddings in general, please click <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact-wedding" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="alignC"><a class="noHoverBg" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/weddings/ceremony-packages.html"> <img src="/usr/media/weddings/wedding-reserve-online-button.png" alt="Reserve Online" /> </a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 1002. Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, Bow Bridge, Central Park Maps, Great Lawn, reservoir, running track, Sheep Meadow, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tours, walking tours, Wollman Rink, wedding photography, wedding pictures', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'weddings-in-central-park.jpg', 'Fotovolia', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Photography', 'Photography', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
