(390, '2015-06-23', 92, 1, 15, 'Ceremonies', '', 'weddings/ceremonies', 'Wedding Ceremonies in Central Park', '<div>\r\n<script src="https://fareharbor.com/embeds/api/v1/"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<table style="background: #ffffff; margin-left: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 11px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 1px solid #d0d0d0;" title="Wedding Ceremony in Central Park" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/wagner-cove-jessica-schmitt-photography.jpg" alt="Wedding Ceremony in Central Park" width="200" height="132" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: 10px; line-height: 13px; padding-left: 2px" align="left">Jessica Schmitt Photography</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>We''ve put together a sample wedding ceremony package with some of our most popular services to get you started with the basics.</p>\r\n<p>Feel free to&nbsp;<a title="wedding contact us" href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact/wedding">contact us</a>&nbsp;if you have any questions.</p>\r\n<p>Book your custom wedding package:</p>\r\n<p><a class="noHoverBg" onclick="FH &amp;&amp; FH.open &amp;&amp; FH.open({ shortname: ''acentralparkwedding'', asn: ''centralpark'', view: { item: 3667 } }); return false;" href="https://fareharbor.com/acentralparkwedding/items/3667/"><img src="/usr/media/weddings/wedding-reserve-online-button.png" alt="reserve online" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>A CENTRAL PARK WEDDING PACKAGE - $2,950</h3>\r\n<p>Our sample package is fully customizable and includes:</p>\r\n<ul class="bullet">\r\n<li>Central Park wedding permit </li>\r\n<li>Services of a dedicated wedding planner</li>\r\n<li>Walkthrough of ceremony prior to wedding day</li>\r\n<li>Wedding day coordination </li>\r\n<li>Officiant</li>\r\n<li>Two hours of photography</li>\r\n<li>Round bridal bouquet</li>\r\n<li>Matching boutonniere</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>CUSTOM WEDDING PACKAGE ADD-ONS:</h3>\r\n<p>The following services can be added to our sample package. You can also remove anything that you don''t need.<!-- or choose a date on the calendar to get started creating your own custom ceremony package! --><!-- calendar --></p>\r\n<ul class="bullet">\r\n<li>Hair and makeup styling</li>\r\n<li>Additional hours of photography</li>\r\n<li>Extended videography packages</li>\r\n<li>Floral centerpieces for your wedding reception</li>\r\n<li>Acoustic musicians</li>\r\n<li>Custom wedding ceremony</li>\r\n<li>Custom wedding cake delivered to your reception venue</li>\r\n<li>Transportation to and from your wedding</li>\r\n<li>Preferred pricing for accommodations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you''ve decided on your package details, we''ll provide you with a contract that includes your custom package and our services. A signed contract and 25% wedding package retainer will secure our planning services. The remaining package balance will be due two weeks before your wedding date.</p>\r\n<p>All payments can be made safely and securely through our online reservation system using a credit card.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>CEREMONY LOCATION IDEAS:</h3>\r\n<p>Here are some romantic Central Park ceremony locations to consider:</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/weddings/acentralparkwedding.com-ladies-pavilion.jpg" alt="Ladies Pavilion" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Ladies Pavilion</strong> by <br /><em>Angela Gaspar Photography</em> </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/ladies-pavilion.html">Ladies Pavilion</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>One of the most popular locations for Central Park weddings, this beautiful cast-iron pavilion is situated on The Lake with the city skyline as a backdrop. This location is perfect for an intimate ceremony in the park.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/weddings/acentralparkwedding.com-cop-cot.jpg" alt="Cop Cot" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Cop Cot</strong> by <em>Fotovolida</em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/cop-cot.html">Cop Cot</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>Scottish for "little house on the crest of a hill," Cop Cot overlooks the park and Central Park South. This rustic wooden gazebo offers a private ceremony location that is easily accessible from the road.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/weddings/acentralparkwedding.com-conservatory-garden.jpg" alt="Conservatory Garden" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Conservatory Garden</strong> </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/conservatory-garden.html">Conservatory Garden</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>The Conservatory Garden is made of three separate gardens, each landscaped in a different style. Hold your ceremony under the shade of Wisteria Pergola in the Italian Garden or under a floral arch in the French Garden. Or get married by the peaceful shaded pool in the center of the English Garden.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click the button below to get started booking your wedding:</p>\r\n<p><a class="noHoverBg" onclick="FH &amp;&amp; FH.open &amp;&amp; FH.open({ shortname: ''acentralparkwedding'', asn: ''centralpark'', view: { item: 3667 } }); return false;" href="https://fareharbor.com/acentralparkwedding/items/3667/"><img src="/usr/media/weddings/wedding-reserve-online-button.png" alt="reserve online" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Take our&nbsp;<a title="central park wedding poll" href="https://www.facebook.com/centralpark/app_126231547426086" target="_blank">wedding poll</a>&nbsp;and help us decide the best location to get married in Central Park!</p>', 'Have your dream wedding in Central Park! Design your own custom package or let us help you with the details. We take care of all the details, from the permit, to the wedding planner, to the officiant, photography and more.\r\n', 'central park wedding, central park wedding ceremony, get married in central park, bethesda fountain, belvedere castle, wagner cove, cherry hill, carousel, central park boathouse, central park lake, conservatory garden, central park proposal, central park wedding permits, central park wedding planner. wedding officiant, central park wedding photography', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'weddings-in-central-park.jpg', 'Fotovolia', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(391, '2015-06-14', 92, 1, 15, 'Receptions', '', 'weddings/receptions', 'Receptions in Central Park', '<div>\r\n<script src="https://fareharbor.com/embeds/api/v1/"></script>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>If you book your wedding ceremony through CentralPark.com,&nbsp;we can also assist you in picking a reception location.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A picnic in the park or dinner at the Central Park Boathouse can be a lovely way to celebrate your wedding.</p>\r\n<p>If you would prefer to celebrate with a view of Central Park, there are numerous options within walking distance. Be sure to consider transportation, convenience and services provided when planning your wedding reception.</p>\r\n<p>For information about wedding celebrations in general, or any of the ways we can assist you please <a href="/contact/wedding">contact us</a>.</p>\r\n<p class="alignC"><a class="noHoverBg" onclick="FH &amp;&amp; FH.open &amp;&amp; FH.open({ shortname: ''acentralparkwedding'', asn: ''centralpark'', view: { item: 3667 } }); return false;" href="https://fareharbor.com/acentralparkwedding/items/3667/"><img src="/usr/media/weddings/wedding-reserve-online-button.png" alt="reserve online" /></a></p>\r\n<div>{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'A picnic in the park or dinner at the Central Park Boathouse can be a lovely way to celebrate your wedding. Choose from numerous wedding reception options within walking distance, some including fantastic views of Central Park and New York City.', '', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'weddings-in-central-park.jpg', 'Fotovolia', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Receptions', 'Receptions', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(392, '2009-10-03', 87, 1, 6, 'Tamandua', '', 'central-park-zoo/tamandua', 'Tamandua - Central Park Zoo', '<p><strong><span style="font-size: small;">Tamandua</span> </strong>( Tamandua Tetradactyla)         \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Pablo the Tamandua" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/Pablo2.jpg" alt="Pablo" width="216" height="118" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.judithwolfe.com" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Judith Wolfe</em> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Pablo the Lesser Anteater</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br /><strong>Zoo collection includes:</strong> Pablo, an eight year old male.<br /><br /><strong>Found in the wild:</strong> Range includes Mexico, Central America and South America in tropical rain forests, savannas and thorn scrubs. <br /><br /><strong>See him at the Central Park Zoo:</strong> Pablo can be seen in the Tropical Rain Forest in the upstairs gallery. Look up. He is usually in his tree or look down to see him sniffing on the floor of his home. <br /><br /><strong>Description:</strong> Tamanduas are solitary creatures about two to three feet in length with about a two foot length tail. They weigh from 5 to 15 pounds. Pablo has no teeth but has a 16 inch tongue as wide as a pencil. It has a sticky mucus for getting those tasty termites. He can whip out his tongue over 150 times per minute while eating.<br /><br /><strong>Zoo Tamandua Habitat:</strong> A large glass window encases Pablo''s home. He has a large tree to climb about in and plenty of room to root around the ground for things to eat. He has the company of two conures.        \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Pablo the Tamandua Eating" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/pablo3.jpg" alt="Pablo Eating" width="202" height="263" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://www.judithwolfe.com" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Judith Wolfe</em> </span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Pablo snacking upside down</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br /><strong>What do they eat:</strong>&nbsp; They mainly eat ants and termites, but they occasionally eat bees. They can eat up to 9000 termites a night. They have no teeth and depend on their powerful gizzard to break down their food. At CPZ Pablo eats a pasty gruel of pureed fruits, honey and he loves high protein wax worms.<br /><br /><strong>Life span:</strong> 8 to 12 years.<br /><br /><strong>Threats:&nbsp;</strong> Jaguars, Margay and large birds of prey.<br /><br /><strong>Fun Facts:</strong> The tamandua baby stays with mom for a year riding on her back. A smelly scent gives tamanduas the nickname "stinkers of the forest." The animal can spray a foul-smelling secretion said to be four times more powerful than a skunk''s! A tamandua''s stomach was found to contain more than one pound (0.45 kilograms) of ants. At 91 degrees Fahrenheit (33 degrees Celsius), tamanduas have one of the lowest body temperatures of any active land mammal.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align="center">\r\n<object width="320" height="265" data="http://www.youtube.com/v/d2YSkMQi6oA&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash">\r\n<param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" />\r\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" />\r\n<param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/d2YSkMQi6oA&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0" />\r\n<param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" />\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 1002. Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists. See Pablo, our Tamandua - lesser anteater.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City,  weekend, weekend activities, Tamandua, Anteater, Central Park Zoo', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'sea_lions.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Tamandua', 'Tamandua', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(393, '2009-05-19', 323, 1, 15, 'Top 10 Romantic Places In Central Park', '', 'top-10-lists/top-ten-romantic-places-in-central-park', 'Top 10 Romantic Places In Central Park', '<p><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/graphics/top10most_romantic(1).gif" border="0" alt="" hspace="3" vspace="3" width="194" height="58" align="right" />From picnics on the North Meadow to dinner for two at the Boathouse Restaurant, Central Park has always provided a wide choice of sites for a romantic rondevouz.&nbsp; Here are the the Top 10 we''ve chosen as the very best.</p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">10.  The Pool<a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0108395/" target="_blank"> </a></h2>\r\n<p>Placid waters rippling gently beneath gracefully weeping willows,<img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/pool.jpg" border="0" alt="" hspace="3" vspace="3" width="250" height="209" align="right" /> velvety lawns stretching to the water&rsquo;s edge, a quiet moment stolen from the temporally voracious metropolis outside: the Pool offers a contemplative landscape that almost aches to be shared.  A modest picnic lunch leisurely eaten on a lazy summer afternoon with only a few dragonflies for company, the Pool can provide simple pleasures in an increasingly complex city.  It is a rare location in the park that can offer even the possibility of solitude, but this mirror-surfaced pond, with its languid curves, has private space to spare.  Perfect for a tryst, away from prying eyes and intrusive ears, the Pool can be the site of intimate idylls throughout the year.</p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">9. <a href="/pages/attractions/wollman-rink.html" target="_blank"> Wollman Rink</a></h2>\r\n<p>It is cold. It is winter. It is New York.&nbsp; And if it is a clear night, it is hard to imagine a more romantic spot than Wollman Rink.  In fact, it is hard to picture Wollman Rink as anything but a romantic spot after watching the movie &ldquo;Serendipity.&rdquo;  Ice skating in Central Park is easily one of the most picturesque activities to be enjoyed on a winter&rsquo;s night.  Unlike the somewhat overwhelming confines of the Rockefeller Center rink, you can actually see stars at the Wollman rinks.  As you take your partner&rsquo;s hand, you can feel the cold tingle of New York''s crisp winter air, listen to the music, and take in the incomparable surroundings as you glide (gracefully or not so) around the rink.  A romantic huddle over hot chocolate forms the perfect coda for the evening.</p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">8. <a href="/pages/attractions/conservatory-water.html" target="_blank"> Conservatory Water </a></h2>\r\n<p>With sailboats gliding by in miniature regattas, Hans Christian Andersen reading to his friend the duckling and Alice<img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/conservatory_water.jpg" border="0" alt="" hspace="3" vspace="3" width="300" height="159" align="right" /> holding court with the Cheshire Cat, Conservatory Water offers scenic accents both romantic and literary.  Surrounded by a group of trees that survive from the original planting, the stately pond lends a sense of serenity to the urban activities being carried out a few yards away.  On the western edge, you can usually find representatives of one of New York&rsquo;s most dedicated fan clubs.  They are the birdwatchers that chronicle events in the lives of one of the Upper Eastside&rsquo;s most celebrated couples, Pale Male and Lola, a pair of red-tail hawks that nest on one of Manhattan&rsquo;s classic apartment buildings on nearby 5th Ave.  They are not the only lovebirds in the area, as the almost constant sight of couples strolling hand in hand will attest to.</p>\r\n<p><center style="page-break-after: always;"></center></p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">7. <a href="/pages/attractions/cherry-hill.html" target="_blank">Cherry Hill</a></h2>\r\n<p>Perched above the Lake, overlooking Bow Bridge and the Ramble, Cherry Hill is at the virtual center of the park, but still manages to remain relatively serene.  Like a reclusive beauty who will only reveal herself to the dedicated suitor, scenic Cherry Hill can only be appreciated by those intrepid enough to take the short walk up the winding road that leads from Park Drive at 72nd St. At the center, you''ll find a beautiful fountain designed by Jacob Wrey Mould. It features a granite pool with a black and gilt cast-iron center construct, topped by eight round lamps and a golden spire.  It is an elegant site that bespeaks a gentler, more refined era.  A place where it would not seem at all strange find a Hansom carriage parked, awaiting you and your paramour for a leisurely journey, the long way home.</p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">6. <a href="/pages/attractions/shakespeare-garden.html" target="_blank"> Shakespeare Garden</a></h2>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Away before me to sweet beds of flowers. <br />Love-thoughts lie rich when canopied with bowers.&rdquo;  <br />- <em>Count Orsino in Twelfth Night, Act I, Scene I </em><br />A fitting quote to introduce our next pick, one of Central Park&rsquo;s hidden gems: the Shakespeare Garden. Nestled between Belvedere Castle and The Swedish Cottage, the Shakespeare Garden first came into existence in 1913. Known as the Garden of the Heart, it was patterned after Victorian era rock gardens. Then, in 1916, to celebrate the tercentennial of Shakespeare''s death, it <img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/shake-garden.jpg" border="0" alt="" hspace="3" vspace="3" width="250" height="221" align="right" />was rechristened in honor of the Bard and only plants mentioned in his plays were planted there. These include columbine, primrose, wormwood, quince, lark''s heel, rue, eglantine, flax and cowslip, many of which sound as if they would be right at home boiling and bubbling in a cauldron.  It is in the spring and early summer that the garden comes into its own, bursting with blooms and fragrant blossoms.  The Shakespeare Garden also offers a variety of secluded rustic benches, perfect for the timeless art of canoodling.</p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">5. <a href="/pages/attractions/conservatory-garden.html" target="_blank"> Conservatory Garden </a></h2>\r\n<p>A tranquil oasis at the north end of the park, the Conservatory Garden offers dozens of fragrantly secluded corners and lush, leafy bowers to host an intimate tryst.  The garden is divided into three sections: the English, Italian, and French. Each offers its own unique charm to the fragrant art of floricultural seduction.  The French, or North Garden, is arranged concentrically around the Untermayer Fountain, whose pool is graced by Three Dancing Maidens, a beautiful statue executed in bronze by Walter Schott.  The Italian, or Central Garden, features a beautiful lawn leading up to a lovely fountain.  Above the fountain, there is a gorgeous wrought iron arbor that is grown over with Chinese Wisteria; it&rsquo;s a lovely place for an out of the way stroll.  The southernmost English Garden is probably the most popular of the three.  Featuring beds of seasonally blooming flowers, it is always in season and at its center is a peaceful little pool that features the statue of a boy and girl.  It is inspired by &ldquo;The Secret Garden&rdquo; by Frances Hodgson Burnett, and was sculpted by Bessie Potter Vonnoh.  The pool is covered with lily pads by mid-summer and the fragrant magnolia tree that stands nearby offers ample shade for a moment&rsquo;s respite, and, perhaps, a few whispered phrases tickling your partner&rsquo;s ear.</p>\r\n<p><center style="page-break-after: always;"></center></p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">4. <a href="/pages/attractions/loeb-boathouse.html" target="_blank">The Boathouse Restaurant</a></h2>\r\n<p>The Boathouse Restaurant looks south out over the Lake and past Bow Bridge, offering one of the most beautifully pastoral vistas in the park.  Dozens of tables all offer spectacular views of Bethesda Terrace as well, with the beautiful Angel of the Waters statue center stage on the Fountain.  Whether it&rsquo;s a balmy summer evening or a brisk fall afternoon, there is no better place to share a sunset in Central Park.  The restaurant offers more than just scenery, too.  With an accomplished and imaginative kitchen and professional floor staff, the restaurant offers a gastronomical experience to equal that of any of New York&rsquo;s finer restaurants.  Add to that the incomparable panoramic view of the heart of Central Park, and you have the perfect recipe for an evening of romantic bliss.</p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">3. <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0104431/" target="_blank"> Belvedere Castle<img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/belvedere1.jpg" border="0" alt="" hspace="3" vspace="3" width="200" height="258" align="right" /> </a></h2>\r\n<p>A storybook setting framed against the cosmopolitan skyline, Belvedere Castle offers a charming juxtaposition between urban architecture and medieval artifact.  It also provides a magically romantic backdrop for a shared moment between lovers.  Strolling along the parapets evokes images of errant knights and ladies in waiting, of a time when suitors declared their devotion by sonnet rather than cell phone.  The edifice gives visitors a scenic overlook to the Great Lawn and Turtle Pond directly beneath.  It is also just a few steps from the Delacorte Theater, which has also played host to its share of star-crossed romances. Of all the romantic spots in Central Park, it is Belvedere Castle that must be experienced by moonlight.  The glint of silvery light reflected off the mullioned windows, the pool shimmering below, all this and the myriad lights of the city beyond, how could even the most audacious suggestion be refused?</p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">2. <a href="/pages/attractions/bethesda-terrace/bethesda-fountain.html" target="_blank">Bethesda Fountain </a></h2>\r\n<p>Bethesda Fountain rises majestically above the Terrace along the south shore of the Lake.  The sculpture that tops it, Angel of the Waters, was designed by Emma Stebbins in 1873 and is one of the most recognizable icons in the entire park.  It is also one of the loveliest places to share a romantic interlude.  Couples can sit by the fountain and watch the row boats, and occasional gondola, glide by on the tranquil waters of the Lake.  Directly across to the north, you can see the Boathouse Restaurant that stretches down to the water&rsquo;s edge.  It is scene that harks back to another era, the turn of the nineteenth century.  You almost expect to see a parasol held by one of the ladies strolling by.  It is one of the magical qualities of Central Park: it not only takes you away from the confines of a loud and busy city, but it also can transport you to another time.  It is here, at Bethesda Fountain, that you can imagine your love by gaslight, waiting to accompany you to dinner at Delmonico&rsquo;s.  Bowlers optional.</p>\r\n<p><center style="page-break-after: always;"></center></p>\r\n<h2 class="top10title">1. <a href="/pages/attractions/bridges-of-central-park/bow-bridge.html" target="_blank">Bow Bridge<img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/attractions/Bow Brige.jpg" border="0" alt="" hspace="3" vspace="3" width="250" height="167" align="right" /> </a></h2>\r\n<p>Bow Bridge stretches gracefully across the Lake, connecting the carefully crafted Cherry Hill and the natural jumble of the Ramble. The bridge is one of the finest examples of the magic that resulted from the combined vision of Calvert Vaux and Jacob Wrey Mould. It is one of the most popular and best known spots to meet, and has hosted numerous tender moments, both on and off the big screen. In fact, if you edited them together, you could probably construct an entire Woody Allen feature just from the scenes filmed on Bow Bridge (and despite rumors to the contrary, the bridge has always been very easy to work with and has nothing but admiration and respect for the celebrated director.)  It is the romantic heart of the park, stretching across the Lake and framing one of the most iconic views in New York, that of the Dakota Apartments and the west side of Manhattan.  Countless proposals have been made on the bridge, as well as hearts poured forth and troths plighted. It is, especially at sunset, the most romantic spot in Central Park.</p>', 'CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 1002. Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, NYC, New York City, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, Bow Bridge, Romance, tours, walking tours, Wollman Rink, romantic places, dates, ', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'columbus_circle.jpg', '<a href="http://www.luminous-newyork.com">Joergen Geerds</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Top 10 Romantic Places In Central Park', 'Top 10 Romantic Places In Central Park', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
