(420, '2012-06-08', 87, 1, 7, 'Rock Cavy', '', 'central-park-zoo/rock-cavy', 'Rock Cavy in Central Park', '<p><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Rock Cavy</strong></span> ( Kerodon rupestris)      \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Rock Cavy" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/CAVY.jpg" alt="Rock Cavy" width="216" height="321" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a href="http://judithwolfe.com/" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>Judithwolfe.com</em></span></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br /><strong>Zoo collection includes: </strong>Two - Cavies are relatives of the domestic Guinea pig<br /><br /><strong>Found in the wild:</strong> Eastern Brazil in dry rocky areas near stony mountains and hills<br /><br /><strong>See Them at the Central Park Zoo:</strong> They can be viewed upstairs in the Tropic Zone in the habitat with the Tamandua.<br /><br /><strong>Description:</strong> Small rodent that resembles the rock hyrax with a face that looks like a squirrel. They have heavily padded feet, are quite agile, and are exceptional climbers. Coat is gray, grizzled with white and black. Throat is white and the belly is yellowish-white. The rump and backs of thighs are reddish. There is no tail and both sexes look similar.<br /><br /><strong>What do they eat:</strong>&nbsp; Leaves, grasses, seeds<br /><br /><strong>Life span:</strong> Four years<br /><br /><strong>Threats:</strong> Least concerned<br /><br /><strong>Fun Facts:</strong> Rock cavies make a variety of vocalizations, including an alarm whistle, chirps, and squeaks.<br />These rodents are related to domestic guinea pigs. One or two young. Several litters per year are common. They live in small family groups.&nbsp; They have nails growing out of their skin with a single grooming claw on the inside hind toes.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 1002. Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Bethesda Terrace, Bow Bridge, Central Park Maps, Great Lawn, reservoir, running track, Sheep Meadow, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tours, walking tours, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Rock Cavy', 'Rock Cavy', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(421, '2012-06-08', 10, 1, 15, 'Parking', '', 'general-info/parking', 'Parking in and around Central Park', '<p>If travelling to Central Park by car, there are numerous parking garages available in the area. These and other garages can be found nearly every other street in the Central Park area.  Companies such as Central Parking and Wilson Parking charge by the hour, and their rates increase or decrease depending on the location of the parking structure.  Some of these locations include:</p>\r\n<ul class="bullet">\r\n<li>115 E 87th St</li>\r\n<li>Time Warner Center (10 Columbus Circle)</li>\r\n<li>58 W 58th St</li>\r\n<li>201 W 56th St</li>\r\n<li>Met Tower (146 W 56th St)</li>\r\n<li>Carnegie House (101 W 56th St)</li>\r\n<li>152-158 St Georges Terrace</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>It may be best to check the <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nysdot.gov/index">New York Department of Transportation website</a> for further information when planning your trip.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0 0 20px; text-align: right;"><small>&mdash; Jesse M. Wheeler </small></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'Numerous parking garages can be found nearly every other street in the Central Park area.', 'parking, central park parking, wilson parking, central parking, garages, parking near central park', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'bethesda.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Parking', 'Parking', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(422, '2009-11-11', 145, 2, 14, 'Josh Koerpel', '', 'about-centralpark-com/staff/josh-koerpel', 'Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<p><img style="margin: 5px; float: right;" title="Josh Koerpel" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/DSC03583.JPG" alt="" width="180" height="247" /></p>\r\n<p>Josh Koerpel is the content director for CentralPark.com. &nbsp;His writing talents sprang from an unlikely set of circumstances.&nbsp; Upon graduating from Denison University in 2003 with a degree in Spanish, he spent the next 5 years crewing aboard tall ships and sailing the world''s oceans.&nbsp; His writing evolved and improved through the record of his experiences in travel journals, and after an accident he and fellow crewmates experienced off the coast of France in 2005, he wrote an article published in SailJazz magazine (US) and ClassicBoat magazine (UK) recounting the event.&nbsp; After returning and receiving his captains license, he moved to New York and spent his days writing and working on the water.&nbsp; Yearning to combine his writing with his other passion, motorcycle travel, he and his wife recently embarked on a 3 month journey to explore northern India on an old british motorcycle. <br />An avid outdoorsman, Josh enjoys the escape and solitude that Central Park provides, and also regards it as an important part of environmental education.&nbsp; He is very excited to be on the CentralPark.com team and vows to do everything electronically possible to provide you with all the wonders of the park at a clicks notice.</p>', 'Josh Koerpel. CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 10021. Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'rock climbing, Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, ice skating, Bow Bridge, Central Park Maps, Great Lawn, reservoir, running track, Sheep Meadow, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tours, walking tours, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'mall.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Josh Koerpel', 'Josh Koerpel', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
