(430, '2010-03-31', 145, 2, 14, 'Jillian Ryan', '', 'about-centralpark-com/staff/jillian-ryan', 'Jillian Ryan - CentralPark.com Staff', '<p><img style="float: right; margin: 6px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/jillian_ryan_adelphi.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="293" />Jillian Ryan, a Brooklyn girl born and raised, is the content director for CentralPark.com. &nbsp; From an early age, she always knew that she had a passion for words and writing and along with this love, she grew eager to see everything the world had to offer.&nbsp; An avid traveler since her youth, Jillian is also a freelance travel writer and who has traveled far and wide for her stories.&nbsp; During her college career at Adelphi University, Jillian studied English Literature and Communications and spent time abroad studying the Italian language and culture in Florence, Italy.&nbsp; She also managed to squeeze in trips to Germany, Ireland and many island destinations while on the road to adulthood.&nbsp; Upon graduation, Jillian landed her gig has a freelance travel writer by chance and she is absolutely in love with it.&nbsp; Since starting, she has spent most of her time exploring tropical localities: Playa del Carmen and San Jose del Cabo in Mexico, St. Lucia, Turks &amp; Caicos, Aruba, Jamaica, St. Kitts and Curacao to name a few.&nbsp; Jillian has also been fortunate to discover many of the great cities in North America such as Toronto, Phoenix, Dallas, Philadelphia, Orlando, San Francisco, Washington D.C. and many others in between.</p>\r\n<p>However, no matter how far Jillian travels or what she gets to see during her journeys, she never forgets her roots: New York City, the most excellent place in the world that she is privileged enough to live and work in.&nbsp; And in the center of the hustle and bustle of her home sweet home is Central Park, a place that Jillian just recently started to explore.&nbsp; She loves walking through and past the park on a nice spring or fall day, especially when the Breast Cancer Walk, which she tries to do annually with her college girlfriends, marches through.&nbsp; A literature geek through and through, Jillian has attended intellectually stimulating book fairs in the park and is really hoping that her new gig as this site''s content director will help her finally score tickets to see Shakespeare in the Park!&nbsp; Also a recent bike riding enthusiast, Jillian plans to spend many warm Saturday and Sunday afternoons cycling through the trails of Central Park so she can discover new and exciting content for the site''s readers.</p>\r\n<p>Keep up with Jillian; follow her and all of her writing on <a href="http://twitter.com/Writing_Jillian">Twitter</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 10021. Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, ice skating, easter, easter egg hunt, weddings, concerts, concert, aa-map, family-map, aa-podcast, family-podcast, Bow Bridge, Central Park Maps, Great Lawn, reservoir, running track, Sheep Meadow, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tours, walking tours, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'lake800.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Jillian Ryan', 'Jillian Ryan', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(431, '2013-08-16', 10, 1, 7, 'Restrooms', '', 'general-info/restrooms', 'Restrooms in Central Park', '<p>There are 16 public restrooms located throughout Central Park at various attractions, landmarks and playgrounds.&nbsp; Please note that some are seasonal and not open during the winter; just less than half are wheelchair accessible.                \r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/usr/maps/CentralParkRunningMap.pdf"><img src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/runners_map_thumb.jpg" border="0" alt="CentralPark.com Runner''s Map" hspace="5" vspace="5" width="188" height="230" align="right" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Central Park Running Map<br /> with Bathroom Locations.<br /></strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><strong>Merchants'' Gate</strong>, 61st Street and Central Park West (closed during the winter)</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/heckscher-playground.html"><strong>Heckscher Playground</strong></a>, Mid-park at 62nd Street</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/arsenal.html"><strong>The Arsenal</strong></a>, 64th Street and 5th Avenue</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/sheep-meadow.html"><strong>Sheep Meadow Cafe at Mineral Springs</strong></a>, Mid-Park at 69th Street (wheelchair accessible, closed during the winter)</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/bethesda-terrace.html"><strong>Bethesda Terrace</strong></a>, Mid-park at 72nd Street (closed during the winter)</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/sports/model-sailboats.html"><strong>Model Boathouse (Kerbs) Cafe</strong></a>, at Conservatory Water at 74th Street (wheelchair accessible)</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/loeb-boathouse.html"><strong>Loeb Boathouse</strong></a>, 74th Street at the East Drive (wheelchair accessible)</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/ramble.html"><strong>Ramble Shed</strong></a>, Mid-park at 79th Street&gt;</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/delacorte-theatre.html"><strong>Delacorte Theatre</strong></a>, at the Turtle Pond at 81st Street (wheelchair accessible)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ancient Playground</strong>, 85th Street and 5th Avenue</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/tennis-center.html"><strong>Tennis House</strong></a>, Mid-park at 94th Street</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/activities/north-meadow-center.html"><strong>North Meadow Recreation Center</strong></a>, Mid-park at 97th Street (wheelchair accessible)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Robert Bendheim Playground</strong>, 100th Street and 5th Avenue (wheelchair accessible)</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/conservatory-garden.html"><strong>Conservatory Garden</strong></a>, 105th Street and 5th Avenue (wheelchair accessible)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Great Hill</strong>, West 106th Street (closed during the winter)</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/discovery-center.html">Dana Discovery Center</a></strong>, 110th Street at Lenox Avenue</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To see these restrooms on a map, download our <a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/maps/runner-s-map.html">Runner''s Map</a> which has each of these locations clearly marked.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'There are 16 public restrooms located throughout Central Park at various attractions, landmarks and playgrounds. ', 'Central Park, Central Park Bathrooms, Central Park Restrooms, Public Restrooms, Public Bathrooms, Central Park Toilets, Public Toilets', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Restrooms', 'Restrooms', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
