(433, '2010-05-19', 10, 1, 0, 'Discussion Boards', '', 'general-info/discussionboards', 'Discussion Boards | Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<div class="content">\r\n<p>For Central Park-lovers that want to meet like-minded individuals  who share their passion for the park, visit the new <a href="http://www.wecaregreen.com/forumdisplay.php?f=37" target="_blank">CentralPark.com  Discussion Boards</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have fun sharing your thoughts and opinions on Central Park by creating a dialogue with fellow users.&nbsp; Topics  include ways to make the park greener, advice and experiences.&nbsp; But if  you don''t see a conversation you like, you can create your own!</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>\r\n</div>', 'For Central Park-lovers that want to meet like-minded individuals who share their passion for the park, visit the new CentralPark.com Discussion Boards. Have fun sharing your thoughts and opinions.', 'Central Park, Central Park Forum, NYC, New York City, Central Park Discussion Boards, Community Central Park, Discussion Boards Central Park', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'default.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/aric-boyles.html">Aric Boyles</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Discussion Boards', 'Discussion Boards', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(434, '2015-06-11', 90, 2, 15, 'New York Philharmonic', '', 'activities/concerts/new-york-philharmonic', 'New York Philharmonic Concerts in Central Park', '<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p><img style="margin: 6px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/phil.jpg" alt="NY Philharmonic" width="200" height="150" /></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>www.nyphil.org</em> </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span>For those that appreciate an evening of classical music under a night of summer stars, the New York Philharmonic will once again present its annual Concerts in the Parks series on the Great Lawn in Central Park.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>2015 Concert Dates:<br /></strong><strong>Wednesday June 17, 2015</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Alan Gilbert</strong><span>&nbsp;</span><span>conducts Bernstein''s</span><span>&nbsp;</span><em>West Side Story</em><span>&nbsp;</span><span>Suite, featuring violinist</span><span>&nbsp;</span><strong>Joshua Bell</strong><span>, alongside works by Barber, Gershwin, Copland, Anderson, Rodgers, and Sousa. FREE</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Thursday&nbsp;June 18, 2015</strong></p>\r\n<p><span><strong>Charles Dutoit</strong><span>&nbsp;</span><span>leads the Orchestra in Berlioz''s</span><span>&nbsp;</span><em>Roman Carnival Overture</em><span>; Saint-Sa&euml;ns''s Violin Concerto No. 3, with</span><span>&nbsp;</span><strong>Renaud Capu&ccedil;on</strong><span>&nbsp;</span><span>as soloist; Stravinsky''s</span><span>&nbsp;</span><em>Petrushka</em><span>&nbsp;</span><span>(1911 version); and Ravel''s</span><span>&nbsp;</span><em>La Valse</em><span>. FREE</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span>Location Info:</span></p>\r\n<p>Concerts take place on the Great Lawn:</p>\r\n<p>Enter on the Westside at&nbsp;West 81st or 86th Streets at Central Park West. Enter on the Eastside at&nbsp;East 79th or 85th Streets at Fifth Ave.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Details</strong></p>\r\n<p>All shows will be followed by fireworks by Bay Fireworks.</p>\r\n<p>Bring a blanket, a picnic and some friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the best seats, try to arrive a couple of hours before the start of the show.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo credit:&nbsp;<a title="new york philharmonic central park" href="http://www.nyphil.org/" target="_blank">NYPhil.org</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'For those that appreciate an evening of classical music under a night of summer stars, The New York Philharmonic presents its annual Concerts in the Parks series. ', 'Central Park, Central Park Concert, Free Concert, Music Concert, Classical Music, New York Philharmonic, New York Philharmonic Concert, Outdoor Concert, Summer Concert, philharmonic in central park, new york philharmonic central park', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.luminous-newyork.com">Joergen Geerds</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'New York Philharmonic', 'New York Philharmonic', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(435, '2015-05-18', 90, 2, 15, 'Naumburg Orchestral Concerts', '', 'activities/concerts/naumburg-orchestra', 'Naumburg Orchestral Concerts in Central Park', '<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p><img style="margin: 6px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/naumburg.jpg" alt="Naumburg Bandshell" width="175" height="263" /></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>www.naumburgconcerts.org</em> </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Since 1905, the Naumburg Orchestral Concerts has presented free, outdoor classical music concerts to New Yorkers and visitors eager to experience an evening of musical enrichment.</p>\r\n<p>Named after Elkan Naumburg, who donated the <a title="naumburg bandshell" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/bandshell.html">Naumburg Bandshell</a> to New York City in 1923, the series seeks to stimulate and encourage new audiences for classical music in the serene setting of Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>It''s the oldest concert series of its kind in the entire United States and currently features some promising new talent&nbsp;of young composers and conductors&nbsp;that it hopes to promote and develop.</p>\r\n<p><strong>See the schedule below:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;"><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>The 2015 Schedule of Naumburg Orchestral Concerts<br /></strong>Concerts take place on Tuesdays. All concerts are at 7:30 PM.</p>\r\n<p>The Knights<br />Tuesday, June 23, 2015; 7:30 PM-10:30 PM</p>\r\n<p>Ensemble le Poisson Rouge<br />Tuesday, June 30, 2015; 7:30 PM-10:30 PM</p>\r\n<p>Boston Symphony Chamber Players<br />Tuesday, July 14, 2015; 7:30 PM-10:30 PM</p>\r\n<p>Orpheus Chamber Orchestra<br />Tuesday, July 21, 2015; 7:30 PM-10:30 PM</p>\r\n<p>ECCO, East Coast Chamber Orchestra<br />Tuesday, August 4, 2015; 7:30 PM-10:30 PM</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Since 1905, Naumburg Orchestral Concerts has presented free, outdoor classical music concerts in Central Park. See more details and the schedule of events.', 'Central Park, Central Park Concert, Free Concert, New York City Concert, Summer Concert, Classical Music, Naumburg Orchestra, Naumburg Bandshell, bandshell concerts, naumburg orchestral concerts, free summer concerts central park, free concert central park, naumburg concerts central park, naumburg orchestra central park, free concerts central park bandshell, central park bandshell, central park naumburg orchestra', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.luminous-newyork.com">Joergen Geerds</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Naumburg Orchestra', 'Naumburg Orchestra', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(436, '2015-06-11', 90, 2, 15, 'The Metropolitan Opera', '', 'activities/concerts/metropolitan-opera', 'The Metropolitan Opera Summer Recitals in Central Park', '<table border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p><img style="margin: 6px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/MET_opera.jpg" alt="The Met Opera." width="246" height="164" /></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>metopera.org</em> </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>In hopes to inspire a new generation of opera lovers, The Metropolitan Opera launched its Summer Recital Series in 2009 in collaboration with City Parks Foundation, to bring free concerts to the parks in every borough of New York.</p>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;series is one of the most beloved summer traditions in the city,&nbsp;and it kicks off in Central Park''s Rumsey Playfield.</p>\r\n<p>See this year''s schedule below:</p>\r\n<div><span><br /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;"><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>2015 Metropolitan Opera Summer Schedule:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><span><strong>Monday, June 15, 2015,&nbsp;8pm</strong><br /></span><span><strong>Central Park SummerStage</strong></span><br />Janai Brugger, soprano<br />Isabel Leonard, mezzo-soprano<br />Nathan Gunn, baritone<br />Dan Saunders, pianist</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span><strong>Wednesday, June 17,&nbsp;2015, 7pm</strong><br /></span><span><strong>Brooklyn Bridge Park, Pier 1, Brooklyn</strong></span><br />Janai Brugger, soprano<br />Isabel Leonard, mezzo-soprano<br />Nathan Gunn, baritone<br />Dan Saunders, pianist</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span><strong>Wednesday, June 24, 2015, 7pm</strong></span><a title="Socrates Sculpture Park" href="http://socratessculpturepark.org/program/metopera/" target="_blank"><span><br /></span></a><span><strong>Socrates Sculpture Park, Queens</strong></span><br />Kiri Deonarine, soprano<br />Ginger Costa-Jackson, mezzo-soprano<br />John Moore, baritone<br />Dan Saunders, pianist</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span>Friday, June 26, 2015, 7pm<br /></span><span>Jackie Robinson Park, Manhattan</span></strong><br />Kiri Deonarine, soprano<br />Ginger Costa-Jackson, mezzo-soprano<br />John Moore, baritone<br />Dan Saunders, pianist</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span>Sunday, June 28, 2015, 7pm<br /></span><span>Crotona Park, Bronx</span><span>&nbsp;</span></strong><br />Kiri Deonarine, soprano<br />Ginger Costa-Jackson, mezzo-soprano<br />John Moore, baritone<br />Dan Saunders, pianist</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span>Tuesday, June 30, 2015, 7pm<br /></span><span>Clove Lakes Park, Staten Island</span></strong><br />Kiri Deonarine, soprano<br />Ginger Costa-Jackson, mezzo-soprano<br />John Moore, baritone<br />Dan Saunders, pianist</p>\r\n<p>More info <a title="metopera " href="http://www.metoperafamily.org/metopera/season/summer-recitals" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>', 'In 2009, in hopes to inspire a new generation of opera lovers, The Metropolitan Opera launched its Summer Recital Series and presented free concerts in Central Park.', 'Central Park, Central Park Concert, Opera Concert, Metropolitan Opera, Outdoor Concert, New York City Concert, Free Concert, Summer Concert, Summer Recital', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.luminous-newyork.com">Joergen Geerds</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'The Metropolitan Opera', 'The Metropolitan Opera', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(437, '2015-07-01', 90, 2, 15, 'Harlem Meer Festival', '', 'activities/concerts/harlem-meer', 'Harlem Meer Performance Festival in Central Park', '<p>For an international and cultural experience spanning the globe right here in Central Park, check out the Harlem Meer Performance Festival.</p>\r\n<p>Held at the Dana Discovery Center at the Harlem Meer, the festival occurs during the summer months and features a different type of international musical and/or dance performance every Sunday.</p>\r\n<p>See the schedule of performances below:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;"><br /></span></p>\r\n<h3>2015 Harlem Meer Performance Festival Schedule</h3>\r\n<p>Performances take place from June 21 - September 6 at 2:00 PM.</p>\r\n<p><span>June 21: Frankie Morales &amp; His Mambo of the Times Orquestra&nbsp;<em>(Salsa/Mambo)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>June 28: Elle Winston&nbsp;<em>(Americana/Blues)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>July 5: Los Soneros de Oriente&nbsp;<em>(Cuban S&oacute;n)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>July 12: &iexcl;Retumba!&nbsp;<em>(Afro-Caribbean Music and Dance)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>July 19: Sean Smith Quartet&nbsp;<em>(Jazz)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>July 26: La Orquesta Jeryco<em>&nbsp;(Salsa)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>August 2: Famoro Diobate &amp; Kakande<em>&nbsp;(</em><em>West African Music)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>August 9: Harlem Blues &amp; Jazz Band&nbsp;<em>(Jump Blues/Jazz)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>August 16: Quimbomb&oacute;<em>&nbsp;(</em><em>Cuban S</em><em>&oacute;n)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>August 23: Ebony Hillbillies&nbsp;<em>(Bluegrass/Appalachian)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>August 30:&nbsp;</span><span>Garifuna International&nbsp;<em>(</em><em>Music and Dance of the African Peoples of Central America)</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span>September 6: Dee Dee LeVant Gospel Ensemble&nbsp;<em>(Gospel)</em></span></p>', 'For an international and cultural experience spanning the globe right in Central Park, check out the Harlem Meer Performance Festival in Central Park. ', 'Central Park, Central Park Concerts, SummerStage, New York City Concerts, Free Concerts, Harlem Meer, Harlem Meer Concert, Harlem Meer Festival, Harlem Meer Performance Festival', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'meadow.jpg', '<a href="http://www.luminous-newyork.com">Joergen Geerds</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Harlem Meer Festival', 'Harlem Meer Festival', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(438, '2013-08-19', 16, 1, 15, 'Squitch The Squirrel', '', 'funstuff/squitch', 'Squitch The Squirrel | Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<p><strong>Squitch, the Squirrel of New York&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><br />In New York City''s Central Park<br />Lived a squirrel known as Squitch,<br />And when tourists stopped to watch him romp<br />He knew he''d struck it rich. <br />He would entertain them with his tail;<br />He would shimmy, shake, and swish,<br />And as cameras clicked on every move<br />He would close his eyes and wish.<br /><img style="margin: 6px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/sqitch1.jpg" alt="Squitch" width="260" height="209" /></p>\r\n<p>Yes, he hoped for peanuts, crumbs, and such,<br />That was every squirrel''s game;<br />But in some ways Squitch was quite unique:<br />What he wanted most was fame. <br />He was New York savvy and he knew<br />That with each delightful antic,<br /> He was captured by a camera''s lens,<br />But his goal was most gigantic.<br /> He was not content to remain unknown;,<br />He had big plans to uncork.</p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><img style="margin: 6px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/squitch22.jpg" alt="Squitch" width="260" height="237" /></p>\r\n<p>Someday everyone would know his name:<br />Squitch, the Squirrel of New York!<br />He''d be famous throughout all the world;<br />They''d arrive from far and near.<br />Crowds would come to Central Park and wait,<br />Hoping that Squitch would appear. <br />And he''d never, ever let them down;<br />He''d cavort and run and pounce,<br />And if other squirrels interfered<br />They''d soon realize they''d be trounced. <br />He would see his name in lights one day,<br />He''d appear on late-night shows.</p>\r\n<p><br /><img style="margin: 6px;" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/squitch3.jpg" alt="Squitch" width="260" height="231" /></p>\r\n<p>There would be a statue showing Squitch<br />In a most distinguished pose. <br />And one lucky day, Squitch''s wish came true,<br />Well, not every single part;<br />But he did enough to impress someone<br />Who took all his hopes to heart. <br />And she wrote a poem about his life<br />So that people would find out<br />That in New York Squitch the Squirrel lives<br />And he''s waiting there, no doubt. <br />So go look around, when you''re in New York;<br />Visit Central Park and wait,<br />And I''m sure you''ll notice Squitch at once<br />And I don''t exaggerate. <br />He will mug and charm and delight your heart,<br />He''ll grab any food you scatter;<br />And if you''re not sure if it''s really Squitch -<br />Does it really even matter? <br />For each squirrel''s here just to entertain<br />With a New York flair and style;<br />But when you go home, don''t forget to swear<br />You saw Squitch - and then, just smile.....&nbsp;â€¨ <br /><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ilene Bauer<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;April 23, 2009</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'CentralPark.com -  Your first stop for information on Central Park, New York City and The Central Park Zoo, 830 5th Ave. New York, NY 10021. Including extensive event listings, maps, attractions, sports, activities, history, essential info for tourists.', 'Central Park, Central Park Zoo, NYC, New York City, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, ice skating, easter, easter egg hunt, weddings, concerts, concert, aa-map, family-map, aa-podcast, family-podcast, Bow Bridge, Central Park Maps, Great Lawn, reservoir, running track, Sheep Meadow, Strawberry Fields, Tavern on the Green, tours, walking tours, Wollman Rink', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'sea_lion.jpg', '<a href="http://www.maryschwalm.com" target="_new">Mary Schwalm</a>', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Squitch The Squirrel', 'Squitch The Squirrel', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(439, '2014-06-09', 3, 1, 15, 'Picnics', '', 'activities/picnics', 'Central Park Picnics', '<table style="margin: 10px 0 5px 5px; " border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Picnic in central park" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/picnic-west-side.jpg"></a> <img title="Picnic in central park" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/picnic-west-side.jpg" alt="Picnic in central park" width="200" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a title="View  stella0619''s profile" href="http://www.centralpark.com/members/profile30001.html">stella0619</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>A Picnic in Central Park.</strong> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Having a picnic in Central Park is a great way to enjoy time with friends, soak in some nature, or just relax with a bite to eat after a long day of walking around.</p>\r\n<p>Pack some food, grab a blanket and head to a spot like the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/great-lawn.html">Great Lawn</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/sheep-meadow.html">Sheep Meadow</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/bridges-of-central-park/bow-bridge.html">Bow Bridge</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/conservatory-garden.html">Conservatory Garden</a>, or&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/attractions/strawberry-fields.html">Strawberry Fields</a>.</p>\r\n<p>You can find descriptions for these and a couple more locations on our list of the&nbsp;<a title="7 best picnic spots in central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/activities/picnics/top-7-picnic-spots.html">7 Best Picnic Spots in Central Park</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;"><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></span></p>\r\n<table style="margin: 10px 0 5px 5px; background: #fff;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><a title="Bow Bridge Picnic" rel="lightbox-guide" href="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/Bow_Bridge_Central_Park_Top_Picnic_Spot.jpg"> <img title="Bow Bridge Picnic" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/Bow_Bridge_Central_Park_Top_Picnic_Spot.jpg" alt="Bow Bridge Picnic" width="200" /> </a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><a title="Picnic Central Park" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.centralparkpicnic.com/best-areas-central-park/cherry-hill-bow-bridge-mid-park-72nd" target="_blank">Picnic Central Park</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<p align="left"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong>Bow Bridge Picnic.</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Need to plan an event around a picnic? You can&nbsp;<a title="contact us central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/contact">contact us</a> for help with putting together your custom event, or you could also check with  the <a href="http://www.nycgovparks.org/sub_permits_and_applications/events_faq.html" target="_blank">NYC Department of Parks and Recreation</a>&nbsp;to obtain a permit and plan your own big picnic.</p>\r\n<p>Please note that groups of more than 20 people will require a special permit that must be  obtained in advance. In addition, other factors such as planned  activities, location, the use of tables and chairs, etc. will affect whether a permit is needed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>(Note: Barbecuing is not permitted in Central Park).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Picnicking in Central Park is free and fun to do. Pack a blanket and some food and choose from one of the many beautiful spots throughout the park to spread out and enjoy. ', 'Central Park, central park picnic, picnic basket, picnic blanket, great lawn picnic, picnic in central park', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'great_lawn_rick.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 40, '', '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Picnics', 'Picnics', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
