(445, '2015-07-29', 442, 1, 7, 'Bike Rentals', '', 'tours/bike-rentals', 'Central Park Bike Rentals', '<div id="toursWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="bikeRental title">Bike Rentals</h1>\r\n<p><strong> Rent a bike and tour Central Park on your own!</strong></p>\r\n<p>Our Central Park bike rentals start at just $15 and include a helmet, basket, lock and map at no extra charge. We have over 400 bikes for men, women and kids as well as tandem bike rentals, baby seats and baby trailers.</p>\r\n<script src="https://fareharbor.com/embeds/script/calendar-small/smyrnatours/items/1257,1744/?lightframe=yes&amp;asn=centralpark"></script>\r\n<p><strong>Bike pickup</strong> is located at 208 W. 80th Street, New York, NY 10024</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy the scenery with a Central Park bike rental as you pedal along comfortably at your own pace. You can stop along the way to explore the many <a title="central park attractions" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions.html">attractions</a> such as <a title="belvedere castle" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/belvedere-castle.html">Belvedere Castle</a>, <a title="strawberry fields" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/strawberry-fields.html">Strawberry Fields</a>, <a title="alice in wonderland" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/alice-in-wonderland.html">Alice in Wonderland</a>, <a title="bethesda terrace" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/bethesda-terrace.html">Bethesda Terrace</a>, the <a title="balto statue central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/balto.html">Balto Statue</a>, <a title="central park lake" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/lake.html">the Lake</a>, the <a title="conservatory gardens" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/conservatory-garden.html">Conservatory Gardens</a>, the 36 <a title="central park bridges" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/bridges-of-central-park.html">bridges and arches</a> located throughout the park and many others. With 843 acres in Central Park, there is no shortage of things to do and see with your bike rental.</p>\r\n<p>You may also wish to consider one of our <a title="guided bike tours central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike.html">guided bike tours</a> to hear about Central Park from a licensed expert.</p>\r\n<p>Our store is open from 10am to 7pm (8am to 8pm in summer) for bike rentals and returns. Delivery is also available anywhere between 42nd street and 72nd street (minimums may apply). We have over 400 bikes for your bike rental ranging in styles and sizes from 14" kids bikes to 26" adult bikes, leisure bikes, comfort bikes, road bikes, mountain bikes, and we also carry tandem bikes, baby seats and baby trailers.</p>\r\n<div><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>CANCELLATION POLICY</h3>\r\n<p>If any scheduled bike rentals are canceled due to bad weather conditions, you may choose to postpone the day service is given or request a full refund.</p>\r\n<p><strong>24 hours prior cancellation</strong>: You may choose to postpone the day service is given or request a full refund.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Same day cancellation</strong>: You may choose to postpone the day service is given or request a refund with a 50% cancellation penalty.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Last hour cancellation:</strong> If you need to cancel your tour within the last hour, no refund or postpone will be provided.</p>\r\n<p>If you would like cancel or make changes to your reservation, please call +1&nbsp;(917) 993-3141&nbsp;or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:tours@centralpark.com">tours@centralpark.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'Renting a bicycle is a fun and affordable way to explore Central Park. Helmet, basket, lock and map included at no charge! We have over 400 bike for men, women and kids, as well as tandem bikes, baby seats, and baby trailers.', 'bicycle rental, rent a bike in central park, bike tour, central park bicycle tour, self guided central park tour, bike tour of central park, tandem bicycle, tandem bike rental, baby seat, baby trailer, multi-lingual tours, bilingual tours, tours in spanish, tours in portuguese, tours in german, tours in dutch, tours in russian, tours in italian, tours in turkish, tandem bikes, baby seats, baby trailers', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'bethesda.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 3, '/usr/media/tours.v2/tours.css', '/usr/media/tours.v2/tours.js', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Bike Rentals', 'Bike Rentals', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(446, '2014-09-23', 442, 1, 7, 'Pedicab Tours', '', 'tours/pedicab', 'Central Park Pedicab Tours', '<div id="toursWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="pedicabTour title">Pedicab Tours</h1>\r\n<div id="toursWrapper"><strong> Sit back and relax as your knowledgeable driver guides you through Central Park.</strong></div>\r\n<p>If biking sounds too strenous, a pedicab tour with a Central Park expert is a great way to see the sights without doing a lot of work. Visit many well-known attractions and famous landmarks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<script src="https://fareharbor.com/embeds/script/calendar-small/smyrnatours/items/1294/?lightframe=yes&amp;asn=centralpark"></script>\r\n<br /> <br /> {{ADSPACE_300_250}}<br />\r\n<h3 id="t1">1-HOUR TOUR</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>The 1-hour tour covers 1/4 of the park and includes the following:</strong></p>\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Balto</li>\r\n<li>Bandshell</li>\r\n<li>Bethesda Terrace</li>\r\n<li>Bethesda Fountain</li>\r\n<li>Carousel</li>\r\n<li>Cherry Hill</li>\r\n<li>Children''s Zoo</li>\r\n<li>Dairy</li>\r\n<li>Dakota</li>\r\n<li>Essex House</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Grand Army Plaza</li>\r\n<li>Heckscher Playground</li>\r\n<li>The Lake</li>\r\n<li>The Mall</li>\r\n<li>Sheep Meadow</li>\r\n<li>Strawberry Fields</li>\r\n<li>SummerStage</li>\r\n<li>Tavern on the Green</li>\r\n<li>Victorian Gardens</li>\r\n<li>Wollman Rink</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class="sep">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 id="t2">2-HOUR TOUR</h3>\r\n<p><strong>The 2-hour tour covers 2/3 of the park and includes everything from the 1-hour tour, plus:</strong></p>\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Belvedere Castle</li>\r\n<li>Conservatory Garden</li>\r\n<li>Conservatory Water</li>\r\n<li>Delacorte Music Clock</li>\r\n<li>Delacorte Theater</li>\r\n<li>Gapstow Bridge</li>\r\n<li>Greyshot Arch</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Heckscher Ballfields</li>\r\n<li>Loeb Boathouse</li>\r\n<li>Reservoir</li>\r\n<li>Shakespeare Garden</li>\r\n<li>Swedish Cottage</li>\r\n<li>Turtle Pond</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class="sep">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 id="t3">3-HOUR TOUR</h3>\r\n<p><strong>The 3-hour tour covers all major attractions and includes everything from the 2-hour tour, plus:</strong></p>\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Alice in Wonderland</li>\r\n<li>Great Lawn</li>\r\n<li>Hans Christian Andersen</li>\r\n<li>Harlem Meer</li>\r\n<li>Lasker Pool &amp; Rink</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Majestic Towers</li>\r\n<li>North Meadow</li>\r\n<li>Obelisk</li>\r\n<li>Tennis Center</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class="sep">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 id="t4">4-HOUR TOUR</h3>\r\n<p><strong>The 4-hour tour covers all major attractions and includes everything from the 3-hour tour, plus a tour of museums and city landmarks:</strong></p>\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Museum Mile</li>\r\n<li>Metropolitan Museum of Art</li>\r\n<li>Solomon R. Guggenheim</li>\r\n<li>Museum of Natural History</li>\r\n<li>Frick Collection</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lincoln Center</li>\r\n<li>5th Avenue</li>\r\n<li>Rockefeller Center</li>\r\n<li>Times Square</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class="sep">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class="sep" style="text-align: left;"><br /><strong>\r\n<h3>CANCELLATION POLICY</h3>\r\n</strong>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If any scheduled bike tours, rentals or pedicab tours are canceled due to bad weather conditions, you may choose to postpone the day service is given or request a full refund.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>24 hours prior cancellation</strong>: You may choose to postpone the day service is given or request a full refund.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Same day cancellation</strong>: You may choose to postpone the day service is given or request a refund with a 50% cancellation penalty.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Last hour cancellation:</strong>&nbsp;If you need to cancel your tour within the last hour, no refund or postpone will be provided.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you would like cancel or make changes to your&nbsp;reservation, please call&nbsp;<span>+1 (347) 871-4499</span>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Try a pedicab tour - it''s a great way to see Central Park without doing a lot of work.', 'pedicab tour, central park pedicab tour, pedicab, multi-lingual tours, bilingual tours, tours in spanish, tours in portuguese, tours in german, tours in dutch, tours in russian, tours in italian, tours in turkish', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', 'bethesda.jpg', '<a href="http://www.centralpark.com/pages/about-centralpark-com/staff/rick-anderson.html">Rick Anderson</a>', '', '', 5, '/usr/media/tours.v2/tours.css', '/usr/media/tours.v2/tours.js', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Pedicab Tours', 'Pedicab Tours', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
