(506, '2013-08-16', 271, 1, 15, 'Top 10 Places to Stay Around Central Park', '', 'hotels/top-10-places-to-stay', 'Top 10 Places to Stay Around Central Park | Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<p>If you''re traveling to New York and would like to explore Central Park, there''s no shortage of hotels in the area. From modest and comfortable to spacious and luxurious, the Central Park area has it all.</p>\r\n<p>While this list certainly doesn''t include every hotel in the area, here are 10 of the most popular places to stay near Central Park:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>1. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/the-plaza.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">The Plaza Hotel</a>:</strong> Located on 5th Ave. at the southeast corner of Central Park, The Plaza Hotel is one of New York&rsquo;s most legendary buildings. The hotel opened in 1907 and has played host to some of the most famous people in the world. It recently underwent a renovation, and many of its rooms were refurbished into condos. However, the hotel still has 282 guestrooms, including 102 suites, which are all just steps away from the main entrance to Central Park.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>2. <a title="Park Central Hotel" href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/park-central.en.html?aid=334464">Park Central Hotel</a>:</strong> The Park Central is located a couple of blocks from Central Park on 7th Ave. at 55th St. It is within walking distance  not only to Central Park, but also to Times Square and Rockefeller Center.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>3. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/j-e-house-new-york-new-york.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">JW Marriott Essex House</a>:</strong> Located at 160 Central Park South, the <a onclick="this.target=''_blank'';" href="http://www.marriott.com/hotels/travel/nycex-jw-marriott-essex-house-new-york/">JW Marriott Essex House</a> is a New York icon, as you can see the "Essex House" sign atop the hotel from many locations in Central Park. If you''re traveling with Fido, you''ll want to check out the Essex House, as it has a pet program that allows dogs to enjoy the lap of luxury too.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>4. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/the-ritz-carlton-new-york-central-park.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">Ritz-Carlton, Central Park</a>:</strong> The Ritz is also located on Central Park South and provides stunning views of the Park and the New York skyline. It has 259 guestrooms, 47 of which are suites, and of course, the Ritz provides the ultimate luxurious five-star experience.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>5. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/trump-international-new-york.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">Trump International Hotel &amp; Tower</a>:</strong> Located in the southwest corner of the park at Columbus Circle, the Trump International Hotel &amp; Tower provides the experience that you''d expect with a Trump property. The 52-story building has 176 guest rooms with full kitchens, floor-to-ceiling windows and five-star everything. It also features a spa and a 55-foot heated swimming pool.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> {{ADSPACE_300_250}} </li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>6. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/helmsley-park-lane.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">Helmsley Park Lane</a>:</strong> The Helmsley Park Lane is a 46-story hotel on Central Park South. It offers fantastic views of the park and is convenient to midtown locales such as Broadway.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>7. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/mandarin-oriental.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">Mandarin Oriental</a>:</strong> Located in Columbus Circle, the Mandarin Oriental is a sparkly new luxurious hotel that opened in 2003. It is a five-star property with 202 guest rooms and 46 suites. If you''re doing business during your stay, amenities include versatile meeting spaces, a fully equipped business center, audio-visual capabilities and Internet access so you can conduct online conferences. You''ll just need to figure out <a title="How to Choose Your Web Conferencing Software - Set Your Business Up for Success" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.webconferenceclassroom.com/how-to-guides/how-to-choose-your-web-conferencing-software/">how to select a web conferencing services provider</a> before you go!</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>8. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/surrey.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">The Surrey</a>:</strong> The Surrey is located at 20 E. 76th St. in the Upper East Side near the Metropolitan Museum of Art. As it is a little more out of the way, the Surrey provides a bit more intimate luxury experience than some of the larger hotels on Central Park South. It has 190 guest rooms and it is also available for extended stays if you''ll be in New York for a while.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>9. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/excelsior-manhattan.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">Excelsior Hotel</a>:</strong> Across the park in the Upper West Side at 45 W. 81st St., the Excelsior is right across the street from the Museum of Natural History. It is also convenient to both Lincoln Center and Columbia University. Rooms at the Excelsior are designed in the Art Deco style and are a little cozier than rooms at other Central Park hotels. However, the prices are a little bit lower too, so this is a good option if you don''t want to break the bank during your stay.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>10. <a href="http://www.booking.com/hotel/us/the-sherry-netherland.en-us.html?aid=334464" target="_blank">The Sherry Netherland</a>:</strong> Located at the main entrance to Central Park on 5th Ave., the Sherry Netherland is one of New York&rsquo;s historic hotels. The property opened in 1927, and it boasts classical friezes in the lobby from the mansion of Cornelius Vanderbilt. The hotel also features Harry Cipriani restaurant, which gives a 20% discount to Sherry visitors who dine there.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you are traveling to Central Park, it pays to do your research ahead of time. Many of these hotels are pricey, but will offer discounts if you travel on certain days, go off-season or <a title="Hotels" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/hotels.html">book online</a>.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><em>&mdash; by Kathryn Sucich</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Kathryn Sucich is a freelance writer. When traveling, she always looks for a hotel that will provide her with amenities such as high-speed Internet service so she can work and use <a onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.webconferenceclassroom.com/reviews/web-conferencing-review/">web conferencing services</a> if necessary during her travels.</em></p>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}', 'If you''re traveling to New York and would like to explore Central Park, there''s no shortage of hotels in the area. From modest and comfortable to spacious and luxurious, the Central Park area has it a', 'hotels, accommodation', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Top 10 Places to Stay', 'Top 10 Places to Stay', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(507, '2013-08-20', 3, 1, 15, 'Exercising in Central Park - Top Activities to Keep You in Shape', '', 'activities/exercising', 'Exercising in Central Park - Top Activities to Keep You in Shape | Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<p>If you''re looking to exercise in New York City, Central Park is a big 843-acre playground with a multitude of activities. From running to biking to basketball, Central Park has it all.</p>\r\n<p>For some sports such as running or biking, there are certain rules you need to follow to keep everyone in the park safe. For example, during times that cars are allowed to drive in the park, both bikers and runners/walkers must share the recreation lane. Bikers must stay on the outer lane, while runners/walkers must stay in the inner lane. When traffic is not allowed in the park, bikers must use the drives while runners/walkers use the recreation lane.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Most Popular Activities in Central Park</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Running and Walking:</strong> There are 58 miles of pathways in Central Park, so there are endless opportunities to explore the park on your own two feet, no matter what the speed. There are three routes on the park drives on which you can run or walk; these loops are 6.1 miles (around the whole park), 5.2 miles (upper loop), and 1.7 miles (lower loop). An extremely popular route is to run around the reservoir, which is 1.58 miles and a soft surface. There are also three bridle paths on which you can run or walk that are between 1.1 and 1.5 miles long.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Baseball and Softball:</strong> There are 26 baseball and softball fields throughout the park. Eight are on the Great Lawn; 12 are in the North Meadow; and six are at Heckscher Ballfields at 63rd St. To play, your team must obtain a permit from the NYC Department of Parks/Recreation.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Biking:</strong> Bicycles are some of the <a title="The Best Cardio Exercise Equipment for Your Home Gym" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.homegymadviser.com/best-cardio-exercise-equipment.html">best cardio exercise equipment</a> around, and you&rsquo;ll get a good workout in Central Park with the varying terrains. You can bike on the three drive loops around the park; however, bikers are not allowed on the pathways, so you can only go in designated zones. If you don&rsquo;t have your own bike, you can rent one at Loeb Central Park Boathouse on the east side at 72nd St. or at several bike shops around the area, or you can also <a title="Bike Rentals" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike-rentals.html">book online</a>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Tennis:</strong> Central Park has 26 clay tennis courts and four asphalt courts. They are located at the Tennis Center, located on the west side from 94th to 96th St. The courts are open from April through November.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><strong>Bouldering:</strong> This form of rock climbing, in which climbers forgo a rope and simply climb boulders with a crash pad underneath, is gaining popularity in Central Park. Popular spots for bouldering include Rat Rock (62nd St.), Worthless Boulder (Central Park North) and Cat Rock (64th St.).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Basketball:</strong> There are two places to play hoops in Central Park. One is at the North Meadow Recreation Center; the other is at the Great Lawn. These courts are first-come, first-served. You can borrow basketballs at the North Meadow site, but you''ll have to bring your own at the Great Lawn.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Football:</strong> There''s a short season for football in Central Park. Park-goers are allowed to play from mid-September through mid-November at North Meadow. Don''t count on playing tackle football, though; only touch football and flag football are allowed.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Volleyball:</strong> If you bring your own ball and net, you can play pickup volleyball games year-round in the park on a first-come, first-served basis. There are five volleyball courts in the park. Three are east of Sheep Meadow (one sand, two asphalt) and there are two asphalt courts northeast of Great Lawn.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>That''s Not All in Terms of Exercise...</strong></p>\r\n<p>In addition, the North Meadow Recreation Center provides many opportunities for exercise. It has 12 handball courts available on a first-come, first-served basis. You can also borrow field day kits which have a variety of balls, bats, Frisbees and jump ropes. It is located mid-park at 97th St.</p>\r\n<p>There are also opportunities for fishing, cross-country skiing, ice skating and so much more. The possibilities are really endless, so bring along whatever sports equipment you have and come enjoy all that the park has to offer.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><em>&mdash; by Kathryn Sucich</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Kathryn Sucich is a freelance writer who enjoys biking, yoga and walking with her kids. If you&rsquo;re going to buy exercise equipment for your home, she finds that reading <a title="Best Home Gyms - Buying Guide &amp; Reviews" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.homegymadviser.com/">home gym reviews</a> will help you determine the best activities and equipment for your interests.</em></p>', 'If you''re looking to exercise in New York City, Central Park is a big 843-acre playground with a multitude of activities. From running to biking to basketball, Central Park has it all.', '', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 20, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Exercising', 'Exercising', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(508, '2013-08-20', 507, 2, 15, 'How to Lose Weight by Using Central Park as Your Gym', '', 'activities/exercising/how-to-lose-weight-in-central-park', 'How to Lose Weight by Using Central Park as Your Gym | Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<p>Why pay for a pricey gym when you have a free 843-acre one down the street? Manhattanites looking to lose weight can forgo the exercise bikes and elliptical machines and instead use Central Park as one big cardio and weight room.</p>\r\n<p>Central Park has 58 miles of pathways for runners and walkers and three different loops around the drives for bikers. In addition, there are many opportunities for baseball, softball, basketball, tennis and much more - enough activities to keep anyone active and on their exercise plan.</p>\r\n<p><strong>5 Central Park Activities to Lose Weight</strong></p>\r\n<p>Let''s take a look at some of the most popular activities within Central Park:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Running/Walking:</strong> You can run or walk on three different routes on the park drives. There''s the upper loop which is 5.2 miles, the lower loop which is 1.7 miles and the full loop which is 6.1 miles. You can also run around the reservoir which is a soft surface and 1.58 miles, a perfectly manageable walk or run. That&rsquo;s not to mention the many, many more miles of pathways that you can explore.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Biking:</strong> Central Park has a wide variety of terrains to challenge both the novice and the most advanced biker. You can only bike on the drives (or the recreation lanes when traffic is allowed through the park). Either bring your own bike or rent one. You can get bikes at Loeb Central Park Boathouse on the east side at 72nd St., or you can <a title="Bike Rentals" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/tours/bike-rentals.html">book online</a>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Baseball/Softball:</strong> There are 26 baseball and softball fields in Central Park, but you need to be on a team and get a permit to play. Eight fields are on the Great Lawn; 12 are in the North Meadow; and six are at Heckscher Ballfields at 63rd St.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Tennis:</strong> Tennis is great for getting in shape, and Central Park has plenty of courts. There are 26 clay tennis courts and four asphalt courts at the Tennis Center, located on the west side from 94th to 96th St. The courts are open from April through November.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Basketball:</strong> You can play hoops either at the North Meadow Recreation Center or at the Great Lawn. You can borrow basketballs at the North Meadow site, but you must bring your own at the Great Lawn. These courts are first-come, first-served.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><strong>Additional Programs to Lose Weight</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are also several special programs for those looking to shed pounds. Stroller Strides, a national franchise, has a Central Park program. People who work out with Stroller Strides walk their kids in a stroller and stop at special points to do exercises, sometimes using small weights or bands to help. The group meets at 72nd St.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, there are several boot camps that meet in Central Park. Two in particular are Stacy''s Boot Camp (<a title="STACY''S BOOTCAMP" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.stacysbootcamp.com//">www.stacysbootcamp.com</a>) and Fitness Fight Camp (<a title="Fitness Fight Camp" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.fitnessfightcamp.com/">www.fitnessfightcamp.com</a>).</p>\r\n<p>Finally, the Central Park Conservancy has a Central Park Circuit fitness program that has a series of fitness classes, each in a different location in the park. This encourages people to use new landscapes and forms of fitness in their workouts.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Make Sure You Stick to Your Diet</strong></p>\r\n<p>Of course, to lose weight, an exercise program works best when you are using it in conjunction with a diet suited to your nutritional needs and eating habits. For example, many people find that the <a title="The Comprehensive Guide to the Atkins Diet Plan" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.atkins-diet-advisor.com/">Atkins diet plan</a> works best for them, while others choose center-based programs or just do it on their own, aiming to eat more vegetables and cutting out high-calorie snacks and desserts.</p>\r\n<p>With the right diet program and exercise regimen in place, you should be able to meet your weight loss goals. And by using Central Park as a backdrop for your workout program, you''ll not only get in shape, but enjoy doing it too, helping you to make exercise a lifelong commitment.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><em>&mdash; by Kathryn Sucich</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Kathryn Sucich is a freelance writer. Before beginning an exercise program or <a title="Guide to Starting the Atkins Diet" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.atkins-diet-advisor.com/starting-the-atkins-diet.html">starting the Atkins diet</a> or other nutritional program, she urges you to talk to your doctor to make sure it''s right for you.</em></p>', 'Manhattanites looking to lose weight can forgo the exercise bikes and elliptical machines and instead use Central Park as one big cardio and weight room', 'lose weight, weight loss, diet, gym', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'How to Lose Weight in Central Park', 'How to Lose Weight in Central Park', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(509, '2014-06-04', 96, 2, 15, '10 Top Restaurants within Walking Distance of Central Park', '', 'activities/restaurants-around-central-park/top-10-restaurants-in-walking-distance', 'Top 10 Restaurants Near Central Park', '<p>There are dozens of eateries within a block or two of Central Park, from small delis and burger joints to high-end five-star restaurants. Here are 10 restaurants that are worth the walk from Central Park:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>1. Robert Restaurant:</strong> Located on the 9th floor of the Museum of Arts and Design in Columbus Circle, Robert Restaurant offers spectacular views of Central Park. On Wednesday through Saturday nights, live jazz accompanies your meal. The restaurant also offers a Sunday jazz brunch. Main courses run from $29 to $39.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>2. BG Restaurant:</strong> If you want to dine in the height of style and get your shopping done at the same time, this restaurant is on the 7th floor of the world-famous Bergdorf Goodman department store. It offers lunch, afternoon tea and bar food. Entrees range from $22 to $37.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>3. Rouge Tomate:</strong> Diners who are more health-conscious will love this restaurant which features organic foods that are optimally prepared to preserve their nutritional qualities. The restaurant is huge, spread over two floors; it is located on E. 60th St. just off of Fifth Ave. Entrees range from $26 to $37.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>4. Marea:</strong> Located on Central Park South just off of Columbus Circle, Marea means "tide" in Italian. It features regional Italian foods that are heavily influenced by the sea, such as oysters, clams and various fishes. Entrees range from $25 to $54. The restaurant also has a $97 prix fixe dinner with four courses.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>5. Sarabeth''s Central Park South:</strong> This restaurant, located between Fifth and Sixth Avenues, offers al fresco dining for breakfast, lunch, tea and dinner. Its brunch is very well known and can get crowded, but it is worth the wait. Dinner entrees range from $17 to $28.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> {{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><strong>6. Asiate:</strong> If you want sweeping floor-to-ceiling views of Central Park and the surrounding skyline, head to Asiate, located on the 35th floor of the Mandarin Oriental hotel in Columbus Circle. The restaurant features a wall of wine with 1,300 bottles. It has a three-course prix fixe menu for $90 or a tasting menu for $135.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>7. Harry Cipriani:</strong> Located at 59th St. and Fifth Ave. in the Sherry-Netherland hotel, Harry Cipriani is almost an exact replica of the original Harry''s Bar in Venice. It features Italian classics; entrees cost upwards of $35.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>8. Shake Shack:</strong> At the lower end of the price spectrum, for some of the best burgers and custard shakes in New York City, head to the famed Shake Shack at Columbus Ave. and W. 77th St., right near the Museum of Natural History. The restaurant has an enclosed sidewalk caf&eacute; as well as a "Rec Room" where you can watch games. Burgers cost between $3.55 and $8.80. Shakes are $5.00.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>9. The Leopard at Des Artistes:</strong> This restaurant on the Upper West Side on W. 67th St. serves Italian cuisine, and the d&eacute;cor is to match, with murals surrounding you as you eat. Prices here range from $28 to $45 for entrees.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>10. Caf&eacute; Sabarsky:</strong> Located at Fifth Ave. and 86th St. in the Neue Galerie, a museum of German and Austrian art, Caf&eacute; Sabarsky is named for the museum''s co-founder. It is open for breakfast, lunch and dinner, and serves traditional German and Austrian food. Sandwiches cost around $14 with entrees around $17 to $24.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Of course, these dining options are just the tip of the iceberg. There are many more restaurants within a stone&rsquo;s throw of Central Park that are sure to please.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><em>&mdash; by Kathryn Sucich</em></p>', 'There are endless activities to do within Central Park, along with endless dining options. Here are 10 restaurants that are worth the walk from Central Park.', 'restaurants, dining', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Top 10 Restaurants In Walking Distance', 'Top 10 Restaurants In Walking Distance', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(510, '2013-08-20', 3, 1, 15, 'Life in the Fast Lane - Renting an Exotic Car in Central Park', '', 'activities/exotic-cars-in-central-park', 'Life in the Fast Lane - Renting an Exotic Car in Central Park | Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<table style="margin: 10px 0 5px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img title="Exotic Car" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/exotic-cars-1.jpg" alt="Exotic Car" width="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>by <a title="CAMARO5" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.camaro5.com/forums/showthread.php?t=169076" target="_blank">CAMARO5</a></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>In the Big Apple, money makes the world go ''round. Think Trump, Rockefeller, Vanderbilt. So how can you feel like New York royalty, even for a day? One way is to rent an exotic car.</p>\r\n<p>You can rent a car at a variety of price points. For example, you can get a Chevy Corvette for about $350 per day, a Ferrari 450 Italia for $2,500 per day or a Lamborghini Murcielago LP640 Roadster for $5,000 per day. If you do get an exotic car in the city, though, the question is where do you drive it?</p>\r\n<p><strong>Central Park - Ideal for a Scenic Drive around the City</strong></p>\r\n<table style="margin: 10px 0 5px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img title="Exotic Car" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/exotic-cars-2.jpg" alt="Exotic Car" width="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>by <a title="NYC Daily Pictures" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.nycdailypics.com" target="_blank">NYC Daily Pictures</a></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>If you''re renting a luxury car, you''re probably not doing so to get from here to there. You want a joy ride, right? Central Park is ideal for this, as it offers sweeping views of the city and you''re not going to get stuck in Manhattan gridlock.</p>\r\n<p>The park has a few main drives on which you can take your car. The best place to drive to get a great view of the city is along the drives in the north end of the park. The drives here are a little more curvy and hilly, so you''re bound to see more of the city and its sights.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Driving Rules You Need to Follow</strong></p>\r\n<p>However, when driving in Central Park, you need to follow the rules. You can''t just zip around the drives, no matter how flashy and fast your car. For example, the speed limit in the park is 25 mph, and you don''t want to go over that. With the number of pedestrians and bikers in the park, going any faster is an accident waiting to happen.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, the park drives are only open during certain hours. They are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>West Drive:</strong> Open weekdays from 8:00 a.m. to 10:00 a.m. and only to high-occupancy vehicles.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>East Drive (from 72nd St./Fifth Ave. to 110th St.):</strong> Weekdays 7:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>72nd St. Cross Drive:</strong> Weekdays 8:00 a.m. to 10:00 a.m. The park is closed to all traffic from 7:00 p.m. Friday through 7:00 a.m. Monday.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n{{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p><strong>The Best Places to Rent a Car</strong></p>\r\n<table style="margin: 10px 0 5px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img title="Exotic Car" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/exotic-cars-3.jpg" alt="Exotic Car" width="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>by <a title="New Santa Ana" rel="nofollow" href="http://newsantaana.com/2012/02/05/pre-superbowl-exotic-cars-and-cockpits-meet-at-the-lyon-air-museum/" target="_blank">New Santa Ana</a></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>There are several car rental companies in Manhattan and the surrounding area that provide luxury car rentals. Some of these places include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Mach 5 Cars:</strong> Provides luxury car rentals in several areas, including New York City. The company has a selection of Ferraris, Lamborghinis, Aston Martins, Maseratis, Porsches and more. Call at (866) 730-2277 or go online at <a title="Mach 5 Cars" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.mach5cars.com/">http://www.mach5cars.com/</a>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Imagine Lifestyles: </strong> Rent everything from a luxury BMW to an ultra high-end Lamborghini. Call (866) 436-3514 or go online at <a title="Imagine Lifestyles" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.imaginelifestyles.com/">http://www.imaginelifestyles.com/</a>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Action Car Rental:</strong> This company can provide you with a bit more moderately priced cars. It has six New York locations, including three in Manhattan. Choose from BMWs, Corvettes, Escalades and more. (212) 253-2299 or <a title="Action Car Rental" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.nycexoticcarrentals.com/">http://www.nycexoticcarrentals.com/</a>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Phantoms NYC:</strong> If you want someone else to drive you around in style, this company offers chauffeured Rolls-Royces. (917) 414-0194 or <a title="Phantoms NYC" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.rollsroycelimousine.com/">www.rollsroycelimousine.com</a>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Image Rent a Car:</strong> Whether you want a Bentley Continental, a Porsche Carrera or a Corvette Convertible, you can find it here. The company will also deliver and pick-up to your door in the Tri-State area. (718) 771-6666 or <a title="IMAGE RENT A CAR" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.imagerentacar.com/">www.imagerentacar.com</a>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Where to Drive after Central Park</strong></p>\r\n<table style="margin: 10px 0 5px 5px;" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="right" bgcolor="#fff">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="center"><img title="Exotic Car" src="http://www.centralpark.com/updata/Image/activities/exotic-cars-4.jpg" alt="Exotic Car" width="150" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align="right"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><em>by <a title="Mach 5 Cars" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.mach5cars.com/category/car-posts/page/2/" target="_blank">Mach 5 Cars</a></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>After you leave Central Park, you can make your way to Madison Avenue which is host to some of the world''s highest-end shops such as Barney''s, Emporio Armani and Ralph Lauren.</p>\r\n<p>Of course, if you shop here (and also if you are driving a luxury car), you''ll also want to look the part. Before your ride, you can purchase driving clothes and accessories such as a Forzieri leather jacket, Prada driving shoes, Chopard sunglasses and <a title="Scuderia Ferrari Chrono Watches" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.enzolifestyle.com/reviews/scuderia-ferrari-chrono-watch-review/">Scuderia Ferrari Watches</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Even if you don''t have a million bucks, you can feel like you do for a day. If you do decide to rent an exotic car in Manhattan, make sure you drive safely, and also make sure you have fun!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><em>&mdash; by Kathryn Sucich</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Kathryn Sucich is a freelance writer. If she were to rent an exotic car in New York, she''d want to wear one of these <a title="Ferrari Hats &amp; Caps Review" onclick="target=''_blank''" href="http://www.enzolifestyle.com/reviews/ferrari-hats-caps-review/">Ferrari ball caps</a> while driving in an Aston Martin DB9 Volante convertible.</em></p>', 'In the Big Apple, money makes the world go ''round. So how can you feel like New York royalty, even for a day? One way is to rent an exotic car.', 'cars, scenic drive, car rental', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 26, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Exotic Cars in Central Park', 'Exotic Cars in Central Park', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(511, '2015-07-10', 417, 3, 15, 'Eating in Central Park - Where to Find the Best Food', '', 'activities/concerts/gma-concerts/eating-in-central-park-where-to-find-the-best-food', 'Eating in Central Park - Where to Find the Best Food', '<p>So you''ve been exploring Central Park for a couple of hours and all of a sudden the hunger pangs strike. Where do you go to satisfy your stomach?</p>\r\n<p>Thankfully, Central Park has endless food choices, from meat on a stick to high-class restaurants. And you don''t even need to cross Fifth Ave. or Central Park West to get to them. Let''s take a look at some of your options:</p>\r\n<p><strong>A Look at Dining Options Across the Park</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Dancing Crane Caf&eacute;:</strong> This caf&eacute; at the Central Park Zoo is open to both zoo visitors and outside patrons. It has both indoor and outdoor seating, and features relatively inexpensive fare, such as sandwiches, snacks and drinks. It is located at 64th St. and Fifth Ave.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Boathouse Restaurant:</strong> Overlooking the Lake, the Boathouse Restaurant has an express caf&eacute; as well as a more formal dining option. It is located at E. 72nd St. and Park Drive North.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Tavern on the Green:</strong> This restaurant is one of New York''s iconic dining spots, attracting thousands of diners every year, and it has also been known as the place to be seen in New York City.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Le Pain Quotidien:</strong> Located just north of Sheep Meadow on the Mineral Springs Pavilion, Le Pain Quotidien provides light fare such as sandwiches and bakery items. There are sit-down options both inside and on the terrace. You can also walk up to place your order and take it to go. The caf&eacute; provides extended-range Wi-Fi so you can check your email either on the pavilion or in nearby Sheep Meadow. It is located mid-park at 69th St.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Petrie Court Caf&eacute; and Wine Bar:</strong> If you want to sit and sip an alcoholic beverage in an elegant setting, this caf&eacute; is for you. Located in the Metropolitan Museum of Art with Central Park as a backdrop, this European-style restaurant by day serves lunch, Sunday brunch and afternoon tea, and by night transforms into a swank wine bar. It is on Fifth Ave. at 82nd St.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> {{ADSPACE_300_250}}\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Kerbs Boathouse Caf&eacute;:</strong> The Kerbs Memorial Boathouse is east of Conservatory Water, also known as the Model Boat Pond. The caf&eacute; is now run by <strong>Le Pain Quotidien </strong>which serves light snacks and beverages and it provides the perfect fare for you as you sit and watch the boats pass by. It is on the east side of the park at 74th St.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Ballplayers'' House:</strong> Next to the famed Central Park carousel and the Heckscher Ballfields, this caf&eacute; serves sandwiches, burgers and other snacks. You can sit outside and watch a ballgame on a Sunday morning or listen to the sweet sounds of kids as they enjoy the carousel. The Ballplayers'' House is located mid-park at 65th St.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong>Ferrara Italian Caf&eacute;:</strong> Located on the plaza of Merchants'' Gate at Columbus Circle, Ferrara Italian Caf&eacute; operates two kiosks. One serves gelato and smoothies; the other serves pastries, coffees and other light fare. There are a number of tables and chairs where you can sit for a bite to eat as you either enter or exit the park</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Pack a Picnic or Food on the Go</strong></p>\r\n<p>Of course, if none of these options appeal to you, you can always pack a picnic at home or by going to one of the grocery stores or delis within a short distance of Central Park (Zabars and Whole Foods are great options) and buying some picnic supplies.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, there are many food carts or trucks around Central Park where you can pick up an ice cream or an ice cold drink. These are especially convenient if you are biking around the park and can''t stop for a long period of time, or if you just need to satisfy a quick craving.</p>', 'So you''ve been exploring Central Park for a couple of hours and all of a sudden the hunger pangs strike. Where do you go to satisfy your stomach?', 'dining, eating, food, restaurants', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Where to Find the Best Food', 'Where to Find the Best Food', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(512, '2014-09-23', 447, 2, 15, 'Holiday Sights Walking Tour', '', 'tours/walking-tours/holiday-sights-tour', 'Central Park Holiday Sights Walking Tour', '<div id="toursWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="walkingTourHoliday title">Holiday Sights Walking Tour</h1>\r\n<script src="https://fareharbor.com/embeds/script/calendar-small/smyrnatours/items/1301,1349/?lightframe=yes&amp;asn=centralpark"></script>\r\n<p><strong>Experience the magic of Central Park and New York City during the holiday season!</strong></p>\r\n<img style="text-align: -webkit-center; float: right;" src="/usr/media/tours.v2/holiday-sights.jpg" border="0" alt="Holiday Sights Walking Tour" width="130" height="162" />\r\n<p>Your guide will take you on a wondrous journey that starts&nbsp;in Central Park by Grand Army Plaza and ends in Bryant Park.</p>\r\n<p>Glittering windows, a giant lit up tree, some of the world''s best hot chocolate and many unique souvenirs&nbsp;await you and your loved ones during this festive season of fun, sharing and love.</p>\r\n<p><em>Available from November 15 to January 5.</em></p>\r\n<p><span>{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Some of the sites covered on the tour include:</strong></p>\r\n<ul class="bullet">\r\n<li><a title="grand army plaza central park" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/grand-army-plaza.html">Grand Army Plaza</a></li>\r\n<li>FAO Schwartz</li>\r\n<li>Bergdorf Goodman Christmas Windows</li>\r\nSwarovski Snowflake\r\n<li>Tiffany''s, Cartier and Fendi Buildings</li>\r\n<li>St Patrick''s Cathedral</li>\r\n<li>Saks Fifth Avenue Christmas Light Show (evening tour only)</li>\r\n<li>Rockefeller Center</li>\r\n<li>Radio City Music Hall</li>\r\n<li>6th Avenue Highlights</li>\r\n<li>Bryant Park Skating Rink and Christmas Kiosks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Experience the magic of Central Park and New York City during the holiday season. You''ll be taken on a wondrous journey that starts in Central Park and ends in Bryant Park.', 'holiday, holiday tour, winter holiday tour, christmas tour', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 5, '/usr/media/tours.v2/tours.css', '/usr/media/tours.v2/tours.js', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Holiday Sights', 'Holiday Sights', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(513, '2014-05-14', 3, 1, 15, 'Famous Movie Site Attractions in Central Park', '', 'activities/movie-inspired-things-to-do', 'Famous Movie Site Attractions in Central Park', '<p>One of the reasons Central Park is one of the most visited landmarks in New York City is because this iconic attraction is featured in so many popular movie scenes. There''s the lunch scene from "When Harry Met Sally" at the Central Park Boathouse restaurant, the ice-skating scene at Wollman Rink from the romantic film "Serendipity", and also the scene of precocious Kevin from "Home Alone 2" interacting with the homeless woman who feeds the birds.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Some Famous Movie Site Attractions in Central Park</strong></p>\r\n<p>Even if it''s not likely that you&rsquo;ll be found gallavanting through the autumn landscape like one of Twyla Tharp''s dancers from the 1980s movie "Hair", there are countless other movie site attractions to experience during your time in Central Park. Here are just a few that played a part in popular movies filmed in New York City:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong><a title="Bethesda Fountain" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/bethesda-terrace/bethesda-fountain.html">Bethesda Fountain</a></strong> Overlooking the Lake in Central Park, the fountain is featured on the lower level of Bethesda Terrace. It was first unveiled in 1873 and was designed by Emma Stebbins, the first woman with the honor of receiving a public commission for a New York City major work of art. The angel atop the fountain is accompanied by a quartet of cherubs that represent Temperance, Purity, Peace, and Health and has been seen in movies like Stuart Little 2, Godspell, and Ransom; on television shows like Gossip Girl and Law &amp; Order; and also in the video game Grand Theft Auto IV.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong><a title="The Bandshell" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/bandshell.html">The Bandshell</a></strong> Its official name is the Naumburg Bandshell, and it''s been featured in movies such as Breakfast at Tiffany''s and Hair. However, the Bandshell is actually used for concerts and other stage events featuring groups like the New York Philharmonic, the Metropolitan Opera, and the Washington Square Music Festival. Good Morning America and the Today Show have both used the Bandshell to feature popular music artists as a way to boost their television ratings. Most of the events that take place at the Bandshell are free, and appeal to people of all ages.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li> <span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;"><span style="background: #efefef; color: green; padding: 2px;">{{ADSPACE_300_250}}</span></span>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong><a title="The Conservatory Garden" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/conservatory-garden.html">The Conservatory Garden</a></strong> Of all the places in the 843 acres that make up Central Park, the Conservatory Garden is possibly the most earth-friendly. This attraction is actually made up of three smaller gardens, one each in the style of English, French, and Italian landscaping. Because the city has designated the Conservatory Garden as an official Quiet Zone, don''t be surprised if you run into a couple tying the knot or children visiting the memorial fountain that pays tribute to Frances Hodgson Burnett''s classic tale, The Secret Garden. Stuart Little also raced his boats in the pond there.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong><a title="Trump Wollman Skating Rink" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/wollman-rink.html">Trump Wollman Skating Rink</a></strong> While many film buffs know that iconic couples from the romantic movies Love Story and Serendipity both skated here, they''d be surprised to learn that in the summer the landmark actually transforms into the Victorian Gardens Amusement Park. As the rink''s name suggests, the Trump organization currently operates it in conjunction with a company from Virginia. The rink is an entertaining place to visit during any season, and it also offers a breathtaking view of the surrounding New York City skyline both day and night.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>&raquo; <strong><a title="Tavern on the Green" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/tavern-on-the-green.html">Tavern on the Green</a></strong> Most film buffs will associate this iconic Central Park landmark with movies like Ghostbusters, Edward Scissorhands, Beaches, Stella, and The Flintstones. Tavern on the Green has also been&nbsp;<span>frequented by famous artists and celebrities such as Grace Kelly and Fay Wray. John Lennon celebrated several of his birthdays at Tavern on the Green in the late 70''s, and it was the restaurant of choice for many opening night Broadway show festivities</span>. In 2009 the restaurant closed down after filing for bankruptcy, reopening again in 2010 as an information center and gift shop. However, in 2012 it was closed&nbsp;once again, this time for renovations. After a long-anticipated wait, <a title="tavern on the green" href="http://www.centralpark.com/guide/attractions/tavern-on-the-green.html">Tavern on the Green</a> re-opened in April of 2014 as a restaurant and is once again accepting reservations.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>About the author:<br /></em><span style="font-style: italic;">Successful internet entrepreneur Kimberly Juchnowski is also a travel writer, inspired by her love of exploring the globe.</span></p>', 'Here are a few famous attractions to visit that were inspired by popular movies filmed in Central Park.', 'popular places to visit in central park, movie tours central park, movie sites central park, bethesda fountain, bandshell, conservatory garden, trump wollman skating rink, wollman rink, ice skating central park, tavern on the green, top places to visit central park, central park in the movies, central park attractions', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 2, '', '', 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, '5 Movie-Inspired Central Park Things to Do', '5 Movie-Inspired Central Park Things to Do', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(514, '2014-08-26', 452, 1, 14, 'Private & Corporate Events', '', 'special-events/private-corporate-events', 'Private & Corporate Events | Central Park Your Complete Guide at CentralPark.com', '<div id="spEventsWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="privateCorporateEvents title">Private &amp; Corporate Events</h1>\r\n<ul class="eventsList sublistEvents">\r\n<li class="tbop"><a title="Team Building Office Picnic" href="/guide/special-events/team-building-office-picnic.html">Team Building Office Picnic 				<span>Play, learn and grow with your company!</span> <span>Teamwork makes the dream work!</span> </a> </li>\r\n<li class="sgp"> <a title="Softball Game &amp; Picnic" href="/guide/special-events/softball-game-picnic.html">Softball Game &amp; Picnic 				<span>There''s no place like home base!</span> <span>Homeruns and Hotdogs!</span> </a> </li>\r\n<li class="idnypwr"> <a title="I Do New York Picnic Wedding Reception" href="/guide/special-events/picnic-wedding-reception.html">I Do New York Picnic Wedding Reception 				<span>Celebrate your wedding day with a picnic in the park... </span> <span>Have your cake and eat it too!</span> </a> </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '', '', 0.00, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '/usr/media/special-events/style.css', '', 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 'Private & Corporate Events', 'Private & Corporate Events', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
